  {name: "JIBE", num_employees: 18, total_money_raised: "$20.9M", twitter_username: "jibe", category_code: "enterprise", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2010, overview: "JIBE builds SaaS recruiting solutions that enable leading companies to hire the best talent, regardless of their existing systems. We are dedicated to making recruiting simple with solutions for enterprises to attract and engage candidates using the latest technology.\n\nJIBE partners with companies across all industries, including Walmart, Wells Fargo, Macy&#8217;s, AT&amp;T, General Motors, Accenture and UPS, bringing them a single platform to power candidate experience without changing their applicant tracking system (ATS).\n\nOur solutions include:\n\n-The first and only solution that allows a jobseeker to submit a complete job application from any device - mobile, tablet and desktop.\n-A candidate-generated employee referral solution.\n-A browser-based solution designed for distributed recruiting teams.\n\nJIBE is headquartered in New York City and also has offices in Washington, D.C. and Oakland, California."},
  {name: "JOOR", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$20.1M", twitter_username: "JOORACCESS", category_code: "fashion", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2010, overview: "JOOR is an online wholesale marketplace for the women&#8217;s contemporary fashion industry created by Mona Bijoor, veteran fashion buyer and corporate strategist.\n\nJOOR&#8217;s vision is to offer the search features and social networking functionality to the wholesale sector to streamline communication, discovery, and buying. Brands can feature their collections, prospect for new boutiques and manage all of their orders online. \n\nJOOR provides direct access to a brands&#8217; sales team and inventory availability so that boutiques have real time access to buying information. "},
  {name: "Kaptur", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$2M", twitter_username: nil, category_code: "photo_video", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: nil, overview: "Kaptur is a website and mobile application that algorithmically finds and collects everyone&#8217;s photos from any event, instantly. Kaptur grew organically to over 1 Million registered users before eventually merged with AHALife. In its early days, Kaptur formed partnerships with Beyonce, David Guetta, GetMarried, and RedBull.  "},
  {name: "Kapture", num_employees: 7, total_money_raised: "$0", twitter_username: "Kapture", category_code: "mobile", city: "Brooklyn", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2012, overview: "Kapture is a mobile app that connects businesses with consumers by offering perks for taking and sharing photos. Our goal is to help businesses engage with consumers and leverage the photos taken of their products and services to increase customer loyalty and acquisition."},
  {name: "TickPick", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$0", twitter_username: "iTickpick", category_code: "games_video", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2011, overview: "TickPick is an innovative new ticket marketplace that aims to take the struggle out of purchasing tickets to sports, concerts and other live events. They designed their site to eliminate the overwhelming number of overpriced tickets. Ticket results are listed and ranked based on a combination of price and quality, which allows people to select the best ticket for them at a glance."},
  {name: "Yapp", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$1M", twitter_username: "yapp", category_code: "mobile", city: "New York City", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: nil, overview: "With Yapp, it&#8217;s a snap to create great looking mobile applications. You don&#8217;t have to be a tech guru or a millionaire to have your own mobile application. Go ahead, App Yourself at http://yapp.us. "},
  {name: "BigTwist", num_employees: 7, total_money_raised: "$620k", twitter_username: "bigtwistpres", category_code: "enterprise", city: "Brooklyn", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: "NA", year_founded: 2011, overview: "BigTwist helps business professionals easily create stunning and interactive presentations."},
  {name: "Trendabl", num_employees: 3, total_money_raised: "$2.86M", twitter_username: "Trendabl", category_code: "fashion", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2012, overview: "Trendabl is a fashion focused photo-sharing iPhone app that will launch in March 2012. Members will be able take pictures of anything fashion related, add a filter and tag the photos with info such as brands, store, color and price. Users will be able to share these posts with their friends or whoever follows them. Users will also be able to follow their favorite fashion icons, celebrities, designers, stylists, magazines, bloggers and websites. Many more details to come as we approach our launch date! Stay tuned&#8230;"},
  {name: "Tumblr", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$125M", twitter_username: "tumblr", category_code: "web", city: "New York", twitter_followers: 1512222, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2007, overview: "Tumblr is a re-envisioning of tumblelogging, a subset of blogging that uses quick, mixed-media posts. The service hopes to do for the tumblelog what services like LiveJournal and Blogger did for the blog. The difference is that its extreme simplicity will make luring users a far easier task than acquiring users for traditional weblogging. Anytime a user sees something interesting online, they can click a quick &#8220;Share on Tumblr&#8221; bookmarklet that then tumbles the snippet directly. The result is varied string of media ranging links and text to pictures and videos that takes very little time and effort to maintain.\n\nThere is little to no learning curve involved in using tumblr. Features are intuitive and quick to establish.  Users simply sign up and begin posting in a minute.\n\nTumblr is backed by Union Square Ventures, Spark Capital and Sequoia Capital."},
  {name: "Aggregift", num_employees: 6, total_money_raised: "$0", twitter_username: "aggregift", category_code: "web", city: "New York", twitter_followers: 138, career_page_link: "NA", year_founded: nil, overview: "Aggregift is a group gifting service that helps you celebrate special occasions with your friends. We saw many of our closest friends&#8217; birthdays go by with the standard wall posts and text message but doing something meaningful was still difficult. We’ve spent our time rethinking why and how people celebrate. Aggregift is a new way to celebrate with friends without spending a lot of time or money.\n\nWhen friends pitch in together, you can give that awesome gift that may normally be outside of a single person&#8217;s price range. We help you tap into the potential of social networks to make celebrating a special day seamless, social and fun. Other friends don’t need to spend the time deciding what to get. They can participate easily, knowing the recipient is getting something they’ll love.\n\nOver the course of the special occasion, your friend gets the unique experience of seeing those closest to them come together to celebrate, no matter where they are."},
  {name: "Altruik", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$9.5M", twitter_username: "altruik", category_code: "search", city: "New York", twitter_followers: 358, career_page_link: "http://www.altruik.com/about/careers", year_founded: 2009, overview: "Altruik is focused on making search engine optimization easy and scalable for eCommerce companies and online businesses. By using their technology to increase visibility in the search engines, companies can generate more site traffic, more visits to their content and product inventory pages, and higher click-through rates.\n\nTheir automated Search Engine Optimization (SEO) solution easily integrates with all Content Management Systems (CMS) and legacy systems and efficiently manages the search engine optimization process. Plus, it offers several advantages over other options by:\n\n\nHandling many of the labor-intensive and tedious tasks associated with implementing site-wide SEO changes. As a result, eCommerce companies and site owners save the time and ongoing cost of ensuring that their site content is visible to prospective customers\nEnsuring that SEO best practices are implemented in a way that is fully compliant with the search engines\nSeamlessly overcoming SEO barriers created by a companyâ€™s infrastructure, including inflexible legacy or Content Management Systems, limited technology resources, and lack of access to relevant performance and search data\n"},
  {name: "AlleyNYC", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$0", twitter_username: "AlleyNYC", category_code: nil, city: nil, twitter_followers: 39163, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2012, overview: "Alleynyc is a 16,000 square foot entrepreneurial hub, where teams  and individuals can grow there businesses surrounded by like minded people, and work collaboratively in a supportive environment. \n\nWe have a mixed between private offices and shared open desk space, offering month 2 month affordable membership plans. Much like a gym membership. \n\nThe amenities we offer at AlleyNYC, are tools to support entrepreneurship and assist with the growth of businesses in all different verticals. "},
  {name: "AlleyWatch", num_employees: 6, total_money_raised: "$40k", twitter_username: "alleywatch", category_code: "news", city: "New York", twitter_followers: 2891, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2012, overview: "AlleyWatch is the destination for startup news; opinions and reviews; investment and product information; events reported, experienced, seen, heard and overheard in New York and beyond. \n\nBut it’s who we are that’s makes us different: we’re the writers and the entrepreneurs; the investors and the mentors; the lawyers and the marketers; the realtors and the recruiters – the people who work in the industry. Which makes our content the insights and observations of startup scene insiders deconstructing the systems we inhabit to tell the stories that no one else can. \n\nWe want to hear about your trials and triumphs, your battles fought and lessons learned: the stories that go untold from the people who go unnoticed. AlleyWatch is here to fill the gap in startup coverage with news, resources and information to connect the community here in New York, the city that never sleeps, filled with dreamers who don’t stop until the world wakes up and takes notice."},
  {name: "Amicus", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$3.78M", twitter_username: "amicusHQ", category_code: "nonprofit", city: "New York", twitter_followers: 3676, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: nil, overview: "Amicus empowers cause-driven organizations to leverage the social networks of their supporters, raise more money, attract more members, and win more votes. "},
  {name: "AppAddictive", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$1.2M", twitter_username: nil, category_code: "advertising", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: nil, overview: "AppAddictive is a platform for businesses to acquire customers, engage customers, and retain customers through social media.\n\nHow?\nAcquire customers\n\n\nUse our drag and drop tools to create promotions and Facebook pages that turn visitors to likes and customers. Add that with our Ad Optimizer to acquire customers that save time and money.\nEngage customers\n-Use our community manager tool to publish engaging posts that encourage commenting and posts from your customers. \nRetain customers\n-Use our social loyalty platform to retain and increase revenues of your existing customers. Use your existing loyal customers to bring you new customers.\n"},
  {name: "Tutorspree", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$1.8M", twitter_username: "tutorspree", category_code: "education", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2010, overview: "Tutorspree finds the perfect tutor for every student, for every subject.\n\nTutorspree is solving the discovery, matching, scheduling and payment inefficiencies in a $7B domestic market. We do this by combining our deep and growing roster of over 5000 active tutors with technology that creates ideal pairings between students and tutors."},
  {name: "Tykoon", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$1.83M", twitter_username: "tykoonnation", category_code: "finance", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: nil, overview: "Tykoon (currently in private beta) is a new social, personalized financial services platform for families where kids can earn, save, give and spend real money. With Tykoon, parents can implement money management via chores, jobs, allowance, spending and giving. Kids can earn money through jobs, chores, and gifts, save based on goals, spend in a kid safe environment powered by Amazon.com and give to charities via the platform. "},
  {name: "AppFirst", num_employees: 17, total_money_raised: "$16.2M", twitter_username: "appfirst", category_code: "analytics", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2009, overview: "AppFirst delivers powerful, yet simple application monitoring to provide DevOps professionals and Tech Execs with full-stack visibility into systems, applications, and business metrics.   Our SaaS-based DevOps Dashboard is powered by a flexible big data platform that collects, analyzes, and correlates numerous sources of data &#8211; from logs to StatsD to Nagios plug-ins to millions of low-level process metrics. With our beautiful, configurable dashboards, you can easily monitor the information that’s important to your organization, enabling you to quickly troubleshoot problems and stay on top of what’s happening in real time with the systems and the business.\n\nUnlike other application management solutions that take weeks to implement, AppFirst starts monitoring your data in literally minutes.  Forget about spending valuable resources on programming or development; we’ve done the hard work for you, allowing you to focus on your core business. Finally, there’s an easy, affordable solution that brings application management and server monitoring to an entirely new level &#8211; and combines it with unprecedented business visibility.\n\nBy integrating business performance and system metrics into a single repository, AppFirst enables you to:\nResolve issues quickly and proactively\nUnderstand how infrastructure performance impacts the business\nGet unified visibility into the metrics and data sources that are important to your organization\nBe up and running in minutes with an affordable SaaS-based solution\n\nWhether you manage one server or thousands, we have the right plan for your organization: sign up today for our Free Plan and automatically test-drive premium features free for 14 days."},
  {name: "Applico", num_employees: 75, total_money_raised: "$0", twitter_username: "ApplicoMobile", category_code: "mobile", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2009, overview: "Applico helps businesses turn their products into platforms.\n\nApplico is trailblazing a new type of services firm, the platform innovation company. It is our belief that platforms are the key business model in the Connected Revolution, and as technology leaders and visionaries we help position our clients to compete where the market is going - not where it is today.\n\nAt Applico, our end-to-end services will provide you with all the help you need to build and scale platforms. Our clients can leverage the full complement of our strategy, platform development, design and multi-faceted technology departments to turn products into innovative platforms that disrupt markets and invigorate internal cultural shifts."},
  {name: "Architizer", num_employees: 12, total_money_raised: "$2M", twitter_username: "architizer", category_code: "enterprise", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2009, overview: "Architizer is the largest and fastest growing source for architecture online. The world&#8217;s architecture is uploaded directly by the people who make it. This intimate relationship attracts a well-educated and affluent crowd who likes good design and great architecture. "},
  {name: "Atavist", num_employees: 15, total_money_raised: "$3.43M", twitter_username: "theatavist", category_code: "software", city: "Brooklyn", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: "https://www.atavist.com/jobs/", year_founded: 2009, overview: "Atavist Inc. operates as a media and software company. The company develops software to create digital publications for mobile applications, the Web, and e-readers. It provides The Atavist, a longform magazine and e-singles publication. The company was founded in 2009 and is based in Brooklyn, New York."},
  {name: "Behance", num_employees: 30, total_money_raised: "$6.5M", twitter_username: "Behance", category_code: "web", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: "http://www.behance.net/careers", year_founded: 2006, overview: "Behance is on a mission to organize and empower the creative world. Behance is the leading online platform to showcase and discover creative work. Creative professionals broadcast their work widely and efficiently, and companies access talent on a global scale. Millions use Behance to display and find talent every month. Behance&#8217;s platform also serves as the backbone for AdWeek, LinkedIn, and thousands of other portfolio sites and online galleries of creative talent.\n\nBehance&#8217;s platform attracts millions of visitors who come to discover top talent, along with powering creative networks for top schools and organizations, distributing work to other online galleries, and enabling portfolio display throughout the social web. And with Behance ProSite, members can create fully customizable personal portfolio sites that sync with their work on Behance, for maximum efficiency and reach. \n\nBy the Winter of 2011, Behance (Behance.net (be.net) and its associated category-specific &#8220;Served sites&#8221;) was receiving over 50 million pageviews from over 9 million visitors per month. \n\nBehance&#8217;s other projects that empower creative professionals:\n\nTHE 99% (the99percent.com) The 99% is Behance&#8217;s think tank and conference, devoted to researching best practices of the world’s most productive creative people. Its daily web magazine shares tips and insights on idea execution. Its annual conference takes place in New York City every spring and has included such luminaries as Fred Wilson, Jack Dorsey, and Seth Godin. The conference sells out a year in advance and serves as a powerful brand building initiative for Behance.\n\nACTION METHOD (actionmethod.com) The Action Method is an intuitive approach to task management, designed to help creative thinkers push their ideas into action."},
  {name: "BioDigital", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$4.45M", twitter_username: "biodigitalhuman", category_code: "biotech", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: "https://www.biodigitalhuman.com/home/jobs.html", year_founded: 2002, overview: "Back in 2002, BioDigital was founded on the premise that 3D technology could transform the way we understand health and medicine. The founders had witnessed its impact on gaming and Hollywood, and were determined to apply state-of-the-art 3D to healthcare as well. Together they opened BioDigital Systems – a biomedical visualization company – in New York City, and over the years, they have helped make biomedical information more accessible for a diverse list of clients, including hospitals, biotech and medical device companies, pharmaceuticals, non-profit organizations, and academic institutions.\n\nThe reactions to BioDigital&#8217;s 3D storytelling – from patients, physicians, healthcare providers, and educators - were so positive that in 2010, BioDigital decided to expand their technology to empower anyone with Internet access to learn about the human body - in a way that resembles life itself. A year later, the BioDigital Human was born. This interactive, medically accurate virtual body enables users to study anatomy, disease, and treatments. The platform is constantly evolving, as our team of software engineers, 3D animators, physicians, and scientists – all with specialized biology training – continue to add both content and features."},
  {name: "BestVendor", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$4.2M", twitter_username: "bestvendor", category_code: "software", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2011, overview: "BestVendor is a free online resource that helps professionals quickly find the best software, apps, and services based on the recommendations of people like them. The company&#8217;s vision is to provide a Yelp-like &#8220;social discovery&#8221; resource for all business tools and services, and bring a lot more sharing and openness to the business purchasing process. Beta signup is available at http://www.bestvendor.com"},
  {name: "Acquaintable", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$40k", twitter_username: "acquaintable", category_code: "web", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2012, overview: "Acquaintable is reinventing online dating by enabling people to meet friends-of-friends. Around 70% of people meet their significant other through friends. However, the major players in the dating space like Match.com introduce users to strangers. Acquaintable shows users a curated feed of friends-of-friends and allows users to message each other only if they both indicate they are interested. Acquaintable takes the creepiness out of online dating.  "},
  {name: "adMarketplace", num_employees: 90, total_money_raised: "$0", twitter_username: "adMarketplace", category_code: "search", city: "New York", twitter_followers: 1001, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2000, overview: "adMarketplace delivers performance in search syndication advertising for online marketers and agencies.\n\nadMarketplace is the creator of Advertiser 3D, the first and only Pay Per Click platform to allow optimizations by keyword, traffic source, and device type. Operating the largest search network outside of the major search engines, adMarketplace works with major online brands and agencies to deliver search performance at scale. \n\nFounded in 2000 by CEO James Hill, adMarketplace provides search advertisers with the simple, transparent control needed to drive ROI. The company was the first to incorporate bidding by traffic source, and then introduced device type bidding to the industry before enhanced campaigns for AdWords. \n\nThousands of advertisers rely on adMarketplace for PPC performance. Advertiser 3D is offered to major brands and agencies as a Managed Service, or as a Self-Serve option for smaller advertisers. 3D’s flexible and transparent XML integration, in combination with granular traffic source bidding, lets quality web publishers easily monetize their inventory."},
  {name: "8coupons", num_employees: 4, total_money_raised: "$0", twitter_username: "8coupons", category_code: "web", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2007, overview: "8coupons is the largest hub for deals near you.\n\nTh primary discovery and comparison engine for deals on places to eat, drink, shop, and do stuff nearby, 8coupons offers a variety of deals in every zip code throughout the U.S. from content partners like Groupon, Restaurant.com, Amazon, GrubHub, eBay, LivingSocial, Google, Valpak, and others, \n8coupons is committed to helping people make the most out of their daily lives by getting the right content, to the right person, at the right time, in the right place. "},
  {name: "Boxee", num_employees: 45, total_money_raised: "$26.5M", twitter_username: "boxee", category_code: "software", city: "Tel Aviv", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: "NA", year_founded: 2004, overview: "Boxee is a partially open-source freeware media player software platform that integrates personal locally stored media with Internet streaming media along with social networking features.  Boxee&#8217;s social networking component allows users to share information about what they are watching or listening to with other boxee users or friends on social networks like Twitter, Facebook, etc.\n\nSince it is partially open source, users can create their own apps, plug-ins, and skins for it.\n\nThe framework for Boxee is based on source code from the Xbox Media Center project, a software originally created by Home Theater PC enthusiasts for the first-generation Xbox."},
  {name: "Branch", num_employees: 6, total_money_raised: "$2M", twitter_username: "branch", category_code: "web", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: "NA", year_founded: 2011, overview: "Branch (formerly Roundtable) enables a smart new brand of high quality public discourse. Curated groups of people are invited to engage around issues in which they are knowledgeable. This service holds the promise of a new platform for dialogue on the web—a necessary departure from the monologues we have grown so accustomed to reading online."},
  {name: "Canvas", num_employees: 32, total_money_raised: "$11.1M", twitter_username: "GoCanvas", category_code: "mobile", city: "Reston", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2008, overview: "Canvas subscribers will be able to use their mobile devices to collect data in a simple form or survey fashion but will do so in a manner in which takes full advantage of the unique data collection capabilities that are available on today&#8217;s modern handsets.   \n\nCanvas solutions are delivered in a simple subscription service that brings Web 2.0 features and wireless technology together allowing users to define and deploy forms and surveys to mobile devices, collect data, review the results and integrate to their own systems. By providing a generic tool that can be tailored to any need, Canvas can be used by any non-software developer to allow users to go wireless, go green, go Canvas in minutes. \n\nCanvas realizes that the unique features of today&#8217;s handsets can allow new data â€œtypesâ€\u009D to be captured.  These include image, video and voice capture, GPS/Location Based Data, barcode scanning and time date stamps.  When combined with the common data forms or surveys that users have mobilized, a new range of analysis and insight is now possible.  \n\nAll of this for less than the cost of the paper it is replacing&#8230;..  "},
  {name: "Chalkable", num_employees: 5, total_money_raised: "$1.3M", twitter_username: "chalkable", category_code: "education", city: "NY", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 2010, overview: "Chalkable is an app store for school and a platform to make those apps work.\n\nApp store.\nAmazing digital tools and content can transform the way students learn in school. The Chalkable app store lists the best education apps from across the web. You can browse apps by category, such as History, Math, Science, and more. When you find an app you like, click to buy it.\n\nPlatform.\nLots of Apps. One login. One calendar. One gradebook. It all just works. The Chalkable platform is a basic set of tools for students, teachers, admins, and parents. We built the Feed, Calendar, Grading, Messaging and more to make using Apps simple.\n\nThe most powerful tools and most immersive content live on the web. With the Chalkable App store and platform, schools gain access&#8230;and that makes for a better learning experience.\n\nChalkable costs $10 a year per student. Half that money goes straight to teacher, student, and admin starting app budgets."},
  {name: "CheetahMail", num_employees: nil, total_money_raised: "$0", twitter_username: nil, category_code: "web", city: "New York", twitter_followers: nil, career_page_link: nil, year_founded: 1998, overview: "CheetahMail provides a wide range of online marketing solutions enterprise companies. CheetahMail&#8217;s client list includes Barclays, Borders Books, Discovery Communications, H&amp;R Block, KLM, Sears Holdings Corporation and Wyndham Hotels. CheetahMail is a business unit of Experian Group (LSE:EXPN)."},
