s and experiences to try out. Your friends go to you when looking for recommendations. Will build relationships and negotiate with existing and new partners Want to grow over time, taking on new responsibly and roles Your goals are to... Build a new “storefront” each month Buy at least 50 products per month Maintain existing relationships with our partners Identify and build relationships with new partners The ideal person… Has merchandising experience in a prior role Has a strong resume that shows you’re ready to take on lots of new responsibility Want to really impress us? Send us images, descriptions and prices of 3 products that you think our customers would love. Explain why they would love them. Figure out how to email us directly. If you’re not up for the challenge, simply email jobs@bespokepost.com Back to top Operations & Customer Service Associate We're looking for an energetic and detailed-oriented individual who wants to join a fast-growing commerce company at the ground level. You'll have direct ownership of the business operations and relationship with our warehouse in Louisville, You’ll be helping to manage our customer service channels (phone, email, and social networks). You… Will own the day-to-day relationship with our off-site warehouse to make sure outbound logistics are running like clockwork. Should be comfortable with your quantitative skills. Experience with Excel is required; experience with SQL is a plus. If you don’t have the latter, you should be comfortable learning it very quickly. Will be obsessed with making sure all orders placed are accurately fulfilled each day Can think on your feet and are willing to do whatever it takes to make things right for our customers when things go wrong. Should be comfortable talking with customers and bringing your personality into the fold. We’re not going for robotic responses. Want to grow over time, taking on new responsibilities and roles. Will own key reporting metrics, working to support multip