  {link: "http://www.smartling.com/careers/productmarketingmgr", title: "Product Marketing Manager", full_text: "Contact Sales Blog +1 866.70.SMART Login Solutions Websites Apps Documents Enterprise Clients Resources About Our Story Our Team Press Investors Contact Us Careers Open Positions Translator Signup Product Marketing Manager Careers > Product Marketing Manager Job Opportunity Overview Objective To drive adoption of the Smartling Platform with prospects, customers and translators. Overview The Product Marketing Manager will collaborate with Product Management, Engineering, Client Services and Sales to drive adoption of the Smartling platform with all our stakeholders. As Smartling releases new features, services and platform functionality, the Product Marketing Manager will develop and execute go-to-market plans. Reports To VP of Marketing // Director, Content Strategy Responsibilities Be the expert on all categories of Smartling buyers, who they are and how they buy with a deep understanding of their buying criteria. Use this knowledge to inform the product development and prioritization process. Gather competitive intelligence, manage the Smartling Competitive Playbook and roll it out to Sales and other stakeholders on a quarterly basis. Craft messaging and positioning for the Smartling Platform, clearly articulating the value proposition, benefits and technical requirements for each customer segment and buyer profile. Plan the launch of new features and services, managing the cross-functional implementation of the go-to-market plan, including market messages, sales materials and client communications. Regularly contribute content to the Smartling Blog and monthly newsletter to keep our community informed and engaged. Manage the client success story and testimonial program, this includes partnering with client services to identify success stories, make contact, conduct interviews, draft copy and distribute the final product to our community. Own and roll-out the Smartling Customer Playbook to Sales and other stakeholders on a quarterly basis. Requirements 3-5 years experience in technology product marketing, experience with SaaS strongly preferred Strong writing skills that showcase a proven ability to translate “tech speak” into powerful client benefits A creative thinker who brings fresh ideas, new perspectives and lots of enthusiasm An effective communicator who can work with cross-functional teams, manage complex projects and get things done under tight deadlines Must know how to thrive in fast-paced environment where change is the only constant Personal Characteristics Excellent interpersonal and communication skills Well-organized, with great attention to detail Creative, Curious, Global-minded Enjoys learning new technologies and data analysis techniques Enjoyable to work with Cultural Fit Teamwork – works well with others within team and across groups in company Customer Focused – passion for customer success and referenceability, always willing to solve customer problems and delight customers Execution Success – plans and meets/exceeds objectives on time and with quality Entrepreneurial – flexible, optimistic, problem-solving approach Leadership and Initiative – does the right thing without being asked, proactive at dealing with issues Apply Now Are you a translation provider? Sign up to be part of the Smartling Translator Network Sign Up What can we help you translate? Websites Apps Documents Enterprise Request a Demo Home Blog Dashboard Contact Sales Solutions Websites Apps Documents Enterprise Clients Resources About Our Story Team Investors Press Careers Open Positions Translator Signup Contact Us Smartling, Inc. 475 Park Ave S Floor 23 New York, NY 10016 +1 866.70.SMARThi@smartling.com Facebook LinkedIn Pinterest Twitter Tweet English Nederlands Español Deutsch Français Italiano Português 日本語 中文 ©2009–2014 Smartling, Inc. | Privacy Policy | Terms | Smartly built in NYC | Smartling Status", is_draft: tru