  {link: "http://www.yodlecareers.com/jobs/new-york/national-account-manager/", title: "National Account Manager", full_text: "Services Success Stories Company Brand Networks Contact Call646-770-8905 Yodle Careers Departments Client Services Corporate Product and Marketing Sales Technology Locations New York Atlanta Austin Charlotte Scottsdale Job Listings Culture Events Employee Reviews Benefits & Perks Blog Job Details Department Sales Type Full-Time Date 12/9/2013 Location Yodle New York 50 W 23rd St Suite 401 New York, NY 10010 Yodle Careers› National Account Manager Yodle is looking for a smart and motivated sales professional to join our National Accounts team. This individual will have the proven ability to both penetrate corporate franchises and associations as well as work with and close deals with the small/medium sized businesses (SMB) within the corporate entity. We want proactive individuals who aren’t afraid to dive in head first and acquire new business. Responsibilities You will be consulting and selling to CEO’s and CMO’s of large corporations and franchisers. You will be responsible for prospecting and working closely with these companies to help them see the value of using Yodle services across all of their locations and overseeing the onboarding of the individual locations. On a day to day basis ,you will be prospecting opportunities, giving online demonstrations, traveling to corporate headquarters to present Yodle’s product and negotiating corporate offerings. This is an individual contributor role that requires some travel. Qualifications Prior experience selling SEO/SEM products to franchises. 3+ years experience with presenting to and working closely with C-Level employees and VPs of marketing 7+ years selling experience; at least 3 successful years in a new business role 3+ years experience making outbound telephone calls and holding face to face meetings with small and medium businesses (SMB). Web based sales preferred Experience creating and giving power point presentations to groups of C-Level employees Experience with a 3-6 month sales cycle Proven ability to quickly develop relationships and build trust with C-Level decision makers Well organized, independent, resourceful and diligent in maintaining CRM data Why Work at Yodle? Yodle offers excellent medical benefits packages for you and your family, including a pet insurance discount for your four-legged furry friends! Each office location offers its own unique set of perks such as free lunch, food trucks, contests, chair massages, gym memberships, commuter benefits, and don't forget about company happy hours! Explore some key benefits of working at Yodle by clicking below. Benefits & Perks Yodle is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Yodle's policy is to select, place, train, and promote the best qualified individuals based upon relevant factors such as work quality, attitude and experience, so as to provide equal employment opportunity for all our employees in compliance with applicable local, state, and federal laws and without regard to non-work related factors such as race, color, religion/creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, marital status, sexual orientation, veteran status, or any other protected class. Job Tools Apply Print Email Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Apply Yodle Talent Network Joining our Talent Network will enhance your job search and application process. Whether you choose to apply or just leave your information, we look forward to staying connected with you. Join Our Talent Network Awards Best Companies to Work for in New York State Yodle Partners Yodle Social © Yodle, Inc. All Rights Reserved. Yodle® is a registered trademark. All other marks are the property of their respective owners. FAQ / Terms / Privacy @YodleCareers General Application Let's Make This Happen. You fill out the form. We'll be in touch. Please click on this link to apply.. National Account Manager — New York, NY Let's Make This Happen. You fill out the form. We'll be in touch. Please click on this link to apply..National Account Manager Join Our Talent Community. Receive job updates and stay in touch with our hiring team. Thank You We'll be in touch with you shortly. Email In Use Personal Information * = Required First Name Last Name Email Phone Number Locations of Interest New York City (HQ) Austin Boston Charlotte Scottsdale Departments of Interest Client Services Corporate Product and Marketing Sales Technology Join", is_draft: true, company_id: 1034, dept: "Sales", years_exp: 5, sub_dept: "Account Management", description: "Yodle is looking for a smart and motivated sales professional to join our National Accounts team. This individual will have the proven ability to both penetrate corporate franchises and associations as well as work with and close deals with the small/medium sized businesses (SMB) within the corporate entity. We want proactive individuals who arent afraid to dive in head first and acquire new business.", key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://www.atavist.com/jobs/", title: "iOS Developer", full_text: "Atavist – Where Stories Begin Navigation Creatavist Featured Clients Creatavist Beta Stories About Us FAQ Our Story People Media Blog Jobs Contact LoginLoginForgot your password?Subscribe You are here: Home > Jobs Jobs Atavist is a media and software company at the forefront of digital, mobile publishing. Our mission is to enable the next generation of multimedia storytelling, reaching readers across mobile devices and the Web. Our storytelling platform, Creatavist, allows anyone from writers, to photographers and filmmakers, to corporations and other organizations, to build beautiful, interactive, mobile-friendly books, magazines, reports, and apps. We are backed by Eric Schmidt, Andreessen Horowitz, Founders Fund, and Barry Diller/IAC, among others. Our flagship publishing arm, The Atavist—built on Creatavist—features original pieces of bestselling, award-wining longform nonfiction. Our new partnership to produce innovative fiction and nonfiction books, Atavist Books, launches next year. All jobs are based in our Brooklyn loft—a casual, creative, dog-friendly environment. All jobs offer competitive salary, equity, and full benefits. iOS Developer, Office Manager iOS Developer Atavist is seeking an iOS developer to maintain and evolve our own magazine app and the white-label reader apps of our clients. Our web-based software, Creatavist, enables the automated creation of iOS and Android apps for publishers of all types. The position requires a self-starter to oversee the development of those apps, as well as The Atavist app, which distributes our own original nonfiction and fiction by bestselling, award-winning writers. We’re looking for a fun-to-work-with, creative problem solver with an interest in data visualization, multimedia storytelling, and the future of reading. We’re a company full of creative people that do things a bit differently, and we live at the forefront of how authors and publishers are creating stories today, and how readers are consuming them. We’re obsessed with elegant design and responsiveness for our readers. Your job will be to help make sure we continue to translate that obsession into the iOS world. Required skills/technologies · Objective-C / Cocoa / iOS SDK / XCode · Javascript / jQuery · Experience with hybrid HTML5/native app development Also welcome · PHP Experience · 2+ years hands-on experience developing iOS mobile Apps Office Manager Atavist is looking for a highly organized, highly competent office manager for a part time job that could transition to full time in the future. We are a small, unique company, full of creative people, that combines technology and journalism. Our office environment, in our loft in DUMBO, Brooklyn, is very important to us. We’ve grown enough that we need just the right person to come in and help us manage it. You will definitely: · Serve as the go-to person for all office needs and being the most knowledgeable person about the office · Managing office equipment, kitchen, and general supplies · Manage utilities and communication with the building · Undertake setup, and arrange food and drink. for in-office lunches, happy hours, and events · Manage equipment purchases and keep track of all equipment in the office · Assist with recruiting: Posting job listings, sorting candidates, scheduling interviews · Help organize office social events You will possibly: · Take on other business management tasks such as running payroll and interfacing with our HR company · Help manage the process of bringing on new hires · Take on other writing, editing, and production tasks related to either our editorial division (The Atavist) or our software platform Required skills: · Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal. · Strong interpersonal skills: Upbeat, friendly and professional. · Excellent time management skills and extremely strong organizational skills. · A very high level of comfort with technology, particularly web-based services: the ability to manage online bill-pay, for instance. You don’t need to know how to fix the wireless router, but you should know how to get it fixed. · Willingness to learn new things even though you never done them before. · Desire to assist others and take on additional responsibilities Useful skills: · Previous office management experience · Interest in journalism, publishing, and/or technology · Other tech skills such as Photoshop, WordPress This is initially a part time job, 20 hours a week to start (working half days every day of the week). As we grow, there is a strong possibility that this could become full-time and involve other duties. Send us a resume and a cover letter describing the experience and perspective you would bring to the position, to jobs@atavist.com. Contact Us: Emailinfo@atavist.com Twitter:Follow @theatavist on Twitter Navigation To get in touch about a larger enterprise project, click here. To try our Creatavist software for free, click here. To learn about how to get your own branded app and more, click here. For general Atavist news and updates, subscribe to our list here. Mission Statement Atavist is a media and software company at the forefront of digital, mobile publishing. Our mission is to enable the next generation of multimedia storytelling, reaching readers across mobile devices and the Web. Whether it's in our own stories or those of others who use our Creatavist platform, we aim to push the edge of the digital reading experience. Who We Are Atavist is a group of writers, editors, and software developers dedicated to the art of storytelling. Based in Brooklyn, New York, we build easy-to-use, innovative software tools for digital publishing and create our flagship nonfiction publication, The Atavist, the pioneering longform publication lauded by The New York Times, The Wall Street Journal, and many more. PlatformFeatured Clients Creatavist Beta Terms of Service Privacy Policy Copyright © 2012 Atavist, Inc. All Rights Reserved. Creatavist Stories About Us Contact", is_draft: true, company_id: 78, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: "Atavist is seeking an iOS developer to maintain and evolve our own magazine app and the white-label reader apps of our clients. Our web-based software, Creatavist, enables the automated creation of iOS and Android apps for publishers of all types. The position requires a self-starter to oversee the development of those apps, as well as The Atavist app, which distributes our own original nonfiction and fiction by bestselling, award-winning writers.", key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://corp.sociocast.com/our-company/", title: "Web Developer", full_text: "Sociocast Sign Up Developers Pricing Our Company Blog Login Company Team Advisors News Careers Company Sociocast empowers enterprise developers and data scientists by providing simple, predictive analytics that are easy to plug into any application or product. Sociocast’s powerful, cost-effective solution enables companies to optimize existing products and services, and create new revenue opportunities. All while using their biggest asset — their data. Whether your company has data scientists in-house or requires a fully automated, turn-key solution, Sociocast can help amplify your company’s Big Data initiatives. GET IN TOUCH Albert AzoutChief Executive OfficerSociocast has invented a radically new approach to a very ubiquitous problem. Team twitter linkedin Albert Azout Chief Executive Officer Albert is a Co-Founder of NYC-based StyleCaster, the fastest growing women’s lifestyle platform on the web. He is also a co-founder of Sub Rosa, a top digital advertising firm in New York City. Prior to Sociocast, Albert worked at Lehman Brothers where he built his quantitative and engineering background. He graduated from Babson College with a B.A. in Business Administration and serves on the advisory board of various start-ups including Last Pictures, Qwiki, Contender.com, and CassaDecor. twitter linkedin Giri Iyengar Chief Technology Officer Giri was formerly the CTO of Signal Patterns, a startup that develops next-generation iPhone and social media applications focused on aggregating consumer behavior. Previously, he was a Computer Scientist at IBM TJ Watson Research Center where he worked on Medical Imaging and Multimedia Mining. Giri did his doctoral work at the MIT Media Laboratory and holds a B.E in Electrical Engineering from IIT Mumbai. twitter linkedin Suren Hiraman VP of Technology Before joining Sociocast, Suren served as Vice President of Technology at Proclivity Systems, a tech company focused on behavioral data mining, a Principal and Practice Manager at SunGard Consulting Services, and the Managing Principal of Global Integration Services for the Northeast U.S. Region at Salesforce.com. Suren holds a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from MIT. twitter linkedin Gna Phetsarath Director of Technology Mr. Phetsarath is a senior technologist with over 20 years experience and a strong focus on high frequency multi-asset trading platforms and high performance computing systems. With a background in financial services technology consulting, he has worked for SunGard Consulting Services, Finetix LLC, Fort Point Partners LLC, and American Management Systems. Mr. Phetsarath graduated from the University of Virginia with a BS in Computer Science, and dual minors in Environmental Engineering and MIS. Launched commercially in summer 2011; 13 employees 1 daily processed terabyte per employee linkedin F William High, PhD Data Scientist Will has a decade of experience crunching data at the top research institutions in his field, including Berkeley, Caltech, Harvard and the University of Chicago. He was previously a data science consultant at ThoughtWorks, and his specialties include Bayesian inference, Monte Carlo techniques and image processing. Will holds a PhD in Physics from Harvard and has coauthored over 30 publications, which have garnered more than 1000 total citations. Daniel Siegmann Software Engineer Daniel Siegmann joined Sociocast as a Software Developer. With seven years experience designing, implementing and testing software, Daniel will be working to support and improve all of Sociocast’s products. He received a master’s degree in computer science in 2005 from Binghamton University and spent his years before Sociocast developing software for modeling insurance products. linkedin Arnaud Lawson Systems Operations Engineer Arnaud received his M.S. in Information Management from the University of Maryland College Park. Prior to joining Sociocast as a Systems Operations Engineer, he worked as a Linux Systems Administrator at Pragmatics Inc., an IT solutions company that provides services and products to the federal government. He helped administer, maintain and expand the IT infrastructure supporting agile software development projects using various open source and proprietary tools. Arnaud also has a B.S. in Information Systems Management from the University of California Santa Cruz. Sagar Patil Java Software Engineer Sagar is a Software Developer with a strong background in Java/JEE. He previously worked with Cognizant Technology Solutions for 4 years before coming to states to obtain a M.S. in Information Systems from State University of New York at Buffalo. Before joining Sociocast he had been working at Vora Research Labs in Cincinnati. Ryan Brogden Business Development Ryan is a part of the business development team with a strong background in marketing. He previously worked with Crimson Hexagon’s marketing team before graduating from Northeastern University. He holds degrees in both marketing and music industry. See MoreSee less Advisors twitter Albert-László Barabási Physicist, Northeastern University Mr. Barabasi is the former Emil T. Hofmann professor at the University of Notre Dame and current Distinguished Professor and Director of Northeastern University’s Center for Network Science. In addition, Barabasi is an associate member of the Center of Cancer Systems Biology (CCSB) at the Dana Farber Cancer Institute, Harvard University as well as recipient of the FEBS Anniversary Prize for Systems Biology and the John von Neumann Medal by the John von Neumann Computer Society. linkedin Gokul Rajaram Product Director, Ads at Facebook Gokul Rajaram is Product Director, Ads at Facebook. He drives the product roadmap and execution for Facebook’s advertising products. Before Facebook, Gokul was Co-Founder and CEO of Chai Labs. Earlier in his career, Gokul was Product Management Director for Google AdSense. Gokul was also product lead for a number of acquisitions for Google, including DoubleClick, AdScape, and dMarc. Gokul has an MBA from MIT Sloan, a MS in CS from UT Austin, and a B. Tech in Computer Science from IIT Kanpur where he received the President’s Gold Medal for being Class Valedictorian. twitter linkedin Dan Ariely Behavioral Economist, Duke University Dr. Ariely is a James B. Duke Professor of business administration with a secondary appointment in economics and a faculty member of the Center for Cognitive Neuroscience at Duke University. As one of the top behavioral economist, Ariely authored “Predictably Irrational: The Hidden Forces That Shape Our Decisions” and co-authored “The Joy of Experimental Psychology.” In addition to his editorial achievements, Ariely has received countless awards and appointments including the Alfred P. Sloan Professor of Behavioral Economics. Robert Goldberg Venture Partner, Raptor Ventures Robert Goldberg is a seasoned entrepreneur, technology leader and investor with more than 30 years of experience building companies from early-stage startups to established enterprises. Most recently Robert was a member of the early executive team at Zynga serving as its first senior vice president of business operations and corporate development. During his career, Robert helped lead three companies to initial public offerings and has been involved in numerous successful exits. Robert holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Engineering and Applied Science from Columbia University in New York City. linkedin Joe Zawadzki CEO, MediaMath In 2007, Mr. Zawadzki founded MediaMath to create the new discipline of media trading. Zawadzki was more recently the founder, President and Chairman of Poindexter Systems / [x+1], a pure-play marketing optimization company. [x+1] was named one of Inc.’s “Top 500 Fastest Growing Companies” in 2006 prior to his departure to found MediaMath. Zawadzki graduated from Harvard University with an BA in English and was a Teaching Fellow in cosmology, set theory, and the history of science. twitter linkedin Jerry Neumann Founder of Root Market Jerry Neumann is an investor in and advisor to early stage companies. He is an active angel investor with investments in 33Across, BankSimple, Flurry, Magnetic, Metamarkets, PerformLine, PlaceIQ, Profitably, The Snowball Factory, The Trade Desk, XA.net, and Yieldbot. He is also an advisor to PubGears, among others. He has founded or co-founded several marketing technology companies, most recently Root Markets, the first exchange-style marketplace for leads. Jerry ran the venture capital division of Omnicom Group, the worlds leading marketing services company, where he was involved with the seed financing of many of the first wave of internet marketing firms, including Razorfish, agency.com and Organic. twitter linkedin Jeffrey Silverman Former Executive at DoubleClick (A Google Company) Jeffrey Silverman is partner at Laconia Ventures, a firm that advices and invests in early stage digital media companies such as Media Armor, Antego, Localytics, Public Stuff, GlobeTrotr, PayPerks, uKnow, Nerve, Little Pim and Citizen Global. Jeffrey is an advisor to C3 Metrics and on the Board of Directors of Sociocast. He was previously President and CEO of Integrated Color Solutions, a graphic arts digital workflow solution for 8 years. He held multiple senior level positions including President of DoubleClick’s Media Division for North America and VP of Global Sales. Jeffrey serves on the Board of Director of the Park Avenue Armory and the New York City-Southern New York Chapter of Multiple Sclerosis and as Chairman of Friends of the Lake. linkedin Joel Perlman President, Copal Partners Joel is President of Copal Partners, a leading outsourced research and analytics company with over 1.400 employees and 100 institutional clients. Joel has broad experience in emerging markets, having set up the firm’s research centers in India China, and Argentina. He advises a number of early stage companies. Joel was previously a consultant at McKinsey where he worked in the FIG and Media sectors in Latin America. He has an MSc Accounting and Finance from London School of Economics. twitter linkedin Tim Hanlon Advertising Executive Tim Hanlon is the Founder and CEO of The Vertere Group, a boutique consulting, advisory and investment firm focused on helping todays most forward-leaning brands, content producers, entrepreneurs, and investors benefit from rapidly changing technological advances in marketing, media and consumer communications. Hanlon was previously Founder and Managing Director of Velociter, the innovation-centric partnership and strategic investment arm of Interpublic Groups corporate media agency division Mediabrands where he was chiefly responsible for driving entrepreneurial innovation through proprietary relationships with emerging venture-backed media/marketing startup firms. Before Velociter, Hanlon was Executive Vice President/Managing Director of Publicis Groups VivaKi Ventures the strategic partnership and investment arm of VivaKi (comprising Starcom MediaVest Group, Zenith Optimedia Group, Digitas, Razorfish, and Denuo), which he founded in 2008, after launching predecessor Ventures practices for Denuo (2006) and Publicis Groupe Media/PGM (2005). In those roles, Hanlon served in formal advisory and directorial positions with over three dozen media-related startups, while managing successful exits with more than a half-dozen firms, including Sling Media (acquired by Echostar/Dish Network, 2007); Navic Networks (Microsoft, 2008); Rapt (Microsoft, 2008); SnapTell (Amazon/A9, 2009); Dapper (Yahoo, 2010); Pelago (Groupon, 2011); and Tumri (Collective Media, 2011) See Moresee less In the News September 11, 2013 Sociocast Goes Back to Beta and Widens Net for Business’s looking to Personalize Web Visits August 27, 2013 Sociocast 'Personalization Platform' Lets Business Owners Customize Web and Mobile Applications in Minutes August 20, 2013 Sociocast pivots from dev-focused analytics to a site optimization app anyone can use June 4, 2013 Sociocast: One of 8 SaaS apps that are changing the way we do business. May 6, 2013 Sociocast showcased in MapR's M7 NoSQL Database Release March 29, 2013 Sociocast Launches Prediction API for Self-Service Big Data Analysis March 28, 2013 Sociocast joins the Application Developers Alliance March 25, 2013 ProgrammableWeb mentions Sociocast's Prediction API in their API Spotlight feature. March 5, 2013 Zynga, Tumblr, Sociocast – Outgrowing the Cloud? February 19, 2013 'Big data' startup Sociocast conjures $1M, opens up 'Prediction API' to SMBs February 12, 2013 Graduating From the Cloud: Sociocast’s Move Reflects Emerging Trend February 7, 2013 Why the Cloud Doesn’t Solve All Problems, Featuring Sociocast. November 26, 2012 Sociocast Named in FOX Business News Black Friday Consumer Data Interview November 26, 2012 Sociocast One of PandoDaily’s “Fifteen NYC-based enterprise startups to keep an eye on” September 25, 2012 Sociocast is Featured in the Economist August 7, 2012 Facebook’s ad product guru to advise NY big data startup Sociocast April 26, 2012 Big data startup Sociocast goes beyond analytics with new SaaS tools. December 6, 2011 New Tools for New Computing Challenges. December 1, 2011 This Man Could Rule the World. Dr. Barabasi joined Sociocast advisory board in 2010 November 2, 2011 Sociocast Raises $1.5 Million For 'Big Data' Analytics Solutions October 28, 2011 Sociocast's Star Line Up Recognized By Adotas October 12, 2010 VentureWire FASTech Conference Spotlights Most Promising Start-Ups October 4, 2010 Sociocast Moves More Deeply Into Social Marketing Metrics September 29, 2010 Sociocast Raises $1.65 million for Real-Time Audience Data September 27, 2010 Sociocast Partners with BackType, OpenAmplify and RapLeaf to Enhance Audience Data for Publishers September 27, 2010 Sociocast Lands $1.65 Million for Real-Time Audience Data More NewsLess News Careers New York City Web Developer / New York City Sociocast is hiring a Web Developer to help grow an industry-leading Big Data company with world-class technology and development processes. You will work with an experienced tech team to build out cutting edge APIs and web-based products across multiple industries. This includes REST APIs, Javascript libraries, iOS libraries and critical client-facing web apps. You will be part of a fast-paced, closely-knit, supportive team delivering in an Agile environment. You will demonstrate the ability to collaborate with your fellow engineers while also working independently and with a high degree of self-driven responsibility. You will deliver value to the team while also continuing to build your experience in leading-edge development. Requirements: 3+ years of production/real-world software development experience Hands-on Javascript and CSS experience in web applications and client-side API libraries Hands-on server-side web development in frameworks like Ruby/Rails, PHP or Java/Spring Ability to pick up new technologies quickly, including new web frameworks Comfortable working in a DevOps agile environment side by side with other developers Self-motivated and comfortable working in a fast-paced environment A collection of tShirts with ironic slogans Additional Skills: Wizard-level abilities with Javascript/CSS a strong plus Experience developing Javascript libraries for REST APIs a strong plus Work with data-driven apps or analytics apps a strong plus iOS experience a plus Apply: Please submit your cover letter and resume to WorkWithUs@Sociocast.com with “Web Developer” in the subject of your email. read moreread less Systems Operations Engineer / New York City Sociocast is hiring a systems operations engineer to help build out an industry-leading Big Data company with world-class operational systems and processes. You will manage production operations processes, including internal CRON jobs, partner integration jobs and ad hoc manual processes. You will be responsible for troubleshooting problems and performing root cause analysis, as well as figuring out how we could be doing things better as a company. You will manage production operations processes, including internal CRON jobs, partner integration jobs and ad hoc manual processes. You will be responsible for troubleshooting problems and performing root cause analysis, as well as figuring out how we could be doing things better as a company. Requirements: 3+ years Operations support experience 1+ years startup experience Managing 24/7 production processes Scripting and maintaining mission-critical tools and infrastructure Familiarity with Java application environments Comfortable working in a DevOps agile environment side by side with developers Self-motivated and comfortable working in a fast-paced environment Additional Skills: Basic Sys Admin experience, including with CentOS Basic Network administration experience Experience with digital advertising or other low-latency, high-load environments Experience with Ruby scripting Experience with Hadoop systems Experience with PostgreSQL systems Apply: Please submit your cover letter and resume to WorkWithUs@Sociocast.com with “Systems Operations Engineer” in the subject of your email. read moreread less Java Engineer / New York City Sociocast is hiring a Java Engineer to help build out an industry-leading Big Data company with world-class technology and development processes. You will work hand in hand with an experienced technology team to build out cutting edge Big Data products across multiple industries. We will collaborate on architecting and building systems and software that are capable of processing hundreds of terabytes of data across real-time and non-realtime streams. You will work across a variety of systems, including highly concurrent, low latency API servers, Grails web applications and Hadoop map/reduce jobs. You will be part of a fast-paced, close