  {link: "http://yipit.com/jobs/", title: "Yipit Data Engineer", full_text: "Every deal in your city Sign Up Login Find Near About Yipit About Team Jobs Submit A Coupon Data Press FAQ Contact Us Follow @Yipit About Contact Us Work With Us Help Yipit Data Sitemap More Cities Terms Privacy © 2014 Yipit Jobs Jobs Yipit is the technology layer for sales and deals. Aggregating, structuring and personalizing this complex space is an extremely challenging problem, and weâ\u0080\u0099re just getting started. To do so weâ\u0080\u0099ve built one of the strongest teams in New York. 1 Yipit Data Engineer Yipit Data develops clever ways to learn about businesses through the data they expose online. We specialize in acquiring this difficult to obtain but extremely valuable information through modern, large-scale technology. We are profitable, VC backed, and our clients include the largest funds on Wall Street. If you're an engineer who thinks they can contribute across the entire business, weâ\u0080\u0099d love to hear from you. You might have significant experience on wall street, you might love data aggregation, or you could be a web technology expert. As we rapidly expand the number of companies and industries we're covering, we need people who can own entire products. At Yipit Data you'd be: Designing, prototyping, and iterating on new products - quickly. Building large, distributed applications on top of Amazon Web Services and Yipitâ\u0080\u0099s existing infrastructure layer. Improving a modern code base, with excellent test-coverage, strong infrastructure support, and continuous deployments. Working with clients to generate ideas and pitch existing ones. Part of a smart, driven, and fun team, committed to growing a new business. (Team, Vin's Blog, Yipit Tech Blog) We work primarily in python but believe in choosing the best tool for every job. We offer highly competitive salary, equity, and excellent benefits. Yipit promotes strong engineering and company cultures; candidates should be committed to being a part of a fast growing start-up. We are highly selective and believe this position will not fit all engineers, however, we can make decisions very quickly for the right people. If interested send your GitHub, LinkedIn or equivalent to jobs@yipitdata.com. 2 Data Product Analyst Are you in an analyst program but interested in technology and startups? Are you an engineer looking to transition towards product management?Yipit Data is a profitable, fast growing, data-driven tech startup in New York and weâ\u0080\u0099ve raised $7+ million from blue-chip VCs. Our current clients include multi-billion dollar hedge fundsJ and some of the worldâ\u0080\u0099s largest technology companies. Weâ\u0080\u0099re rapidly expanding the number of industries and companies weâ\u0080\u0099re covering and are offering a rare product role to help build out our business.Youâ\u0080\u0099ll gain valuable experience in: Analytics: Work with massive amounts of incredibly interesting data. Your comfort with manipulating large data sets and deriving meaningful insights from them, without losing sight of the details, will be critical. Customer and Product Development: Work with clients to refine current offerings and develop new product lines to fit their needs. Analyze market demand to determine optimal pricing for new products. PR: Develop relationships with reporters from leading publications – WSJ, Bloomberg, Reuters – as you publish data-driven industry reports. Sales: Sell into hedge fund and e-commerce clients by leveraging your expertise, intellect, and poise. Operations: Build out our business operations and financial processes as we scale to a world class operation. Yipit Data utilizes Yipitâ\u0080\u0099s proprietary data sets to provide research and analytics on e-commerce to investors. Our current clients include multi-billion dollar hedge funds and some of the worldâ\u0080\u0099s largest technology companies.The workload is highly varied and incredibly intense. Ideal candidates are likely in an analyst program at a leading consultancy, investment bank, or similar, and can demonstrate they are: Intellectually and professionally nimble: able to take on a variety of independent workstreams An extremely hard worker: ready to make the success of this startup the primary focus of your life Compensation includes equity, highly competitive salary and excellent benefits As you can see, the position will appeal to a narrow and exceptional set of individuals. We expect it to be very competitive, but we promise to look at every individual and make an interview decision quickly.Send your resume or LinkedIn to jobs+analyst@yipit.com. 3 Web Developer We're one of the leading Django shops in New York, and our code goes from development to production fast. We have high levels of test coverage, strong CI infrastructure, and automated deployments. Weâ\u0080\u0099re looking for extraordinary software engineers comfortable with web applications, databases and distributed systems. The number of years of experience is not important to us.Learn more about us here, and if interested send a link to your GitHub, LinkedIn or equivalent to jobs+developer@yipit.com, and we'll take a look shortly. Learn more about our Team and Technology or email jobs@yipit.com with any questions!", is_draft: true, company_id: 1033, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Data", description: "If you're an engineer who thinks they can contribute across the entire business, wed love to hear from you. You might have significant experience on wall street, you might love data aggregation, or you could be a web technology expert. As we rapidly expand the number of companies and industries we're covering, we need people who can own entire products.", key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://artsicle.hiretracking.com/artsicle/job/61", title: "Engineering Intern", full_text: "| job openings (view all) http://www.artiscle.com/ engineering intern artsicle is hiring summer interns! love art? ready to join one of the fastest growing startups in nyc? want to have some fun with your internship? if so, keep reading! artsicle interns will learn about startup life, tech, the art world, and what it means to build something. you'll be exposed to a ton of other great startups, mentors, investors. you'll visit artist's studios, stop by gallery openings, and help build something world changing. you can build new skills and develop a portfolio of real work. and we think you'll have fun, too. you'll have a very flexible schedule and can often work from anywhere (minimum of 20 hours/wk). and hey, if we all get along, we might just ask you to stick around fulltime. check out the description below and apply! here at artsicle, we believe in getting our hands dirty across the full stack, from the css to our ec2 servers. artsicle's cto is a self-taught developer - so don't worry about not having a cs degree. however, what comes with being self-taught is not to fearing the unknown and knowing how to jump in and learn just about anything. artsicle is looking for self motivated developers who don't cringe at the thought of stepping outside their comfort zone, or the idea of taking a customer support call. artsicle is a small team and it's very likely that you'll do everything from wire a piece of art to tweak our recommendation algorithm - it's a great way to become a jack of all trades. if you believe in learning new skills while excelling at your current ones, then artsicle is the place for you. our stack - mysql, redis, memcached, linux, ruby, rails, and front end stuffs (html, css, js/coffeescript) requirements: html & css - if you don't know html & css, start learning here. a strong understanding is quick and invaluable. http://learn.shayhowe.com/html-css programming language - we don't care what language but proficiency in one will help you learn another. keen eye for design - you care that that font is 24px, not 23px. strong writing & communication - clear writing skills and a confident opinion will help you communicate with the team. start-up attitude - we're passionate about what we do, and we want you to be too. get it done - you feel comfortable doing things, even when no one is telling you exactly what to do. great to have: interested in - going deep in javascript, the good parts of course. knowledge of coffeescript is even better. git - or subversion, mercurial etc. twitter bootstrap - it makes communication and responsiveness a lot easier. sass - a great superset of css a bit of photoshop knowledge always helps if you don't meet the above criteria yet, here are a few steps to help you get there: learn to program - a fantastic get started book. http://pragprog.com/book/ltp2/learn-to-program rails tutorial - not only do you build twitter but you learn some up to date techniques such as tdd. http://www.railstutorial.com build something (anything), push it to the world and tell us about it. share this position: share in twitter share in facebook apply required fields are marked as (*) first name (*) last name (*) email (*) resume location personal website what have you built? (programmed or otherwise) (*) what do you love about artsicle? (*) github (link) tell us about ways you've sought self improvement. (*) powered by hiretracking", is_draft: true, company_id: 72, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://www.biodigitalhuman.com/home/jobs.html#collapseOne", title: "Senior Web Developer", full_text: "sign up log in sign out email password remember me forgot password? or 3rd party login facebook google features pricing jobs we want to improve the way people understand their health. we have a diverse team of software engineers, 3d animators, graphic artists, and scientists - who all share a passion for technology and healthcare. we're determined to transform the way people communicate about their health, starting with how they learn about the human body. join our team if you'd like to work in a fast-paced, dynamic startup environment be a part of cutting-edge 3d technology in the health and wellness space meet smart, interesting, and creative people dedicated to improving healthcare and patient literacy share a workspace in the heart of soho, manhattan! job listings senior web developer biodigital, an established nyc-based digital health company, is seeking an extremely talented web application developer to help build its latest flagship product, a cutting-edge 3d web application (www.biodigitalhuman.com). the ideal candidate has intimate knowledge of the latest web technologies and a strong desire to build a high-quality, scalable web app that will revolutionize the health and medical sectors. the successful candidate thrives in a fast-paced start-up environment, but seeks to join a fun, proven company headquartered in the heart of soho. qualifications degree in computer science or software engineering, or equivalent experience at least 3 years’ programming experience experience with python, java, perl, javascript, html 5, css, mysql or similar technology passion for working at the intersection of technology and health, and desire to build a cutting-edge health visualization platform interest in the latest state-of-the-art programming technologies highly motivated, independent, and hungry to succeed strong communication skills knowledge of opengl, webgl, or other 3d programming experience a plus for an outstanding programmer, this is an opportunity to lead and learn at a company driving radical changes in healthcare. the hire will report directly to senior management. competitive compensation, excellent benefits. and the opportunity to get in early on a company whose potential has already been proven. submit resume to recruiter@biodigital.com. the company biodigital is a biomedical visualization company that is revolutionizing the way people understand their health and the human body. its latest product, the biodigital human, is a comprehensive 3d human body accessible through the web. the human platform allows users to learn about anatomy, disease, and treatments in a manner that resembles life itself. the platform has already received tremendous accolades, including #1 education app in the google chrome web store, winner of nvidia’s one to watch award at the 2012 emerging companies summit, featured presenter at tedmed 2012, and one of .net magazine’s 20 best 3d websites of 2011. the tight-knit team of engineers, 3d animators, scientists, and entrepreneurs are passionately working to solve real-world problems. contact us faq biodigital blog jobs terms of service privacy policy © 2013 biodigital, inc. humanely made in nyc. all rights reserved.", is_draft: true, company_id: 108, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://songza.com/page/careers/", title: "Android Development Lead", full_text: "Songza Search: Sign up Log in Music Concierge Popular Browse All Careers at Songza The only thing more awesome than listening to great music from Songza is being part of the team that makes Songza tick. We’re passionate about building products that are useful, simple, and delightful. Songza is a lifestyle enhancement service. Our goal is to make the things our users do every day better. Our free streaming music service has expert-made playlists for every occasion and makes it outrageously easy to find the right one, at the right time. Songza is one of the most exciting startups in NYC. We’ve been named among the Top 10 Most Innovative Companies in Music by Fast Company, an Editors’ Choice app by Apple, Google Play and PC Mag, as well as an ‘App Store Best of 2012’ by Apple. In July 2013, Mayor Michael Bloomberg presented us with a New York City Neighborhood Achievement Award . We’ve been covered by the New York Times, Wall Street Journal, CNN, TechCrunch, and Mashable. Most importantly, we delight millions of users like these: The Songza app is like your much cooler friend who always has the perfect song for every moment. @OliviaWilde Songza is making my workday so much better right now. @_DrunkBlonde @Songza officially makes mornings 1000x better.‏@allisonplove Songza makes running so much more enjoyable. @nixhaley So @alfredoflores just showed me @songza for workout playlists. Why didn't any of my 26 million best friends show me this? #whichplaylist. @JustinBieber Starting to think Songza is better than a boyfriend. It knows exactly how to make me happy. @perfectcompanyy Falling to sleep: Songza. Waking up: Songza. Working out: Songza. My life is forever changed. @JonUchacz Songza is in the Long Island City neighborhood of New York City. We’re one subway stop from Grand Central Station and you can practically spit into the East River from our office. Besides a breathtaking view of the Manhattan skyline, Long Island City has great food options and good neighborhood bars. Our office is a funky, open, industrial space, and will never be featured in the Herman Miller catalog. Over the last 7 years, our team have become expert and highly regarded players in a complex media landscape -- prior to Songza, we founded AmieStreet.com and sold the brand and customer base to Amazon in 2010. Songza’s fast growth, high app ratings and word-of-mouth buzz has us poised for a fun, successful 2013. We work hard. We play music all day. We high five when awesome things happen. We love what we do. Available Positions Android Development Lead iOS Engineer Infrastructure-ish Engineeer Editorial Internship Regional Sales Manager Yield Optimization Manager Account Manager Other Positions Editorial Internship Songza is looking for an enthusiastic and motivated intern to do music research and make amazing long-form playlists. You’ll also be brainstorming activities to soundtrack and updating existing playlists, all while listening to great music. A successful candidate will be a team player who is obsessed with music and interested in expert-level music curation. Seriously, music should be your favorite thing and you should know a lot about it. You should also be intensely curious about the artists, genres, eras, etc. that you know nothing about. This editorial position is ideal for a college student who wants to make playlists that will delight Songza's users and expose them to great music, and who wants to learn more about the fast-paced and quickly-evolving music industry in the context of a startup company. Applicants should be willing to commit at least 12-18 hours per week at our Long Island City office. We will work with you to create a weekly schedule that accommodates your school and work commitments. We are recruiting interns for spring and summer internships, that run from the end of January to mid-June, and from June to the end of August. Salary: A $1000 stipend given in two parts at the middle and end of your internship. Requirements: High school degree Advanced knowledge of recorded music (preferably across several genres) Strong Internet research skills, particularly with regard to music Ability to multitask and meet deadlines under pressure Be available a minimum of 2-3 days per week in the office, from 11 a.m.- 5 p.m. A great personality Bonus Points: Experience writing about music (please include writing samples in your application if you have them) Experience copy editing Enrolled in a 2-4 year accredited U.S. college or university and eligible to receive credit or have an academic letter of support for your internship Basic knowledge of the digital music space Please send your resume, cover letter, and writing samples to internships@songza.com. Infrastructure-ish Engineer Songza is seeking an experienced infrastructure-ish engineer to ride herd over our prodution systems and infrastructure. Wait. WTF is an infrastructure-ish engineer? It's a software engineer who will be a full member of our engineering team, doing a mix of software development and operations. While this position is similar to what is often called a site reliability engineer or a devops engineer, we have no organizational silos. We expect and encourage all members of the engineering team to contribute wherever their skills and interests take them. For this particular position, however, we're looking for somebody whose skills and interests center around keeping our servers going 7 x 24. We're looking for somebody who can not just manage existing systems, but also drive improvements in infrastructure and process. You need to have the skills to develop tools to handle new situations where existing tools are inadequate. Our production envinronment is AWS-based, using Ubuntu Linux. Your responsibilities will include managing, deploying, and monitoring all of our AWS assets. Typical projects will include: Improving our server management and deployment processes. The goal is being able to roll out a new server instance, correctly configured for its role, with a single command. Improving system monitoring. We need to know quickly when any piece of hardware of software has failed or is operating out of normal limits. This includes our own servers as well as external providers. Improving our software deployment process, so new versions can be deployed faster. Improving processes for data backup, operational redundancy, and disaster recovery. Desired areas of experience: Managing cloud-based Linux servers in a 7 x 24 production environment Managing AWS assets, including EC2, S3, EMR Python for system management System management tools such as puppet, chef, fabic, boto Monitoring tools, including nagios, graphite, statsd, cloudwatch Managing large MongoDB installations Log management tools such as rsyslog and elasticsearch To apply, send resume (Word, PDF, or URL) to tech-jobs@songza.com. Account Manager Songza’s Account Manager is a critical part of the Sales Team. He or she will work with the Sales Team to ensure seamless campaign execution while providing high-level client service support. The success of all digital advertising campaigns lies in the hands of the Account Manager. The ideal candidate will be a key contributor within the Sales team and Songza as a whole. Responsibilities: Create dynamic, creative proposals and media plans that meet advertisers’ objectives and showcase what Songza has to offer Ensure online advertising campaigns are implemented in an accurate and timely manner Monitor campaigns and ensure campaign delivery across various ad serving platforms Analyze and optimize advertising performance to meet client KPIs and maximize profit Provide advertisers and/or agencies with campaign reporting when necessary Develop and nurture quality business relationships with clients Qualifications: Bachelor’s degree 2+ years of experience in client-facing, media account management roles Existing knowledge of DFP, MoPub and LiveRail are preferred Excellent organizational, analytical and time management skills Professional and polished written and verbal communication skills Ability to multi-task and deliver results under pressure Strong competence with Mac operating system and Microsoft Office suite of applications Strong work ethic; desire to work in an entrepreneurial environment Active on social media Team player Loves Songza! Sounds like you? Email: gab@songza.com with the Subject: \"Account Manager\". Yield Optimization Manager Songza’s mission is to make the things our users do every day better. Our Yield Optimization Manager will contribute to the success of our indirect sales channel by managing demand partner relationships across mobile, desktop, and video platforms; driving revenue from daily optimizations; and on-boarding new demand partners and monetization products. Songza’s Yield Optimization Manager will: Monitor existing demand partner relationships across mobile, desktop, and video platforms for performance and efficiency Optimize demand stack on a daily basis Evaluate potential new partners and coordinate with ad ops and development teams to prioritize on-boarding projects Use marketplace insight from demand partners to identify opportunities for audience development, new products, and revenue growth Oversee inventory management, forecasting, and yield management across all programmatic platforms Five Things About You. You have up to four years of prior experience with video and/or display ad serving platforms (DFP, MoPub, or Liverail preferred), third party demand UI’s (Rubicon, OpenX, iAd, AdExchange, etc) or yield optimization products. You are familiar with testing and implementing ad tags for programmatic deals. You have strong analytical skills and the ability to analyze performance data to drive inventory recommendations and troubleshoot issues. You have a keen attention to detail and experience handling multiple ongoing projects. You are passionate about being part of a fast-growing, disruptive start-up that improves the lives of millions of people every month. To apply, send salary requirements and resume to gina@songza.com, with the subject, \"Yield Optimization Manager\" Regional Sales Managers (New York, Chicago, Toronto) Songza’s mission is to make the things our users do every day better. We believe advertising on Songza should accomplish the same thing. Our native advertising solutions integrate brands into users’ daily routines by answering the most important customer question: \"How can this brand improve my day?\" Songza is looking for a regional sales manager to help us refine and scale the next generation of intent-based marketing with a solution that is native to the Songza user experience. This seller will be part of our founding sales team and will be critical in growing our revenue through \"Industry First\" initiatives as well as digital, audio, video and other pre-roll executions. We are looking for an individual who is entrepreneurial in spirit and thrives on building a book of business from the ground up. Songza’s Regional Sales Manager will: Proactively prospect, qualify, grow, and maintain a regional territory account list and manage activity with our CRM tool. Prospect and develop key ad agency and company relationships at all levels in order to effectively build and maintain territory ad revenue. Create exciting sales presentations, incorporating industry research and campaign performance data, and great mock-ups. Execute and deliver high quality responses to all RFPs based on client objectives and goals. Negotiate pricing and contractual agreements. Drive tons of new business! Seven things about you National media sales experience in either digital, mobile, radio, print, or video is required. A proven book of business is a plus. A minimum of 6 years of advertising sales experience with proven track record of exceeding sales goals and the ability to develop and manage a consistent sales pipeline. Contacts and relationships with leading agencies and clients in your territory. The ability to work across multiple agency departments (digital, broadcast, strategy, planning, and buying) to uncover different budgets and decision makers/ influencers. Excellent communication and presentation skills with extensive knowledge of digital and mobile media advertising and the overall ecosystem. A creative and fun spirit who inspires others, especially brand champions. Ability to meet and exceed quarterly revenue goals. Interested? Contact Us: Pete Roper | proper@songza.com. iOS Engineer As an iOS engineer, you will be responsible for all phases of development and testing, and deployment of our iOS products. You will work closely with our backend team to interface with the Songza HTTP API, and our graphic design experts to build a beautiful and fun to use user experience. You love shipping code. You love music. You have worked on large scale software projects. Like all our engineers, you are language-agnostic, but you're also an Objective-C wizard. You believe in automated testing and code review. You need to be able to work in a fast-paced, cloud-based development environment. We ship frequent updates to our mobile products to implement new features, fix bugs, and keep the user experience fresh. We're not slaves to any particular methodology, but neither do we believe in cowboy coding. Our goal is to find just enough structure to keep things from turning into chaos without getting bogged down in meaningless process. We don't have any hard and fast checklist of requirements, but these are the sorts of things we're looking for: 2+ years Objective-C and iOS programming experience Experience building universal apps and implementing custom views Automated testing of applications A solid understanding of HTTP and RESTful webservices Experience with some form of version control (we use mercurial) A bachelors in computer science or equivalent experience Most important, you must love working in a high-speed environment, where everybody makes a difference. Code we write in the morning is often in production the same afternoon. Your ability to drive technical decisions is a function of how good your design and code are, not your job title or how well you dress. To apply, send resume (Word, PDF or URL) and cover letter to tech-jobs@songza.com. Android Development Lead Songza is looking for somebody who can take over all phases of development, testing, and deployment of our existing Android products, and drive all new development efforts. You will be responsible for recruiting and mentoring an additional Android engineer to fill out our mobile development team. You will work closely with our backend team to interface with the Songza HTTP API, and our graphic design experts to build a beautiful and fun to use user experience. You love shipping code. You love music. You have worked on large scale software projects. Like all our engineers, you are language-agnostic, but you're also a Java wizard. You believe in automated testing and code review. You need to be able to work in a fast-paced, cloud-based development environment. We ship frequent updates to our mobile products to implement new features, fix bugs, and keep the user experience fresh. We're not slaves to any particular methodology, but neither do we believe in cowboy coding. Our goal is to find just enough structure to keep things from turning into chaos without getting bogged down in meaningless process. We don't have any hard and fast checklist of requirements, but these are the sorts of things we're looking for: Thorough knowledge of using Eclipse IDE and Android SDK Experience leading a development team Experience building Android apps from scratch utilizing standard SDK techniques Experience creating custom UI elements Experience delivering streaming media on Android Have shipped a commercialy viable Android app A bachelors in computer science or other relevant experience 2+ years of Android development experience Experience with HTTP, JSON, and REST Web Services Most important, you must love working in a high-speed environment, on a small team where everybody makes a difference. Your ability to drive technical decisions is a function of how good your design and code are, not your job title or how well you dress. To apply, send resume (Word, PDF or URL) and cover letter to tech-jobs@songza.com. Don't See What You're Looking For? Just because we don't list your dream job, that doesn't mean we don't want to hear from you. We've got a number of positions (engineering and otherwise) in the pipeline that we're not actively recruiting for right now. If the perfect person came along, we'd jump at the chance to bring them on board earlier than planned. Just send us a resume and a cover letter explaining why your life (and our employee list) won't be complete until you're part of the Songza team. For engineering jobs, send to tech-jobs@songza.com. For all other postions, jobs@songza.com. If you send to the wrong address, we can usually figure out what you meant and get it to the right person, but we'll make fun of you. So don't do that. See Us On Campus Songza participates in several academic career fairs over the year. Our on-campus recruiting schedule has wrapped up for spring 2013, but we'll be back on college campuses in the Fall. We'll be posting specific schools as we finalize our plans this summer, but if you're interested in getting your career off to a great start with Songza, there's no need to wait for us to visit your campus. Just drop an email to tech-jobs@songza.com (for engineering postions) or jobs@songza.com (for other postions). We'd love to talk with you. Songza plays you the right music at the right time. Made by Music Experts. 100% Free. No Audio Ads. Get the free Songza app © Songza Media, Inc. Advertising Careers Copyright Privacy Policy Terms of Service Twitter Facebook Google+", is_draft: true, company_id: 775, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: "Songza is looking for somebody who can take over all phases of development, testing, and deployment of our existing Android products, and drive all new development efforts. You will be responsible for recruiting and mentoring an additional Android engineer to fill out our mobile development team.", key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://augmate.com/careers.html", title: "CTO", full_text: "Home Tour About News Careers Contact MENU Join us as we explore a new frontier h1 { color:#74838c;} We are looking for specific individuals that can help us to build a new and improved workplace environment. As a wearable first company, we are looking for futurists, with a passion for optimizing the way things are, the vision to see the way things should be, and the ability to build that future now. Augmate is building a development platform that will allow us to produce agile and scalable digital eyewear applications to improve the way deskless workers perform in the field. We are looking for entrepreneurial individuals that can help design this solution and capitalize on this tremendous opportunity we have in front of us. CTO At this early stage, you must have the expertise to architect and engineer our core platform. There is quite a bit of work ahead. You will be an intricate part of developing our wearable first engineering culture and the team that will lay the foundation for the future of the industry. You will assist in determining the optimal technologies that will allow us to scale with our customers and evolve rapidly as this technology advances. You should have experience with developing enterprise software in cloud-based environment, a strong understanding of how to best leverage third-party API’s, and experience developing a secure platform that facilitates performance utilizing real-time information in a workplace. Above all else, you must be a passionate coder that genuinely enjoys to build. We are looking for a leader. We would like this leader to effectively communicate our vision, not only to the members of our team, but to the partners and customers we are working with. You should be comfortable as a recognized thought leader in the space, as we pave the way for wearable technology to impact the workplace. If you have had experience working on software that has been implemented into a large industrial environment, well that’s a big plus in our book. Apply Apply ENTERPRISE SOFTWARE ENGINEER As part of the foundational team, your role is crucial. You will be developing Augmate’s ability to connect with outside enterprise databases (i.e. SAP) and engineer the infrastructure that will ultimately manage, deliver, and display data that will change the way workers interact with their environment. You must have experience working in large enterprise environments, engineering ERP systems, manipulating large amounts of data, working with third-party API’s, and optimizing solutions in a rapidly evolving cloud-based environment. You will be leading the design, development, and testing of features/functions delivered via platform components and/or services that are highly scalable, available and reliable. Apply Apply LEAD ANDROID DEVELOPER We are building software on the platform of the future. It just so happens, most of these digital eyewear platforms are running Android SDK. Our Lead Android Developer, as part of our foundational team, will be instrumental in developing industry leading digital eyewear applications for the deskless workplace. We are looking for someone who is passionate about building scalable and agile applications, with development experience in enterprise software API and cloudbase applications. You will be focused on user interface design and integration with revolutionary new hardware. You will be working to optimize our solutions to leverage sensors and gesture driven interfaces. Knowledge of computer vision would be a plus. Apply Apply WEARABLE ENGINEER In order to really maximize the capabilities of our software we have to optimize our the capabilities of hardware we’re working with. Incredible attention to sensors and their mechanics will improve the way we understand and are able to deal with the spatial requirements of deskless work environments. You will be crucial to our operations, working closely with the user experience team, as we work with our various hardware partners to provide actionable enhancements to both their capabilities and ours. As our main area of concern is with Augmented Reality, a keen understanding of OpenCV is desired. Experience with various embedded systems and hardware technologies like Bluetooth and Wifi are a plus. Ultimately, we are looking for someone who dreams about wearable technologies and desires to be at the forefront of their physical development. Apply Apply API DEVELOPER As API Developer. you’ll be building out crucial connections to various online services in order to lay the groundwork for a robust end-user experience. You’ll be partnering with internal teams to ensure that AUGMATE maintains the optimal API strategies, standards and best practices as well as collaborating with product owners to develop both private and public APIs. To that end you should be proficient in various protocols and data formats, including REST, JSON with expertise in security, including OAuth and SSL. Apply Apply DEVELOPMENT INTERN You’re a hacker -- a digital enthusiast with an entrepreneurial streak who is ready to join a small start up. You piece together existing technologies and are incredibly excited about the future of wearable technologies and augmented reality. As Development Intern, you’ll be on the ground floor of a fast growing startup developing the foundations of digital eyewear applications. Your experience with various coding platforms allow you to quickly piece together physical and application prototypes. We’re looking for someone with an insatiable desire to be even better. Apply Apply BUSINESS OPERATIONS & MARKETING INTERN In this highly diversified role, you'll assist in expanding the Augmate business in all directions. You will be working on the operations and marketing side of a leading software development startup, on a cutting edge technological platform, digital eyewear and wearables. We're looking for someone with some serious business, analytical, and social media savvy, a keen ability to understand the potential of this market and our brand, -and an interest in being at the intersection of hardware and software. Along with strong organization skills, a keen ability for strategy and aggressive implementation, you must have great communication skills and be able to build out our content strategy. You will be placed directly at the forefront of this new technological frontier and be directly involved with the growth of not only Augmate, but the industry as a whole. Apply Apply UI / UX DESIGN INTERN As a UI/UX Design Intern at Augmate, you will work closely with engineers and the business team throughout all stages of the product cycle. We are looking for a critical thinker with great design sense, a strong technical background, and an eye for making things better. This is an opportunity to create the standard for how the world will interact with digital eyewear technologies that display field-of-view information in the near future. As an ideal candidate, your skills in Adobe’s Creative Suite as well as HTML and CSS make you a great communicator, able to quickly prototype ideas. We’re looking for an out of the box thinker who understands 3D space and is not afraid to challenge the way things are and propose the way things should or can be. 3D Modeling experience in Sketchup, Rhino, 3DSMax, or Maya is a plus. Apply Apply Home Tour About News CareersBack to Top  1-885-AUGMATE Copyright © 2013 AUGMATE.COM All rights reserved.    ✉ INFO@AUGMATE.COM TERMS OF SERVICE | PRIVACY POLICY", is_draft: true, company_id: 83, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 10, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://www.unpakt.com/1/jobs-unpakt", title: "Senior Engineer - Web", full_text: "UnpaktLog inRegisterContactFor moversFAQAbout UnpaktHow it worksHow it worksAbout UnpaktFAQContactRegisterLog inFacebookTwitterGoogle+ Contact Us If you're interested in joining Unpakt, we would love to hear from you. Email: jobs@unpakt.com Phone: 855-2UNPAKT Careers About Us We are a small team led by a highly successful entrepreneur with over 20 years experience in the moving industry. We are creating a fun and energetic culture in a 4,000 sqft loft office just steps away from Union Square. We are creating an intense, fun and respectful culture. Our compensation package includes competitive salary, equity participation, and we will help with relocation expenses for the right hire. What we do Unpakt has created a marketplace for quality movers in New York City and is open for business, already booking moves. We are now expanding into markets like Boston, Chicago, Washington DC, Los Angeles, Miami, and Houston, before going international. We are gaining traction within the moving community and our customers have enjoyed the experience of using Unpakt. Booking moves over the phone is like walking down the street to visit your local travel agent, it doesnâ\u0080\u0099t happen anymore and we are leading the industry to a new behavior. Come join the fun! Senior Engineer - Web Customer Support Associate Marketing Director Senior Engineer - Web As one of our senior developers, you love working in an agile environment, want to solve a real-world problem with a large market potential, and know how to write maintainable code. Working as a full-stack software engineer you will work closely with our development team. You will quickly take the reigns and be driving the quality of our code base, mentoring other developers, and communicating effectively with the non-technical members of the team. Our compensation package includes competitive salary, and we will help with domestic relocation expenses. Requirements: 2+ years experience with Ruby on Rails, Javascript, and CSS 5+ years experience in production software environments Pragmatic software design Test Driven Development Additional Skills Desired Pair programming Experience with testing frameworks - Rspec, Cucumber, Jasmine Postgres MySQL, MongoDB jQuery, AngularJS Development operations experience with Unix/Linux environment Ability to coach less experienced developers Ability to communicate well with non-technical teammates Ping pong lover Scotch aficionado Customer Support Associate Weâ\u0080\u0099re looking for an energetic, outgoing, and team-oriented Customer Support Associate who can get things done. If you thrive in a fast-paced environment and find gratification in solving problems and assisting customers, Unpakt is the place for you! Job Description: You will be managing inbound customer inquiries, interact using our live chat, and correspond via e-mail and by phone Must be flexible for weekend coverage Moving experience is a plus but not a necessity Responsibilities: Provide superior customer service while responding to general and product related inquiries via live chat, e-mail, and phone Understand the customerâ\u0080\u0099s needs and work proactively to find a solution in a timely manner Light to moderate data entry Perform other duties as required and assigned Requirements: Bachelorâ\u0080\u0099s Degree Must have at least 3+ years experience in a similar role Proficient with Microsoft Office, Mac, and CRMs Additional Skills Desired: Must be articulate, courteous, patient, and professional at all time with a sense of timeliness and completion Have excellent verbal and written communication skills in English Professional phone demeanor Have strong attention to detail Have a track record of working tirelessly to find solutions to problems Tech savvy, or a working knowledge of online and mobile technology Work well independently and well with a team Ability to organize and manage several projects at once Must submit a cover letter with resume Marketing Director Unpakt is seeking a full-time Marketing Director to work closely with all departments to execute Unpaktâ\u0080\u0099s strategic marketing plan, partnerships, affiliate, social media, and PR. We are looking for a creative, execution-oriented Marketing Director who can put Unpakt on the map. You will own the marketing domain for our startup, whether online or offline efforts. Your focus will be to expand and deepen penetration to main cities around the country. Your range of work might cover a lot of ground, and you will often need to be scrappy and self-sufficient, but we also have the financial resources to bring in external resources or scale up investment as justified. You will have a lot of freedom to experiment to see what works, but will also need to be diligent about investing time and money in the ideas delivering the best results. Job Description: Design and organize creative offline and online marketing campaigns Be comfortable both executing work directly and managing vendors to help produce campaigns Assess, cultivate, and implement strategic partnerships Execute the strategies, plans and development of the Affiliate Program Run and optimize AdWords campaigns Manage content generation and distribution Work with PR agency on all public relations activities to generate greater brand awareness for Unpakt Lead our social media presence and related content strategy Own all aspects of Vendor Marketing (marketing to our movers partners/merchants) Requirements: Bachelorâ\u0080\u0099s Degree or greater 3+ years marketing experience Hands-on experience with SEO and SEM best practices Experience with Google Analytics Ability to interact effectively with various constituents at a company including C-level leaders Demonstrate ability to manage relationships and partnerships with individuals, organizations, and communities Startup experience a plus Excellent communication and writing skills Highly-motivated and entrepreneurial BlogFor moversPressCareersDeals©Unpakt LLC 20131-855-2UNPAKTPrivacy policyTermsMade with ♥ in NYCUnpakt is a SupplierMember of the AmericanMoving & Storage AssociationWhat we doHow it worksFor moversBlogCompanyAbout Unpakt/1/about-unpaktCareersPressDealsNeed help?FAQContacthttps://www.unpakt.com/contactConnectFacebookTwitterGoogle+YouTube©Unpakt LLC 20131-855-2UNPAKTPrivacy policyTermsMade with ♥ in NYCUnpakt is a Supplier Member of theAmerican Moving & Storage Associationpowered by", is_draft: true, company_id: 957, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: "As one of our senior developers, you love working in an agile environment, want to solve a real-world problem with a large market potential, and know how to write maintainable code. ", key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/mms-technical-account-manager", title: "MMS Technical Account Manager", full_text: "You will proactively help customers of the MMS Backup Service to ensure their success. You should be excited about the core mission of MongoDB, and the opportunity to help our customers. You are both a technical and a business resource, deeply engaging with customers and understanding how they use MongoDB and MMS, and helping to plan the implementation of MMS within their environment.Responsibilities On-board new customers, working with them directly to implement MMS Backup for their solution Keep in contact with customers to make sure they are satisfied with the service and that it is working for them Reach out to customers when we detect problems or issues, working them to implement solutions Answer customer inquiries about billing Stay aware of overall support queue, pitching in as needed to help the technical support team Analyze and study the incoming customer support requests to determine what potential changes or improvements to the product that would lower the incidence of problems Keep abreast of the product, documentation and operations, so that you are a deep resource to engineers, technical support and sales Requirements Familiarity with system administration and networking to help technical users install software on Linux and Windows Experience working with clients and advocating for their success Capability to write small programs to fix problems A CS/CE Degree or equivalent experience Interested in learning new things Knowledgeable about a wide range of web and internet technologies Outstanding communication skills, both verbally and in writing Familiarity with Amazon Web Services and other cloud infrastructure platforms Excited to join a meritocracy where great work gets noticed", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, sub_dept: "Technical Services", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/lead-kernel-tools-engineer", title: "Lead Kernel Tools Engineer", full_text: "The Kernel Tools team is responsible for developing the tools that enable MongoDB users to interact with the server. The Lead Engineer will be in charge of designing and developing new tools as well as adding features to existing tools. The Lead Engineer will report to the VP of Engineering and will grow a team of 3-5 engineers. A strong foundation in application development methodologies and testing is required to deliver this suite of highly performant and reliable multi-platform tools designed to work in the most demanding environments.Responsibilities Lead the team responsible for building tools which enable MongoDB users to interact with the server Develop new tools and new features on existing tools Test all current and future tools/features for high performance and reliability across multiple platforms Build out a team capable of producing in a fast-pace environment Requirements 4+ years of software engineering or related experience Proven leadership and strong problem-solving skills Experience using RDBMS or NoSQL databases C/C++ programming skills Expertise in databases and operating systems Good understanding of software development processes Excellent verbal and written communication skills A track record of delivering complex software projects Experience with Go programming language a plus Experience with MongoDB a plus Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 4, sub_dept: "Dev Ops", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/newrecent-grad-software-engineer", title: "New/Recent Grad - Software Engineer", full_text: "You are eligible to apply to this position if you are currently in your final year of a Bachelor’s or Master’s program in Computer Science or are within one year of having obtained your degree. MongoDB, Inc is seeking Computer Science students located in the United States with a strong background in CS theory and systems, to join us in building the next revolution in database technology at our Silicon Valley and NYC locations.Eligibility for our diverse Software Engineering Roles By applying for our New/Recent Grad Software Engineer position you will be considered for various roles across MongoDB’s Engineering teams. During your first six months as an employee you will participate in our rotational program to determine where your personality, passion, and skill set fit best. Engineering teams include MongoDB Management Services (MMS) - working on our cloud services/our hosted monitoring service Developer Experience (Drivers) - working on the drivers for each of our official languages, integration with third party tools and frameworks, sample MongoDB-based applications, documentation, tutorials, and outreach with developer communities Core Server (Kernel) - contributing to the MongoDB database working in C++ Internal Tools & Kernel Tools Team – writing developer facing tools to make every engineer (and we have alot) as productive as possible Dev Ops - working with our internal infrastructure and deployments Documentation Team - Building the reference materials for all of MongoDB's products including MongoDB, MMS, and the drivers Performance/QA - Ensuring that MongoDB is the fastest and most stable database available Field Services Team - Shadowing Consulting Engineer/Solutions Architect (pre and post Sales Engineer) Requirements In the process of receiving or having received a BS or MS in Computer Science A solid foundation in computer science theory, with strong competencies in data structures, algorithms, and software design Extensive programming experience You are fluent in C++ and/or proficient with, Python, Java, JavaScript, Ruby or other comparable high level programming languages You have a strong systems background There is a good chance you’ve probably been a TA or Head TA for a CS course You’ve had one or more internships with prestigious software companies You are familiar with MongoDB and have probably used it to build an application or project You’ve probably been a participant in several hackathons Candidate must be located in the United States Benefits Competitive Salary Health benefits include: Medical, Dental, Vision, with FSA accounts Stock options 401(k) Commuter benefits Unlimited vacation/sick days Perks Fully stocked kitchens, and weekly catered lunches Equipment of your choosing In office Yoga and Bootcamp Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.axial.net/about/careers/", title: "Python Engineer", full_text: "Axial Network Search Events Leaderboards Pricing Case Studies Case Studies Testimonials Transactions Resources M&A Blog Entrepreneur Blog Library About Team Careers Sign In Careers Axial is building a platform that will transform how private companies connect with capital. The Axial network is an online marketplace connecting people, information and capital. Our vision is to enable every private company to successfully finance or sell their company. Our team is small still and we are recruiting exceptional people into every role. No matter what the position, we look for three things: You have a history of doing things exceptionally well, academically, athletically or professionally You are focused, driven, intelligent, and have a bias for action You are happy, friendly and a natural communicator; you add energy to the room Account Management Account ManagerAs an Account Manager at Axial, you’ll be fanatical about solving for and delivering what Axial Members need to succeed. You’ll lead the post-sale efforts in building relationships with your Members. You’ll become a domain expert in business development across the entrepreneurial economy for people who invest in, acquire, or advise private companies in this day and age.Read MoreAccount Manager Why Member Success? As an Account Manager at Axial, you’ll be fanatical about solving for and delivering what Axial Members need to succeed. You’ll lead the post-sale efforts in building relationships with your Members. You’ll become a domain expert in business development across the entrepreneurial economy for people who invest in, acquire, or advise private companies in this day and age. You will become an expert on the Axial product so you can intelligently teach and advise Members on the best ways to engage with the Axial network. At Axial, we are extremely passionate about the success of our Members for two main reasons: 1. We’re committed to excellence. Axial delivers the most critical online business development tools to the buyers, investors, advisors and CEOs in the private markets. We’re committed to delivering the best possible consulting and thought leadership to our Members. 2. We believe in our mission. Creating long-term relationships with our Members is absolutely crucial to our success. We must delight them in order to sustain them and grow. How will you do it? You will become a business development consultant to every Member you serve You will become an expert on private equity, entrepreneurship, and investment banking You will onboard and educate new Members on their Axial Membership You will teach Members best practices and provide expert insight You will build long-term relationships with Members to ensure they remain with Axial You will save at-risk Members through intense value-driving negotiations You will serve as a liaison between customers and our Product & Engineering teams You will be the face of Axial at our regular in-person meetings and events with Members You will contribute to the strategic direction of the company, as well as to the evolution of the product You will be measured by your abilities to a) influence your Members to engage with Axial and b) retain long-term Memberships with existing Members What We’re Seeking Highly passionate and engaging individuals with the ability to connect authentically with others Intellectually curious thinkers with a need to constantly uncover information and solve problems Exceptionally impressive communicators, written and verbal True hospitable nature and a passion for making people happy, challenged, and delighted Energy and capacity to handle constant change and make quick decisions Tenacity and grit. You hate to lose, you love to win, and your work ethic is through the roof. Ability to speak up, rattle the cage, question the status quo to push the team forward Highly collaborative people who win when their team wins Bachelors Degree or higher One to three years work experience, preferably in a customer-facing role Apply Administrative Executive Assistant to CEOWe are seeking a seasoned, trusted, and competent Executive/Personal Assistant to serve the professional and personal needs of our CEO. We are a fast-growth technology company headquartered in the Flatiron. Our environment is casual, friendly, and transparent, but we demand excellence and maintain extremely high standards. Read MoreExecutive Assistant to CEO We are seeking a seasoned, trusted, and competent Executive/Personal Assistant to serve the professional and personal needs of our CEO. We are a fast-growth technology company headquartered in the Flatiron. Our environment is casual, friendly, and transparent, but we demand excellence and maintain extremely high standards. The CEO needs the following: Someone who can help him manage all facets of his life; the role will be roughly 70% EA and 30% PA Someone who wants to work in a fast growing company environment while also handling personal and family items, errands, and commitments around town and at his home Someone who has extraordinary detail orientation You must be able to take on a heavy professional and personal calendar, billing, travel and vacation logistics, financial wires for investments, and managing personal vendors You must develop a direct relationship and rapport with his family to be successful Someone who is always responsive, has a sense of urgency, gets it done right reliably Extremely discreet. You will be entrusted with considerable amounts of private information. No slip-ups, no poor judgment Energetic, cheerful, consistently positive attitude Ideally, this person would work for the CEO for the very long-term Requirements: You are a career executive assistant; this is your profession, you excel in it, you love the role of being the trusted gatekeeper, coordinator and partner to the CEO 10+ years as an EA / PA working in demanding fast-paced and rapidly changing environments Experience with complex calendar management Experience interacting discreetly, professionally and wisely with executives, vendors, family members, etc Experience with putting together small dinners / events, etc Experience getting around Manhattan Must be responsive; you’re not on call 24/7, but you’ve got to be available and responsive Apply Engineering Python EngineerAs a Python Engineer at Axial, you will build data-service backends using the Flask and Django web-application frameworks. You will work on the same team as Product Managers, Designers and Front-End Engineers who specify, design and build products and widgets that consume your data-services.Read MorePython Engineer As a Python Engineer at Axial, you will build data-service backends using the Flask and Django web-application frameworks. You will work on the same team as Product Managers, Designers and Front-End Engineers who specify, design and build products and widgets that consume your data-services. Axial’s mission is to enable every private company to access the capital needed to finance or exit their business. Your software will connect entrepreneurs, investors, brokers and business advisors, driving the largest network of private investors in the world. The Problems You’ll SolveAs an engineer at Axial, you will solve difficult technical problems so our Members don’t have to. Some of our biggest technical challenges right now are: Search. Search connects entrepreneurs, and their advisors with capital and services. By constantly improving search, we help our Members: – secure the capital needed to finance or sell their business – connect and build relationships – constantly improve relevancy Shared Authorization Framework. We serve both small businesses and large companies. If you’ve ever wanted to build a licensing management system that manages user, group and feature access required to support the disparate needs of smallest and largest companies in the world, we’re your destination. Go SOA. We believe our data is our business, and we believe that decoupled data-services give us the maximum flexibility and utility in accessing our data. The Axial Corps of EngineersWe are a team of 8 engineers dedicated to achieving excellence in every aspect and level of our system, from our automated build system to our increasingly modular front-ends. In pursuit of excellence, we focus on one thing at a time, one area at a time, one day at a time. Our slogan is “Factum non Verbum”, “Actions not Words”: We ship improvements to our product every day Simplicity and flexibility are our guide We change our minds when we’re proven wrong You’re an ideal candidate if you … communicate and collaborate well are a seasoned python expert have designed and implemented distributed HTTP data services have extensive SQL experience have worked with git are experienced working with and managing a *NIX system love flat, repeatable data structures The benefits of being an Axialite … competitive salary competitive equity we buy you all the books you need conveniently located Flatiron office (near 4/5/6/N/R/Q/L/F) Apply Front-End EngineerAxial’s engineers develop technology to drive the transformation and democratization of modern capital markets. In addition to leveraging and building search technology to transform an entire industry, our engineers use their skills to advance our data, social and other technology-driven product strategies and initiatives.Read MoreFront-End Engineer The Area: Software Engineering Axial’s engineers develop technology to drive the transformation and democratization of modern capital markets. In addition to leveraging and building search technology to transform an entire industry, our engineers use their skills to advance our data, social and other technology-driven product strategies and initiatives. The Role As a Front-End Engineer at Axial, you’re responsible for developing and refining the client-facing HTML, Javascript and CSS portions of our platform. We’re a tight-knit team here so collaboration is a must. You’ll be building technology hands-on with a small product and design team, and be responsible for prototyping and creating responsive and elegant UIs to drive site engagement and manageability. You’ll also be working to help us improve our service aggregators, applications templating, and client-side libraries, and to extend and improve the power and scale of the Axial platform. You will be challenged to deconstruct designs into fine-grained, distributed modules capable of reuse in any portion of our platform. You’ll be challenged to engineer great, sustainable technology at high speed, but that’s okay ‘cause you’re a champ. We look for technologists who: - Are expert at working with JavaScript, HTML, and CSS- Are intimately familiar with browser quirks- Love creating well-crafted interfaces and elegant web UI’s- Communicate and collaborate well Bonus points for: - Bootstrap, jQuery, or Django- Experience developing in *NIX environments- Experience with a non-JavaScript programming language (python, php, ruby, perl, sh) The benefits of being an Axialite … we are building something very important the team you’re joining is pretty darn good and getting better with every new hire we pay people what they’re worth, not what we can get away with stocked and ever-expanding technical library onsite stocked fridge and bottomless coffee bike-friendly good location w/ roof in the Flatiron Apply Marketing Marketing ManagerAxial is looking for a driven inbound marketer interested in helping build a rapidly growing business. You’d be a great fit at Axial if you act like an entrepreneur (scrappy, smart, efficient, self-directed) and want to contribute to the success of an organization serving the Entrepreneurial Economy. You know that marketing is critical to growing a business and care deeply about inbound marketing.Read MoreMarketing Manager Axial is looking for a driven inbound marketer interested in helping build a rapidly growing business. You’d be a great fit at Axial if you act like an entrepreneur (scrappy, smart, efficient, self-directed) and want to contribute to the success of an organization serving the Entrepreneurial Economy. You know that marketing is critical to growing a business and care deeply about inbound marketing. You love Panda and Penguin because they just made the kind of marketing that you love to do that much stronger. You know the behavioral differences between LinkedIn Ads and Adwords. And you care deeply about what data can tell us about our marketing (and what it can’t). You know more than anything that you want to work for a great company where you can take ownership of projects and see them all the way through to completion. You want a place where you do everything in marketing – from creating all your own campaigns (meaty reports, lighthearted snackable content, and everything in between), sending emails, setting up specific landing pages, reaching out to the press and people on Twitter and on and on. About Marketing at Axial We have a belief that good marketers don’t just understand one part of the job. We’re all full stack inbound marketers running our own campaigns from start to finish, accountable for production, distribution, measurement and results. We work with designers or drop into InDesign ourselves to finish up big content pieces, build out landing pages in WordPress, set up ad campaigns, manage lead nurturing processes in Eloqua and run analytics on our own campaigns. Owning the whole process makes us much better at what we do – and helps us all build the skills we need to be successful versatile marketers over the long run. What You’ll Do: – Writing, writing, writing: blog articles, in-depth reports, and downloadable content and offers – Constantly experiment with new content types, topics, formats, and ideas – Build and optimize landing pages – Develop high-performing ad campaigns – Write emails and build nurturing campaigns – Interview successful entrepreneurs and investors in entrepreneurs – Analyze and report on your campaign performance How Success within Marketing and within Axial is Measured – The extent to which you elevate the quality of your teammates – Your contribution to a work environment organized around sustainable high performance – Inbound leads generated – Organic traffic finding your content & campaigns – Number of downloads of your content & campaigns – Organic blog subscriber growth and social media follower growth Musts: – 5+ years of relevant marketing experience – A love for writing and publishing and a card-carrying believer in inbound marketing – Exceptional written communications, with previous writing experience, blogging or journalism – A consistent sense of urgency and curiosity in all of your work – A demonstrable desire to market to and serve the entrepreneurial economy – Ability to link all activities to key ROI metrics and other business objectives Does this sound like you? If so, please attach a resume and a writing sample or two. Apply Marketing EngineerAxial is looking for a software developer to support the work of the broader marketing team by building and maintaining the technical infrastructure to help grow a world class marketing organization. Over the past five years we have built the largest network for the entrepreneurial economy and we want to add a person to handle the development and ongoing maintenance of the Axial website, technical integration with our CRM platforms, and marketing analytics.Read MoreMarketing Engineer Axial is looking for a software developer to support the work of the broader marketing team by building and maintaining the technical infrastructure to help grow a world class marketing organization. Over the past five years we have built the largest network for the entrepreneurial economy and we want to add a person to handle the development and ongoing maintenance of the Axial website, technical integration with our CRM platforms, and marketing analytics. The Role: You are a top-notch developer with a keen interest in helping facilitate the growth of the largest network available for entrepreneurs to grow, finance or sell their business. You will utilize machine learning to dynamically personalize our website to maximize engagement and conversions. You will take sole ownership of building major customizations and add-ons to our public facing site, including integrations with third party API’s. You will drive direct business growth using your technical skills. The Problems You Will Solve: You will have the opportunity to wear lots of hats and contribute on a number of levels including: Developing internal marketing reporting and analytics tools using cutting edge programming languages such as Python Building tools and plug-ins that can contribute to the open source community Translating complex data sets into insightful and meaningful visualizations Managing API integrations between website, analytics software, and internal systems Creating rich interactive experiences for our Axial WordPress CMS through custom PHP and MySQL development Apply Product Development Product ManagerAt Axial, the Product Development Team leads the way in product innovation. We are the driving force responsible for conceptualizing, shaping, and launching new products. At the core of our work is an authentic commitment to doing whatever maximizes success for our user base. At Axial, we call our users “Members”. We strive to learn everything we can about them -- their needs, their behaviors, their lives. This informs every decision we make and every product we ship.Read MoreProduct Manager Product Development @ AxialAt Axial, the Product Development Team leads the way in product innovation. We are the driving force responsible for conceptualizing, shaping, and launching new products. At the core of our work is an authentic commitment to doing whatever maximizes success for our user base. At Axial, we call our users “Members”. We strive to learn everything we can about them — their needs, their behaviors, their lives. This informs every decision we make and every product we ship. The Product Manager Role Product Managers at Axial lead the ideation process, define the product, and work with Engineering to launch new products and features. Product Managers are part of a multi-disciplinary team of product development, design, QA, and UX professionals who collaborate closely with each other to build products that touch millions of people. Product Managers at Axial are data-driven, critical thinkers with a strong understanding of technical application development, the right design sense, and an exceptional ability to interpret user behavior and intent. Responsibilities:- Drive all stages of the product development life cycle.- Deeply understand the market opportunity and identify the needs of our “Members,” to create new and improve existing Axial products- Effectively strategize, organize, and communicate new ideas and concepts to the organization at large- Create requirements for new products and features, and work with rest of the Product Development and Engineering teams to manage the end-to-end implementation Qualifications:- BA/BS degree, preferably in Computer Science or related field- 4+ years of relevant work experience in an outstanding product organization- Experience building products with agile product development principles- Ability to lead productive brainstorming sessions and create thoughtful product plans- Great teammate, great attitude. Arrogance, snarkiness, or immaturity isn’t tolerated- Drive and urgency to build great products- You are an exceptional communicator in all contexts: written, spoken, internal, external Preferred Qualifications:- Direct experience launching notable products in early stage or high-growth environments- Understanding of web-based data and analytic models- Prototyping capabilities Apply Sales Account Executive - Private CompaniesThe Private Companies (PC) sales team at Axial is responsible for recruiting and introducing owners and operators of private companies to intermediary Members on the Axial network. PC Account Executives are highly effective communicators who are able to correspond with senior level executives across various industries and enterprise sizes.Read MoreAccount Executive – Private Companies What is a Private Companies (“PC”) Account Executive?The Private Companies (PC) sales team at Axial is responsible for recruiting and introducing owners and operators of private companies to intermediary Members on the Axial network. PC Account Executives are highly effective communicators who are able to correspond with senior level executives across various industries and enterprise sizes. PC Account Executives are resourceful sales professionals who employ a consultative approach to helping CEOs, business owners, and entrepreneurs achieve their long-term growth, financing, or exit objectives through the use of our tools and products. We are passionate about helping private companies achieve the best outcome possible for their businesses. The Role: As a PC Account Executive, your day will be composed of three primary activities. First is outbound prospecting to engage owners and operators of private companies. Second is onboarding these private companies and connecting them with investment bankers, M&A advisors, and other Members of the Axial Network. Third is ongoing education, training, and relationship management to ensure private companies continue to engage with Members. You will achieve success by generating high levels of new conversations, effectively training private companies to engage with Members, and demonstrating how these companies can reach their longer-term goals more successfully with the help of our Members. Our team is highly driven and values collaboration and transparency. Minimum Qualifications: Track record of over-achieving goals in prior positions History of setting goals and achieving them, in the classroom, playing field, or in business Prior participation in a winning team environment 0-2 years of trained sales experience OR financial services experience Exceptional verbal and written communication skills Bachelors Degree or higher Personal Qualifications: You are committed to your success and will do what it takes to achieve your goals You are comfortable with interfacing with senior-level executives Enjoy winning the trust of those around you and developing relationships Highly personable and able to connect with prospects on a human level You love to win, more than you hate to lose You have a committed work ethic to personal and team goals Learn more about the Axial Member Development team by reviewing our culture deck, titled The Axial Way. Click here Apply Sales AssociateThe Member Origination Associate (MOA) team at Axial is responsible for outbound prospecting and recruiting new prospective Members into conversations with Sales Executives. MOAs are are highly effective communicators and able to gain access to senior-level executives and distinguish between their unique business needs across a wide various of industries (private equity, venture capital, investment banking, commercial lending, business brokers, family offices, etc.).Read MoreSales Associate Our Sales Associates are Member Origination Associates (“MOA”): The Member Origination Associate (MOA) team at Axial is responsible for outbound prospecting and recruiting new prospective Members into conversations with Sales Executives. MOAs are are highly effective communicators and able to gain access to senior-level executives and distinguish between their unique business needs across a wide various of industries (private equity, venture capital, investment banking, commercial lending, business brokers, family offices, etc.). MOAs specialize in high quality communication over phone, voicemail, and email. They are creative and find ways to help unique people solve unique problems. The Role: As a MOA, your day will be composed of three primary activities. First is responding to inbound inquiries and pre-qualifying new Prospective Members. Second is outbound prospecting to engage new Prospective Members. Third is providing Prospective Members with a smooth and value-added transition to the Sales Executives. You will achieve success by generating high levels of new conversations, discovering core value propositions for different types of firms, and demonstrating how these firms can reach their goals faster by engaging other deal professionals via the Axial Network. Our team is highly metrics driven and values collaboration and transparency. Minimum Qualifications: Track record of over-achieving goals in prior positions History of setting goals and achieving them, in the classroom, playing field, or in business 1-3 years of trained sales experience OR financial services experience Exceptional verbal and writing skills Prior participation in a winning team environment Bachelors Degree or higher Personal Characteristics: Hospitable and solution-oriented in nature You write down your goals and measure them regularly You love to win, more than you hate to lose You are willing to commit to mastering sales for the next 2-3 years You have high expectations of yourself and those around you You enjoy being part of a team and doing whatever it takes to help that team succeed Learn more about the Axial Member Development team by reviewing our culture deck, titled The Axial Way. Click here Apply Sales Operations Associate Axial is a fast-growing technology company built around an exceptional group of talented account executives and account managers. We are investing in the growth of our sales operations and strategy function to help us go-to-market more effectively, enable our team to be more productive, and to help continue Axial’s rapid growth and acceleration.Read MoreSales Operations Associate What Will The Associate of Sales Operations Do At Axial? The Associate of Sales Operations at Axial will be responsible for supporting the Sales Operations Manager and helping build the sales operations and strategy function at Axial. There are two core operations responsibilities relating to the Sales Operations function. The primary responsibility centers around Salesforce productivity and Salesforce enablement. This is a wide-ranging responsibility and includes everything from appropriate inbound lead assignment (developed in conjunction with the marketing organization) to assisting in territory development to the identification of necessary resources to accelerate talk time for the sales team. Finally, the last responsibility relates to the reduction of organizational churn through the development of dashboards, systems, and analytics to help the Member Success organization in account management and account support. The Sales Operations Team The Sales Operations team at Axial is led by the Manager of Sales Operations but will include the Associate of Sales Operations as a critical direct report, responsible for helping build and develop the function. The Sales Operations team will also include a set of temporary and offshore resources, primarily responsible for data management and data integrity. As the team grows the Sales Ops Associate will have an opportunity to oversee these functions. At first, the Sales Operations Associate will be asked to roll up their sleeves and dive into the work itself – becoming an expert on Salesforce reporting, analytics, workflows, uploads, and lead assignment sequences to enable the acceleration of the Sales Operations function at Axial. Specific Objectives 1. Maintain and manage the size of the Axial database sufficient to support near-term go-to-market strategy 2. Materially increase revenue and productivity per sales person 3. Decrease sales person ramp time to on-target productivity 4. Decrease churn and Accounts at Risk through the development of dashboards, analytics supporting the Member Success organization 5. Increase Operational Efficiency (Billing, Fulfillment, Collections) Responsibilities:● Build Salesforce workflows and protocols to allow for efficient lead and territory allocation ● Work with a team of offshore and onsite resources to grow the Axial database, clean qualified accounts, and oversee all data integrity ● Track, report and discover valuable new sales operations metrics to determine business health and trends ● Work cross-functionally to maintain and improve Salesforce dashboards for all teams ● Develop new workflows and protocols to drive sales productivity and sales team enablement ● Conduct ongoing data analysis of user base to enable “Members for Life”: Programs to identify Members at risk before renewal date Programs to identify win-win opportunities to increase Member Success & ACV Establish strong working relationships with finance, Member Development, Marketing, Member Success, & Engineering teams to achieve above objectives without constant management involvement Requirements: ● 0-2 years experience, previous roles as a consultant, business analyst, or finance analyst OR voracious appetite to learn and develop those skills ● Ability to master Salesforce.com: objects, data quality, custom workflows, reporting, and dashboard tools ● Exceptional problem solving and analytical skills, including experience with complex data structures and models ● Aptitude for Excel, for all forms of analysis and data modelling ● SQL knowledge (or other querying languages) and experience with data warehousing technologies a plus ● Ability to demonstrate thought leadership, present rigorous analysis and insights with clarity and confidence ● Can-do attitude willing to lead by example, do whatever it takes to succeed, and shift altitudes between high-level strategic planning and low-level tactical database administration and support Apply Sales Operations ManagerThe Manager of Sales Operations at Axial will be responsible for the senior leadership of the Sales Operations function. The overall goal of the Manager of Sales Operations is to work closely with the Head of Sales & Member Development to build and develop a first-class sales organization and to contribute both strategic and tactical insights to enable that development. Read MoreSales Operations Manager What Will The Manager of Sales Operations Do At Axial?The Manager of Sales Operations at Axial will be responsible for the senior leadership of the Sales Operations function. The overall goal of the Manager of Sales Operations is to work closely with the Head of Sales & Member Development to build and develop a first-class sales organization and to contribute both strategic and tactical insights to enable that development. There are three core strategic responsibilities relating to the Sales Operations function. The first is go-to-market strategy. This includes developing an overall go-to-market plan for new customer segments, helping map and size the market for potential new Axial Members, and growing the size of the near-term addressable market through database management and oversight. The second primary responsibility centers around Salesforce productivity and Salesforce enablement. This is a wide-ranging responsibility and includes everything from appropriate inbound lead assignment (developed in conjunction with the marketing organization) to territory development to quota and compensation plan development to the identification of necessary resources to accelerate talk time for the sales team. Finally, the last responsibility relates to the reduction of organizational churn through the development of dashboards, systems, and analytics to help the Member Success organization in account management and account support. The Sales Operations Team The Sales Operations team at Axial will be led by the Manager of Sales Operations but will also include additional teammates and direct reports as well as a set of ancillary support resources. The Manager of Sales Operations will oversee one immediate direct report, a Sales Operations Associate, as well as a group of paid interns and offshore resources focused on database management and data integrity. The Manager of Sales Ops will also manage a dedicated Salesforce Developer who will be responsible for custom development of our Salesforce instance to further support our sales and Member Development team. Specific Objectives Maintain and manage the size of the Axial database sufficient to support near-term go-to-market strategy Materially increase revenue and productivity per sales person Decrease sales person ramp time to on-target productivity Decrease churn and Accounts at Risk through the development of dashboards, analytics supporting the Member Success organization Increase Operational Efficiency (Billing, Fulfillment, Collections) Help management improve decision-making regarding pricing and go-to-market issues Responsibilities Manage a team of offshore and onsite resources to grow the Axial database, clean qualified accounts, and oversee all data integrity Oversee Salesforce workflows and protocols to allow for efficient lead and territory allocation Develop new workflows and protocols to drive sales productivity and sales team enablement Track, report and discover valuable new sales operations metrics to determine business health and trends Conduct ongoing data analysis of user base to enable “Members for Life”: Programs to identify Members at risk before renewal date Programs to identify win-win opportunities to increase Member Success & ACV Work cross-functionally to maintain and improve Salesforce dashboards for all teams Go-to-market territory analysis and coverage, re-alignment Analyze and contribute to sales compensation models / designs Deliver executive level updates in key leadership meetings (Quarterly Business Reviews, etc.) Gain management confidence such that the insights you produce are utilized in executive and board level presentations Establish strong working relationships with finance, Member Development, Marketing, Member Success, & Engineering teams to achieve above objectives without constant management involvement Requirements: 5-7+ years industry experience with previous experience as a consultant, business analyst, or finance analyst Mastery of Salesforce.com: objects, data quality, custom workflows, reporting, and dashboard tools Exceptional problem solving and analytical skills, including experience with complex data structures and models Expert in Excel, for all forms of analysis and data modelling SQL knowledge (or other querying languages) and experience with data warehousing technologies a plus Ability to demonstrate thought leadership, present rigorous analysis and insights with clarity and confidence Ability and/or interest and aptitude in growing and leading teams Can-do attitude willing to lead by example, do whatever it takes to succeed, and shift altitudes between high-level strategic planning and low-level tactical database administration and support Apply Sales Executive - PCM TeamThe Private Capital Markets (PCM) sales team at Axial is responsible for identifying and recruiting new capital providers onto the Axial Network. Sales Executives are highly effective communicators and able to correspond with senior level executives at various types of investment firms (private equity, family offices, debt funds, VC funds, independent sponsors, senior lenders, commercial banks, etc.).Read MoreSales Executive – PCM Team What is a Private Capital Markets (“PCM”) Sales Executive? The Private Capital Markets sales team at Axial is responsible for identifying and recruiting new capital providers onto the Axial Network. Sales Executives are highly effective communicators and able to correspond with senior level executives at various types of investment firms (private equity, family offices, debt funds, VC funds, independent sponsors, senior lenders, 