o the Axial Network. AB Account Executives are highly effective communicators, possess strong interpersonal skills, and are able to build long-term relationships with a variety of different Member types.Read MoreAccount Executive – Advisors & Brokers What is an Advisors & Brokers (“AB”) Account Executive?The Advisors & Brokers (AB) sales team at Axial is responsible for recruiting new business broker and advisory Members to the Axial Network. AB Account Executives are highly effective communicators, possess strong interpersonal skills, and are able to build long-term relationships with a variety of different Member types. AB Account Executives are adaptable and quick on their feet, and use their creativity and salesmanship to drive adoption of new features and tools among our Members. The Role: As an AB Account Executive, you will prospect, qualify, build, and nurture Member relationships with a focus on advisory and business broker Members of Axial who are primarily selling or raising capital for companies. Your day will be composed of three primary activities. First is prospecting and qualifying business brokers and M&A advisors who are not currently Members of Axial. Second is to provide ongoing training and education to Members to drive adoption of our products and tools and building long-lasting relationships that drive both our Members’ and our company’s success. Third is to serve as liaisons between our Members and the product development team, delivering feedback and insights that shape the evolution of our product. You will achieve success by generating high levels of conversations with Members, driving high levels of Member engagement with the product and with each other, and helping Members solve their problems using the suite of tools and solutions we’ve built. Our team is highly metrics driven and values collaboration and transparency. Qualifications: – History of setting goals and achieving them, in the classroom, playing field, or in business – Exceptional verbal and writing skills – Prior participation in a winning team environment – Bachelor’s degree or higher – 0-2 years of work experience Personal Characteristics: – You love to win, more than you hate to lose – Calm and confidence in cold sales calls and difficult customer interactions – You are a problem solver – You have high expectations of yourself and those around you – You enjoy being a part of a team and doing whatever it takes to help that team succeed Learn more about the Axial Member Development team by reviewing our culture deck, titled The Axial Way. Click here Apply Sales Executive - IBA TeamThe Investment Banking & Advisory (IBA) sales team at Axial is responsible for identifying and recruiting new investment bankers and M&A advisors (accountants, attorneys, consultants, etc) onto the Axial Network. Sales Executives are highly effective communicators and able to correspond with senior level executives at various types of large, medium, and small firms.Read MoreSales Executive – IBA Team What is an Investment Banking (“IBA”) Sales Executive? The Investment Banking & Advisory (IBA) sales team at Axial is responsible for identifying and recruiting new investment bankers and M&A advisors (accountants, attorneys, consultants, etc) onto the Axial Network. Sales Executives are highly effective communicators and able to correspond with senior level executives at various types of large, medium, and small firms. While most of our outbound efforts are via phone, we also spend a fair amount of time at conferences, events, and the home offices of prospective Members. We are passionate about finding unique solutions to help intermediaries bridge the relationship gap between their clients and qualified investors. The Role: As a Sales Executive, your day will be composed of three primary activities. First is prospecting and engaging in new conversations with firms that do not yet participate in the Axial Network. Second is managing an active sales pipeline of 