  {link: "http://www.adaptly.com/job_listings/22", title: "Director of Technical Operations", full_text: "Request A DemoLog In Contact Us Home Solutions Technology Work with Us Case Studies About Us Team Timeline Investors Press Careers Blog Back to Careers Director of Technical Operations We are looking for Director of Technical Operations to create and lead our technical operations team. You’ll be responsible for working with our technology and product teams to ensure that our products and services are highly available, performant and scalable as our business continues to grow. You’re a hands-on leader who’s been following DevOps principles and practices since before they started calling them that. Roles & Responsibilities Staff and lead a team of (in-house and outsourced) IT and operations professionals. Ownership, care and feeding of all productions systems (hosted in the cloud). Automate and maintain production deployment of applications and underlying supporting code. Build and maintain systems to monitor key system performance metrics. Collaborate with development to ensure that our applications and infrastructure are scalable and maintainable. Manage outside vendor relationships and overall IT spend. Ensure that security patches and processes are implemented and maintained. Own and participate in oncall pager rotations. Develop business continuity plan. Requirements Hands-on leader who can bring operational focus to our technology organization. 10 years of experience in technical operations leadership. Deep experience with cloud hosting providers such as AWS and/or Heroku. Expert in Linux, experience with Postgres, Redis, MongoDB, Hadoop and Hive. Experience with automation tools such as Capistrano and Chef. Experience supporting applications written in Ruby. MS or BS in Computer Science or related field. Employee Spotlight SEAN SHILLO VP of Engineering \"At Adaptly, trying to disrupt social advertising and redefine established concepts is what we breathe. I