  {link: "http://bark.co/jobs/senior-ruby-engineer/", title: "Senior Ruby Engineer", full_text: ".job-post { margin: 70px; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 150%; } .job-post h2 { margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 175%; /*font-family: \"burbSmall\", Arial, Helvetica, Geneva, sans-serif;*/ } .job-post p { margin-top: 15px; } .job-post h3 { margin-top: 15px; } .job-post ul { list-style: disc; margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 5px; } .job-post a:link { color:#4bb3e0; } .job-post .photo-right { float: right; border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 15px; margin-left: 20px; padding-bottom: 5px; } .job-post .photo-right .caption { margin:0; text-align: center; font-style: italic; font-size: 90%; } Bark & Co. About Jobs News Senior Ruby Engineer Woof! Arf! Yip! ArrroOOooOoo! Do you love sniffing around the back end? Do you find it difficult to write code because of your clumsy paws? Does the question, “who’s a good engineer?” give you anxiety attacks? Then you’re barking up the right tree! Bark & Co. is a fast-growing business for people who love (*ruv) dogs and is dedicated to building products that foster the health and happiness of dogs everywhere. Are you an amazing engineer? Then you should probably work at Bark & Co, here’s why: “OK glass, find bacon.” Dogs: You love dogs, dogs love you. We have plenty of pups in the office. Growth: We are growing super fast and we need incredibly smart folk to build incredible dog apps. Impact: Every dev has a huge impact on how we work and how we build things. Fancy Tech: Love machine learning? Love to work on highly scalable systems? Want to create an app for Google Glass? This is your place. Exciting Problems: Have the urge to mathematically calculate the optimal treat for a 5lb Chihuahua? (Hint: It’s probably poop) We have lots of data to comb through. Brand Spankin’ New Office: Complete with pods to work in, beer fridge, and dog beds. Benefits: Competitive salary and equity, 401k and health insurance. Benefits Your Pup: Unlimited dog treats, belly rubs, BarkBox, and PetPlan health insurance. Interested? Send us a note at tech@bark.co with links to your work and a photo of your pup (if applicable). The quantity of your experience is not nearly as important as the quality of it. Code examples and shipped products speak volumes to us. This position is full-time salaried position (with equity) and on-site at our amazing new office in Chinatown, New York. We offer health insurance for both you and your pup, 401k, wonderful team lunches, and a warm dog to pet anytime you wish. Sign up for our awesome Barkbox email newsletter. We get a kick out of hearing from people who contact us. Give our FAQ a quick read, or, if you love legal copy take a look at our privacy policy and terms of service", is_draft: true, company_id: 92, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
