  {link: "http://www.adaptly.com/job_listings/26", title: "Director of Software Engineering", full_text: "Request A DemoLog In Contact Us Home Solutions Technology Work with Us Case Studies About Us Team Timeline Investors Press Careers Blog Back to Careers Director of Software Engineering We are looking for Director of Software Engineering to lead our Software Engineering team based in NYC. As a hands-on leader, you’re comfortable getting your hands dirty and writing your share of code as well as managing the team. Additionally, you’ll help establish standards and best practices for development of all of our products and technologies. You’re a believer in Agile methodologies, contribute to the open source community, and are constantly learning and working to improve your craft. ROLES & RESPONSIBILITIES Day-to-day leadership, mentoring and growth of our core team of software engineers. Work in partnership with our Product, Test and TechOps teams to ensure that our products and services are world class. Identify and implement appropriate design, development and testing methodologies, best practices, coding standards, documentation and tools. In conjunction with the CTO, own and manage software development roadmaps in alignment with product, engineering and business priorities. Act as a senior architect for the team; assist in coding, testing, debugging, and documenting of applications. REQUIREMENTS Demonstrated experience leading the development of consumer grade, high-volume/high-availability software applications. Expert in software design methodologies and experience with multiple programming languages such as Ruby, Java, Clojure, Python, Go, etc. Strong experience with agile software development values and practices, such as Scrum. Prior experience with test-driven development and continuous integration. Strong SQL and RDBMS data modeling skills, as well as experience with various NoSQL technologies such as document databases or key value stores. Experience with Ruby/Rails, PostgresSQL, Hadoop/Hive, Redshift, Cassandra, Redis, Storm preferred. Experience with cloud hosting providers such as AWS and/or Heroku. 5+ years management experience in a software engineering organization of 10+ engineers 10+ years of software development experience. MS or BS in Computer Science or related field. Employee Spotlight SEAN SHILLO VP of Engineering \"At Adaptly, trying to disrupt social advertising and redefine established concepts is what we breathe. I wake up every day excited to tackle difficult challenges with brilliant people and have fun doing it.\" To apply Submit your resume here to apply. Technology Work with Us Case Studies Team Timeline Investors Press Careers Blog Twitter PMD Facebook PMD Center Adaptly NYC 22 W. 19th St. Third Floor New York, NY 10011 Adaptly Los Angeles 736 Lincoln Blvd. Suite #2 Venice, CA 90291 Adaptly Chicago 222 W. Merchandise Mart Plaza #1212 Chicago, IL 60654 Adaptly International 2nd Floor 68/69 St Martins Lane London, WC2N 4JS Connect with us! facebook linkedin twitter github Made in New York © Adaptly Inc. All Rights Reserved. Adaptly is a registered trademark. All other marks are property of their respective owners. Privacy × Request a Demo × Thank you! Someone from our sales team will be in touch with you shortly.", is_draft: true, company_id: 25, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 5, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/kernel-program-manager", title: "Kernel Program Manager", full_text: "MongoDB is seeking a Program Manager for the Core Server team. The candidate must be a highly technical and organized individual with a passion for facilitating large scale engineering endeavours. The Program Manager role will help manage the Server team’s interaction with a large and vocal user base and other teams within MongoDB. The Server Program Manager should be hyper-organized, but able to see the project big picture in order to help plan both long term and prioritize smaller feature requests. Responsibilities Work closely with CTO and VP of Engineering to help prioritize backlog and plan release roadmap Recognize patterns in a sea of information and effectively categorize and create links between related issues and projects Clearly and succinctly describe issues submitted by the community and double-check them after they're closed by engineering Have a clear understanding of the organizational structure in order to escalate and filter information to appropriate person or team Work with Field, Support and Sales teams to align outside feature requests with existing engineering priorities Requirements Able to see the big picture and help plan and prioritize across individual projects Hyper-organized when it comes to \"Jira Hygiene\" Strong interest in thorny technical issues central to databases: distributed systems, consensus algorithms, data replication, query optimization, data storage, OS internals, concurrency and scheduling, networking, etc. Attuned sense of priority and urgency MongoDB expertise is not a requirement, but interest in working with the database is 2+ years working in an Engineering role e.g., Programmer, Project Manager, Technical Writer, Support Engineer Nice-to-haves Have a passion for contributing to open source Ability to independently expand knowledge of new domains Last, but not least, desire to take an active role in innovation MongoDB expertise is a plus", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/java-application-engineer", title: "Java Application Engineer", full_text: "MongoDB is looking for a server-side Java engineer to join us in building the best database monitoring system on the planet. We have recently launched MMS, a freely available, cloud-based monitoring and alerting system for MongoDB. MMS is already being used to monitor thousands of MongoDB nodes and processes billions of metrics per day. There is tons to do to make it even better and to scale the system as we rapidly add new customers.Responsibilities Design, implement, and test core MMS features in a small team environment Assist ops team to troubleshoot operational issues with MMS itself Assist support team in using MMS to troubleshoot customer issues with MongoDB Requirements Expert Java engineer with 2+ years experience building web applications, front to back Experience with multi-threaded applications and concurrency Some experience of scripting (e.g. Python) a plus Familiarity with JSP/JavaScript a plus Familiarity with MongoDB a big plus Nice to haves You want to be part of a great team working at the forefront of database technology innovation You're flexible. You'll be joining a small team, so you're willing to take on a wide variety of responsibilities You are well organized, used to keeping many balls in the air at the same time You realize that comprehensive testing is your responsibility as a developer Apply now in New York, NY About MongoDB MongoDB (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading NoSQL database. Designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable.", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/perl-driver-engineer", title: "Perl Driver Engineer", full_text: "You will be the voice of Perl, on both the MongoDB internal team and within the broader MongoDB community. You will be responsible for supporting MongoDB in the Perl ecosystem through driver development, integration with open source tools, community support, and developer.Responsibilities Develop and support the Perl driver for MongoDB Create and contribute to open source applications and libraries Advocate the adoption of MongoDB to the broader Perl developer community Evangelize our developer products in person and online by presenting at conferences, blogging, writing technical tutorials, and other similar activities Requirements Strong experience programming in and a passion for Perl Experience writing Perl C extensions using XS or perlguts Active participant and contributor to open source Considerable success as a software developer, architect, or consultant working with web or data processing technologies Nice to Haves Experience with MongoDB and the Perl driver a big plus Experience publishing to CPAN a big plus Experience with the Moose object system Some experience with other dynamic typed programming languages like Ruby or Python Experience blogging and writing technical articles on Perl Apply now in New York, NY Apply now in Palo Alto, CA", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://www.smartrecruiters.com/AppboyInc/74187393--backend-amp-dashboard-software-developer-", title: "BACKEND AND DASHBOARD SOFTWARE DEVELOPER", full_text: "Backend and Dashboard Software Developer New York, NY Company Description Appboy is a rapidly growing analytics and marketing automation platform for mobile apps. Job Description Appboy is looking for a broad scope software developer to help build our SDK backend and developer web dashboard. We're tackling a variety of cutting-edge problems, from efficiently delivering real-time analytics for millions of transactions to designing blazing fast, ultra-responsive web applications. We use a diverse technology stack rooted in Rails, Coffeescript and MongoDB, but we're always open to incorporating new technologies. Candidates should have previous experience with software and product design and be able to intelligently discuss design decisions. Qualifications Recommended QualificationsDegree in computer science or equivalent experienceExperience with functional languages and MVC frameworks such as Ruby on Rails or Python/DjangoUnderstanding of algorithms, data structures, and designExcellent communication skillsBonusExperience handling rapid user growthExperience with Rails, HTML5, MongoDB, JS/Coffeescript, and modern web technologiesExperience with mobile developmentPrevious work at startupsProduct or UI/UX design Posted by Blake Walsh share this job The free social recruiting platform Learn more", is_draft: true, company_id: 56, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.1stdibs.com/about/jobs/java-software-engineer", title: "Java Software Engineer", full_text: "The Most Beautiful Things On Earth® Search Search Profile Categories Browse Furniture Shop By Category New Listings in Furniture All Furniture Seating Lighting Case Pieces Tables Mirrors Decorative Art Folk Art Asian Art and Furniture Rugs and Carpets Serving / Ceramics / Silver / Glass Wall Decorations Building / Garden Elements More Furniture and Collectibles More Ways To Browse 1stdibs@NYDC Maison Gerard: Line Vautrin Boxes Taschen Limited Art Editions Antiques Antiques Associations Members 20th Century Specialists Contemporary Design and Editions Saturday Sale Other Shop by Creator Fine Art Shop By Category New Listings in Fine Art All Fine Art Paintings Photography Sculptures Drawings and Watercolor Paintings Prints and Multiples Mixed Media More Art More Ways to Browse Taschen Presents Sebastiao Salgado's Genesis Taschen Limited Art Editions Amy Arbus Warhol I'll Be Your Mirror Exhibition Schedule Art Books Art Dealers Association of America Association of International Photography Art Dealers Art Offered by Furniture Dealers Other Shop by Artist Jewelry & Watches Shop By Category New Listings in Jewelry & Watches All Jewelry & Watches Rings Earrings Necklaces Bracelets Cufflinks Brooches Silver, Flatware and Silverplate Objets d'Art and Vertu Watches More Jewelry and Watches More Ways To Browse Bella Italia Modern Times Fine Watches Antique and Fine Jewelry Rare Jewels Engagement Rings Contemporary Jewelry Antique and Modern Silver Russian Works of Art Other Shop by Creator Fashion Shop by Category New Listings in Fashion All Fashion Clothing Accessories Books Fashion Jewelry Ephemera More Ways To Browse Haute Couture Vintage Clothing and Accessories Contemporary Clothing and Accessories Capsule Collections Versace SuperModa Punk Vintage Band Tees Fortuny Textiles Other Shop by Designer Estates Shop By Category Featured Properties Beach Houses Country Homes Great Old Houses Notable Architects High Rise Residences Collections Antique Collections Rococo Neoclassical Biedermeier Americana and Folk Art English Country House Modern Collections Art Nouveau Art Deco Italian Design Mid-Century American Scandinavian Modern Studio Design 20th Century Specialists Postmodern Design Contemporary Design and Editions Themed Collections Country Club Wild Kingdom Grand Scale Cabinet of Curiosities Color Blocking The Library Creators Shop By Category Furniture Creators Artists Jewelry & Watch Creators Fashion Designers Other More Ways to Browse Collections Creators 1stdibs ABOUT US Who We Are Our Story The Team Press Careers Contact Us Privacy Policy CAREERS AT 1STDIBS Back to Careers APPLY Java Software Engineer 10/22/2013 Build a beautiful career at 1stdibs JOIN our story1stdibs is the world’s leading online marketplace for rare and beautiful goods. We bring together the most prestigious international dealers of antiques, fine art, estate jewelry, vintage couture, rare furniture, design and luxury homes to offer a uniquely curated shopping experience to the discerning consumer. MEET our peopleLeading the industry for over a decade, 1stdibs' work environment combines the energy of a young start-up with the stability of an established name. Our executive team comprises leaders from Google, eBay, Barnes & Noble.com, Gilt Groupe and MLB Advanced Media, and we're backed by Benchmark Capital, the venture capital firm that supported eBay, Twitter and other successful start-ups. GROW your careerAt 1stdibs, we want you to feel welcome; welcome to think big, welcome to grow your career and welcome to share your unique knowledge and experience with us. Our open loft office in the Flatiron District is conducive to inspiration, collaboration and creativity, and we don't succumb to egos. We always want to hear a bright idea! LIVE your lifeAt 1stdibs, we believe a healthy, happy employee is more creative and productive. With that in mind, we offer many perks to help you maintain that important work-life balance, such as complimentary yoga and the chance to enjoy socializing with your coworkers during our weekly catered lunches. Read on and learn about more of the beautiful reasons to work at 1stdibs. This is an amazing opportunity to rebuild a high volume online marketplace. We are planning on a complete architecture overhaul. Databases will be redesigned, hardware will be revamped, web stack replaced, caching layers implemented. You will have the opportunity to build something exciting and new with the guarantee that your work will be seen by a strong and rapidly growing, global online community of dealers and consumers including antique dealers, interior designers and collectors. Some of what you’ll do… Contribute to a small team designing and developing a services platform Leverage caching, messaging and asynchronous processing Contribute to the design of a new database schema Implement an end-to-end ecommerce solutions Analyze and assess business requirements, choose the right tools and libraries to implement solutions Work closely with a fantastic Product organization to envision and create solutions that delight our existing customer and attract many new ones About you… Love the util.concurrent package Ability to bring your intellectual curiosity and thoughtful opinions with you everyday. Be awesome and make those around you awesome! Experience developing consumer-facing websites in professional production environment a plus Experience Developing code for high-traffic web sites Able to troubleshoot and explain performance bottlenecks Know that mule and tomcat aren’t just animal names An appreciation for one-of-a-kind items such as furniture, art and jewelry always welcome Your participation in the larger Developer Community is strongly supported and encouraged! APPLY All Positions Marketplace Support Specialist Interaction Designer Photographer - Atlanta Visual Web Designer Accounting Operations Manager Director, Analytics Graphic Designer Web Analyst (Part-Time) Front-End Engineer (JavaScript, HTML, CSS) Mobile Architect Extras Summer Fridays Weekly White Linen Lunches Snacks Full Benefits & 401k Paid Family Leave Commuter Benefits In-Office Yoga SHARE: FOLLOW US: twitter facebook pinterest About Us Support Center Contact Us Careers Press Privacy Site Map Dealer Login", is_draft: true, company_id: 6, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://betaworks.com/job/dots-vp-of-engineering/", title: "Dots – Head of Engineering", full_text: "betaworks - a company of builders Purpose Products People Community < Back to Studio Positions Dots – Head of Engineering Apply Now We’re adding millions of new players to Dots each month. With this scale comes new and interesting challenges on how to efficiently organize and process profile and leaderboard data. In addition to data, we’re building a creative and talented engineering team in need of a strong technical leader. Our ideal candidate is as creative as they are process-driven, and knows how to get the best out of a strong team. We’re not stuck to any specific technologies, but we’re currently using Cocos2D, PHP, MySQL, Apportable SDK (for Android), with our API scaled on multiple Amazon EC2 machines. Responsibilities: Provide strategic direction of technical, architectural and design efforts Build and organize growing team with technical disciplines Manage delivery of multiple and concurrent product releases Build, maintain, and evangelize technology best practices across organization Create dev operations infrastructure and process to support rapid growth Deep understanding of industry trends and emerging technologies Work with product team to build a strong quality assurance practice that includes manual and automated testing Personally own a specific technical function as an active developer (iOS, infrastructure, or API) Qualifications: 3 years of technical management and development experience Desire and passion for pushing the bounds of latest technologies Experience with Agile/Scrum/Lean principles and values Experience building scalable solutions for handling high volume traffic Strong communication, analytical and presentation skills Deep subject matter expertise of a specific technical function (infrastructure, backend development, frontend web or mobile development, etc) Apply Now Open Beta Privacy Policy User Agreement Events Jobs Blog Facebook Twitter © 2014 betaworks 416 W 13th Suite 203 New York NY 10014 Made in NY.", is_draft: true, company_id: 101, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://artsy.net/job/developer", title: "FULL STACK SOFTWARE ENGINEER", full_text: "Discover art from leading galleries,museums, and private collections.Search Artists, Artworks, Movements, Mediums or Keyword…BrowseFilterpartnersPostsAboutLog inSign upFull Stack Software Engineer You're an experienced full stack software engineer with an impressive track record in building complex distributed applications written in Ruby and JavaScript. You have used relational databases and have some experience with document or key-value stores, such as MongoDB or Redis. You can show architect-level understanding of large systems in which you played an integral role. Throughout your career you have committed yourself to products over multiple releases and shipped software as an individual contributor or technical lead in a very strong team. You have participated in several open-source projects and maybe even maintained a few. You're passionate about beautiful code and inspiring products and are looking for an opportunity to build something that users love. What is Artsy? In a sentence, Artsy is like Pandora for the fine art world. Our goal: using artificial intelligence we want to make the traditionally closed-off and intimidating art world easily accessible to anyone with an Internet connection. We believe that by increasing access, we can expand the market and get more people educated and passionate about fine art. Why work at Artsy? First and foremost, you will get to work with an amazing team. We invest an extraordinary amount of time finding the best possible people. This means we go through many candidates before making an offer, but as you know, five great engineers are better than a hundred good ones. High alignment between Artsy's business goals and user experience goals. The larger an audience we reach, the more we educate them, and the more we help them discover art they love, the better our business does, and the more we support our institutional partners and the artists they represent. There are no set hours or holidays, no pointless bureaucracy. Work whenever you want, wherever you want. That's the beauty of hiring world-class people, they deliver incredible results and are wonderful to work with — what else matters? The Netflix Culture slides do the best job of describing how we think about culture at Artsy. To create an awesome UX we employ cutting-edge technologies such as Node.js, Backbone.js, Coffeescript, Haml, Sass, Ruby on Rails, and MongoDB; but when we can't find a technology that does what we need… We write our own open-source projects and contribute them back to the community. We are solving very hard problems. To make art historically relevant recommendations, you can't rely on collaborative filtering alone. We do real-time search in 800 dimensional space (one dimension for every art historical category). We are also working on semantic search, fuzzy full-text search, visual similarity search, and high-resolution image tiling and security among others. At its core, Artsy is a technology company. In addition to the engineering team, both the CEO and COO have technical backgrounds (Computer Science from Princeton, and Mathematics from Columbia). Our ultimate goal is to create Artificial Intelligence with the qualities of the world's most omniscient art advisor. If Skynet ends up winning, at least it will have good taste :). We have partnered with over 250 of the largest galleries in the world and several major art museums. No startup has ever come so close to unlocking this massive data set before. Our downtown Manhattan office has stunning 360 degree views of New York. You can see the horizon in all 4 directions, the iconic midtown and downtown skylines, the Hudson and East rivers. This is where we do Stand-up. We have super-value-add investors and advisors including: Peter Thiel, Jack Dorsey, Eric Schmidt, Joe Kennedy (CEO of Pandora), Charlie Cheever (Quora founder), Alexis O'Hanian (Reddit founder), Keith Rabois (COO Square), Founder Collective, Dave Morin (Path founder), Wendi Murdoch, Dasha Zhukova, and Thrive Capital. At Artsy, we are bringing art, science, design, and engineering together. Forgive the cliche, but there's no better way to say it: we want to change the world. If you want to change it with us, please drop us a line and include some links to what you've built: jobs@artsy.net. ©2014 Artsy|AboutJobsPressOpen SourceTerms of UsePrivacy PolicyFeedback", is_draft: true, company_id: 74, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Full Stack", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
