  {link: "https://www.betterment.com/about/jobs/engineering-intern/", title: "Engineering Intern", full_text: "betterment log in try it menu why betterment about us blog faqs pricing story philosophy security press team jobs contact engineering intern about the right team member: you coded your final project in one weekend, don’t get folks who don’t get git, and your best friend is hubot. you can write code without breaking a sweat, and are looking to challenge your skills against new york’s finest. about the internship: you’ll work on a meaningful project that focuses on your area of interest in engineering. some examples of engineering internship projects in the past: - developing a script to automate the data retrieval behind betterment’s past performance widget on a monthly basis - creating five dashboards displaying charts, numbers and maps to make valuable data transparent to everyone in the company. interns also embed with existing engineering teams that are delivering code to production on critical company projects. this is great exposure to what it’s really like being a professional software engineer; something very different from working on independent projects. tech: java, javascript, html, css, android, iphone, web services, git qualifications: prior internship experience at a startup or similar interesting software side project work that’s been completed outside of school proven willingness and ability to build working software major/class preferred: computer science, physics, mathematics, any engineering discipline. junior/senior what makes being a betterment intern the best? you’ll get hands-on, real world work experience at an exciting, young company that wants to see you grow. you’ll work on small teams, side-by-side your mentor and other full-timers, so you can benefit from their expertise and maximize your learning opportunities. you’ll get your foot in the door at a growing company that loves to hire their interns when they finish school. come jo