  {link: "http://www.asheavenue.com/careers/", title: "Back-End Developer", full_text: "Ashe Avenue Contact Blog Careers Services Team Work Careers Back-End Developer Ashe Avenue is searching for an adventurous spirit to join our development team. Do you enjoy experimenting with new technologies? Do you enjoy contributing to the open-source world? Do you find optimization, caching, server architecture, and object-oriented or MVC programming enjoyable? While we typically shun labels, we are looking for a back-end team member with a passion for server-side development. You must possess a feverish desire to produce top quality, D.R.Y. code. You must be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment and wired to research and look for the newest tools, technologies or libraries. You must enjoy jumping between languages, environments and projects while never letting your skills stagnate. You will be working with skilled developers across our Brooklyn and Chapel Hill offices, and collaborate with members of the front-end team to produce high-profile, client-facing work. We have offices in Brooklyn, NY and Chapel Hill, NC so the candidate should live in either of those areas. Please send your resume to jobs [at] asheavenue.com, and be sure to include your GitHub page or links to work you’ve done. Requirements: At least 2 years developing professionally in Ruby, PHP, or server-side Javascript, plus a desire to continually add to your language portfolio Strong understanding and experience with web application frameworks like Rails, Yii, Cake, or Express, etc. Comfort with modern databases, either Postgres, MySQL, or any of the various NoSQL databases (Mongo, Rethink, Couch, etc.) A preference for developing in an agency, consulting, or startup environment Natural curiosity, hunger, and a desire to progress through fast-paced client work Experience with native mobile application development for iOS or Android is preferred but not required. Comfortable working in Linux environments Experience working with Git Nice-to-haves: DevOps or sysadmin experience Experience with native mobile application development for iOS or Android Open-source contributions We offer full health benefits, 401k plans, and employee incentive programs. We love technology, music, and art. We could be your new home. Drop us a line. Seriously. jobs [at] asheavenue.com. Front-End Developer Ashe Avenue is looking for an experienced Front-end Developer responsible for producing HTML markup, CSS and client-side engineering solutions for websites and web applications. The position requires extensive knowledge and understanding of HTML, CSS and JavaScript. This role is production focused with a commitment to client success through a balance of quality, prioritization, creativity and efficiency. Responsibilities: • Ability to work in a collaborative environment and communicate effectively to other members of the team both verbally and in written documentation • Develop using the latest client-side web technologies, specifically HTML5, CSS and JavaScript (jQuery) • Remain current on new technologies and design trends for web, mobile and social media platforms • Collaborate with design, development and client services teams to maintain creative and efficient production processes • Assist in the estimating and scoping process for new work • Maintain and contribute to coding standards to promote best practices and community building both internally and externally • Recommend timely, researched, high-quality solutions and services to clients to further business objectives • Suggest areas for improvement in internal processes, along with possible solutions • Able to work in Brooklyn, NY or Chapel Hill, NC These attributes are pretty essential: • Understands the application of and demonstrates expert knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript • Possesses excellent working knowledge of the Adobe Creative Suite, specifically Photoshop • Thrives in a team environment and facilitates effective team interaction • Familiar with source control principles and comfortable with Git • Experience with coding and deploying applications in a cross-platform and cross-browser environment • Experience with CMS integration and maintenance, especially Drupal • Experience with MVC frameworks such as Yii, Rails, Symphony and CodeIgniter • Experience with PHP, Ruby and other Web programming languages • Familiar with integrating websites and web applications with social media platforms and third party APIs – Ashe Avenue loves you. Ashe Avenue Facebook Twitter LinkedIn Brooklyn 67 West St. Floor 4 (Greendesk, #C6) Brooklyn, NY 11222 Chapel Hill 1506 E Franklin St. Suite 300 Chapel Hill, NC 27514 Stay in the Loop Sign up for the latest news from Ashe Avenue. ©2014 Ashe Avenue Development, LLC", is_draft: true, company_id: 76, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://arc90.recruiterbox.com/jobs/25863/", title: "Mobile App Developer", full_text: "arc90 is looking for a talented mobile developer to design and build an exciting new music platform. you definitely: enjoy creating compelling mobile experiences. have experience developing ios and/or android phone and tablet applications. have experience working with restful apis. have experience implementing mobile analytics. know and respect the ios and android design principles and conventions. value and have implemented mobile app unit testing and test automation. are familiar with mobile performance techniques such as caching and concurrency. can collaborate with designers to plan, test, and implement features. are a good communicator and enjoy working with a team of smart folks. in our wildest dreams, you: are proficient in c, objective-c, cocoa, ios sdk, java, and/or the android sdk. have worked on or released ios/android apps in the app store or google play. have open-source android or ios applications and/or libraries. have experience implementing mobile credit card processing, maps, or qr code scanning. have experience with streaming media to mobile devices. have experience designing and developing restful web services. have experience with html5, css, javascript, and a backend language like python, ruby, clojure. can sling together a join or two in sql. are interested in innovative coding design patterns and approaches. about us arc90 is part of the sfx family of companies. we are a team of designers, developers, and strategists dedicated to building the next generation of electronic music experiences. we offer a relaxed and fun work environment where your input and abilities will have a direct impact on the end product of every project you are a part of. you’ll be part of a tight-knit, supportive, creative, collaborative community that is passionate about building great user experiences, learning new skills and techniques, and doing the right thing. join us! to apply send us a note introducing yourself and why this position appeals to you. include a resume and several code samples. applicants who do not send code samples will not be considered... we like people who can read directions! =", is_draft: true, company_id: 66, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://betaworks.com/job/dots-mobile-engineer-2-openings/", title: "Dots – Mobile Engineer", full_text: "betaworks - a company of builders Purpose Products People Community < Back to Studio Positions Dots – Mobile Engineer (2 openings) Apply Now We’re building more games! We’re scaling our team and titles (games) in pairs of two. Each title has a game designer paired with a mobile engineer. Our game designers know how to code and prototype, but are often self-taught and spend more time thinking about game mechanic, design, and user experience, so they work best when paired with a ridiculously talented and creative mobile engineer. You’ll enjoy working with our team on the entire design process and get to focus on what you do best — building apps. Responsibilities Work with your game designer to turn a concept in high-quality mobile app Write beautiful self-documenting code that others can easily read and adapt Participate in regular code reviews Communicate iOS project status to team in an accurate and detailed way Work with peer teams to share best practices and help out as needed Qualifications 2 years experience in iOS development 6 months experience in Cocos2D development Proficient in C and Objective-C Self-reliant hacker that can quickly adopt new systems and languages Strong communicator with excellent problem solving skills Apply Now Open Beta Privacy Policy User Agreement Events Jobs Blog Facebook Twitter © 2014 betaworks 416 W 13th Suite 203 New York NY 10014 Made in NY.", is_draft: true, company_id: 101, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/lead-software-engineer-test", title: "Lead Software Engineer in Test", full_text: "You want to build, lead and mentor an organization creating the infrastructure, tools, frameworks and test cases to validate the correctness and acceptability of the MongoDB databases and Management Service (MMS). Leading a cross-functional team you need to build reliable mechanisms (automation frameworks, fault-injection, simulation, etc.) to test a distributed database at scale, not just in terms of numbers of nodes, but data volume, throughput, response time etc. Our customers and community value reliability and consistency, so test cases will need to be design with the engineering and product management teams combined with your wild imagination to push the edges and boundaries of the product with the goal of Customer Success. You need to be both a visionary and and effective leader, mentor and manager of people. Responsibilities Architect, Design & Implement frameworks, tools and other building blocks to test the products Effectively leads a team of engineers to build the testing infrastructure and test cases to ensure the correctness, acceptance and performance Work with engineers to perform root-cause analysis and preliminary problem diagnosis Work with MongoDB users and customers to reproduce bug reports from the field Work with the product manager and engineering leads to produce great test plans and ensure that they are completed Juggle priorities and plans in order to make the date Manage, mentor and grow the test team and test function within the engineering organization Provide the tooling for engineers to provide \"early warning\" of degradations in quality (in a sandbox or in the mainline code) Requirements 8+ years leading and/or managing an engineering team Excellent Programming knowledge of (C or C++ preferred, Java / Scala ok) Excellent scripting skills (Shell, JavaScript, Python or Go) Experience testing distributed & enterprise software Excellent verbal & written communication skills Strong UNIX/Linux operational skills (Windows a bonus) Strong problem-solving skills Should have experience with cloud providers (Amazon EC2, Azure, Joyent , Rackspace, Softlayer) Should have database experience (SQL or Non-relational) Should have experience with/knowledge of hypervisor technologies (KVM, VMWare, Xen or Hyper-V)", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 8, sub_dept: "Testing", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://arc90.recruiterbox.com/jobs/22142/", title: "Java Developer", full_text: "Java Developer to design and build a new music platform New York, New York, United States Arc90 is looking for a talented Java developer. You will work closely with the team to design, build, test, and deliver the features that make up our client’s software platform. If you are interested in cutting edge technology, but have a strong background in traditional Java service development, we want you! We’ve got plenty of challenging problems, a fantastic team and development environment with which to tackle them. We are looking for someone who: Is a smart, motivated, focused person who enjoys crafting great software. Has strong software development skills building RESTful web services using Java technologies. Has a broad range of interests when it comes to development. When building software, you tend to have the users’ experience in mind. Can sling together a JOIN or two in SQL. Understands the benefits of writing tests Is either in or moving to NYC (preferred), or is particularly great at working remotely Is a good communicator and enjoys working with teams of smart folks. In our wildest dreams you: Have tinkered with Clojure, with an interest in further experimentation. Are an expert in SQL Server, especially stored procedures wrangling. Have experienced performance tuning applications on the JVM. About us Arc90 is part of the SFX family of companies. We are a team of designers, developers, and strategists dedicated to building the next generation of electronic music experiences. We offer a relaxed and fun work environment where your input and abilities will have a direct impact on the end product of every project you are a part of. You’ll be part of a tight-knit, supportive, creative, collaborative community that is passionate about building great user experiences, learning new skills and techniques, and doing the right thing. Join us! To apply: Send a short note introducing yourself and why this position appeals to you. Include a resume and several code samples. Applicants who do not send code samples will not be considered… we like people who can read directions! Apply for this position or See other jobs at Arc90 Application Form First Name * Last Name Email * Phone * Resume * Cover Letter * Twitter Handle * Website / Blog / Portfolio Github Profile * Code Samples Tell your friends about this position In October 2013, Arc90 was acquired by SFX Entertaiment. We're continuing to do the same great product work we've always done, but now we're applying our skills to create an exciting new music platform. You can read about the announcement on our blog.", is_draft: true, company_id: 66, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/mongodb-database-kernel-engineer", title: "MongoDB Database Kernel Engineer", full_text: "MongoDB is looking for outstanding engineers to work on its popular database server. The engineer's main goal is to develop the next generation of MongoDB and to maintain the current one. Kernel engineers work on MongoDB internals, contributing with design, code, and test for the product. They'll be involved in a range of opportunities, from design and implementation of new features to troubleshooting and fixing existing ones. This position is based in our New York City headquarters. Relocation assistance provided.Responsibilities Understand and improve current functionality of the MongoDB Kernel Identify, design, implement, test, launch and support next generation features related to scalability, reliability, robustness, usability, security, and performance of the product Work with other engineers to coordinate seamless changes in a feature-rich, large code base Work with client drivers, support, consulting, training, and marketing teams to coordinate changes Requirements Strong domain knowledge of at least one of the following: distributed systems, concurrency control and recovery, data replication, file systems and storage, compiler and code generation, query processing and optimization. (Be prepared to offer an engineering talk on a domain of your choice.) Hands-on experience building industrial-strength software related to at least one of your domain knowledge areas above Experience with large code bases, either in C++ or C, and Linux development B.Sc. in Computer Science. M.Sc. and Ph.D. in relevant domain a plus Nice to haves Have a passion for contributing to open source Development in more than one of the following platforms: *nix, Windows, and MacOS Ability to independently expand knowledge of new domains Last, but not least, desire to take an active role in innovation Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, sub_dept: "Dev Ops", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://arc90.recruiterbox.com/jobs/22145/", title: "Python Web Developer", full_text: "arc90 is looking for a talented python developer to join our team. you definitely: are a smart, motivated, focused person who enjoys crafting great software. have a strong understanding of python. have dabbled with and are conversant in another language or two (preferably javascript). have a broad range of interests when it comes to development. when building software, you tend to have the users’ experience in mind. have a bias towards shipping software. you understand technical debt and why it is sometimes necessary. can sling together a join or two in sql. have an in-depth understanding of programming as a craft. this doesn’t necessarily mean a bs in computer science or anything, but if you’ve got one, great. understand the benefits of writing tests. are either in or moving to nyc (preferred), or are in the americas and particularly great at working remotely. are a good communicator and enjoy working with teams of smart folks. if you’re a cowboy coder, look elsewhere. it’d be nice if you: have experience with a wsgi web framework (like django or similar). have experience scaling websites. understand and enjoy http and restful web applications. about arc90 arc90 is part of the sfx family of companies. we are a team of designers, developers, and strategists dedicated to building the next generation of electronic music experiences. we offer a relaxed and fun work environment where your input and abilities will have a direct impact on the end product of every project you are a part of. you’ll be part of a tight-knit, supportive, creative, collaborative community that is passionate about building great user experiences, learning new skills and techniques, and doing the right thing. join us! to apply: when you apply, please provide a few python code samples with your resume. apply for this position or see other jobs at arc90 application form first name * last name email * phone * resume * cover letter * twitter handle website / blog / portfolio github profile * code samples tell your friends about this position in october 2013, arc90 was acquired by sfx entertaiment. we're continuing to do the same great product work we've always done, but now we're applying our skills to create an exciting new music platform. you can read about the announcement on our blog.", is_draft: true, company_id: 66, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
