  {link: "http://www.bustedtees.com/jobs", title: "Web Designer", full_text: "bustedtees, the webs leading comedy e-commerce site is seeking an ambitious, well-rounded web designer with front-end development experience. we're a small, fun-loving team dedicated to bringing the best funny t-shirts and cool stuff to the internet. our goal at bustedtees is to make people laugh which means working here is pretty much awesome! the founders of collegehumor started bustedtees in 2004 and we're still working with them to put out hilarious products every week. we're re located in downtown manhattan, are growing rapidly! as a candidate, you must be excited to work on different aspects of our design team including web design ui.ux, email template design, t-shirt design and ad design.you should be comfortable working in an collaborative environment that feels like a start-up. about the role: collaborate with the engineering and product team to design beautiful and intuitive web pages and interfaces. optimize current web product through iterative design process including ui.ux, graphic design and a/b testing. designing t-shirts for bustedtees! designing landing pages, emails and advertisements . editing images from photo-shoots and occasionally prepping files for print with our screen printer. collaborate and contribute to our creative process, vetting ideas from collegehumor, funnyordie, tmz and upright citzen brigade writers and offering your own! about you: design clean, intuitive and beautiful user interfaces across multiple devices and platforms. deliver organized, notated design documents compliant with web standards. code your design on the fro and be able to test and execute your code across browsers. comfortable with graphic design/illustration in addition to web design, youâ\u0080\u0099re happy to design a t-shirt or ad creative from scratch! you love optimization and a/b testing, it doesnâ\u0080\u0099t just have to look better, it has to work better and the numbers have to prove it! practice consistent design formatting and work within templates so your work is standardized and scalable. high attention to detail. you love at least one of the following: pop culture, movies, tv, video games, comedy (if you donâ\u0080\u0099t love one of those we assume youâ\u0080\u0099re dead and need not apply) you have an online portfolio with working sites or examples. position is based in manhattan, remote applicants not considered but you can move here, itâ\u0080\u0099s awesome! your experience: 2-3 years of professional design experience expert knowledge of the entire adobe suite. experience designing for web experience with ui.ux design experience with graphic design working knowledge of javascript experience with illustration experience working on a transactional web product preferred. this position is for working onsite.", is_draft: true, company_id: 157, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.axial.net/about/careers/", title: "Front-End Engineer", full_text: "As a Front-End Engineer at Axial, you’re responsible for developing and refining the client-facing HTML, Javascript and CSS portions of our platform. We’re a tight-knit team here so collaboration is a must. You’ll be building technology hands-on with a small product and design team, and be responsible for prototyping and creating responsive and elegant UIs to drive site engagement and manageability.\n\nYou’ll also be working to help us improve our service aggregators, applications templating, and client-side libraries, and to extend and improve the power and scale of the Axial platform. You will be challenged to deconstruct designs into fine-grained, distributed modules capable of reuse in any portion of our platform.\n\nYou’ll be challenged to engineer great, sustainable technology at high speed, but that’s okay ‘cause you’re a champ.\n\nWe look for technologists who:\n\n- Are expert at working with JavaScript, HTML, and CSS\n- Are intimately familiar with browser quirks\n- Love creating well-crafted interfaces and elegant web UI’s\n- Communicate and collaborate well\n\nBonus points for:\n\n- Bootstrap, jQuery, or Django\n- Experience developing in *NIX environments\n- Experience with a non-JavaScript programming language (python, php, ruby, perl, sh)\n\nThe benefits of being an Axialite …\n\nwe are building something very important\nthe team you’re joining is pretty darn good and getting better with every new hire\nwe pay people what they’re worth, not what we can get away with\nstocked and ever-expanding technical library onsite\nstocked fridge and bottomless coffee\nbike-friendly\ngood location w/ roof in the Flatiron", is_draft: true, company_id: 88, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://adstruc.com/s/home/jobs/director-engineering", title: "Director of Engineering", full_text: "Login Forgot your password? Login I am a: Agency Advertiser Operator « Back to jobs Director of Engineering Location: NYC Department: Engineering Type: Full Time We Are Looking For: ADstruc seeks an experienced Director of Engineering to lead its software engineering team, oversee the design and architecture of its flagship media-buying platform, and continuously prepare it for growth. Responsibilities: Lead a small team of software engineers in a startup environment Manage the performance of your team, helping them become even better engineers and grow in their careers Spend 25-50% of your time hands-on, working on everything from backend and user-interface to database systems and third-party integrations Work alongside product management to evolve the team’s agile development process and foster a positive and results-driven engineering culture Manage the availability and performance of all environments, continuously fixing bottlenecks and planning for growth Occasionally attend client meetings and participate in business discussions where strategy and technology intersect Lead the hiring of all future software engineers Requirements: 5-7 years of software engineering experience with 2+ years in a leadership role Experience developing web applications with agile methodologies Excellent coding, design, and architectural skills (PHP, SQL, Linux) A record of successful contributions to a productive engineering culture Experience managing environments, scaling web applications, and using monitoring tools (e.g. Nagios, Zabbix) Strong interpersonal communication skills and experience interfacing with clients A college degree from a Computer Science program Benefits: Apple equipment Competitive salary Health, dental and vision insurance Stock options Team outings, including volunteering at various charities Great SoHo office space Free ping pong lessons We Are: ADstruc is the leading buying platform for the outdoor advertising industry, including both traditional and digital Out-of-Home media. With an emphasis on data-driven planning, ADstruc's platform helps agencies, national brands, and local businesses discover and efficiently purchase Out-of-Home media across hundreds of operators. Our cloud-based solution also allows outdoor advertising operators to easily manage and promote their inventory online and interact with clients in real-time. Our entire team is based in Soho and we are backed by some of the biggest names in venture capital, including DFJ, RRE, SoftTech, Founder Collective and more. Apply for this position About | Jobs | Blog | Tech Blog | Telmar Partnership | Privacy | Terms of Service | Help | Contact Us | Sitemap | Made in NY | Twitter How Much Does A Billboard Cost? ADstruc is the leading buying platform for the outdoor advertising industry, including both traditional and digital Out-of-Home media. With an emphasis on data-driven planning, ADstruc's platform helps agencies, national brands, and local businesses discover and efficiently purchase Out-of-Home media across hundreds of operators. Our cloud-based solution also allows outdoor advertising operators to easily manage and promote their inventory online and interact with clients in real-time. © 2010 - 2012 ADstruc, Inc. Certain products are subject to patents pending. Questions? Chat with us.", is_draft: true, company_id: 31, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 5, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://bark.co/jobs/senior-front-end-engineer/", title: "Senior Front-End Engineer", full_text: "Senior Front-End Engineer\nWoof! Arf! Yip! ArrroOOooOoo! Do you love sniffing around the back end? Do you find it difficult to write code because of your clumsy paws? Does the question, “who’s a good engineer?” give you anxiety attacks?\nThen you’re barking up the right tree!\nBark & Co. is a fast-growing business for people who love (*ruv) dogs and is dedicated to building products that foster the health and happiness of dogs everywhere.\nAre you an amazing engineer? Then should probably work at Bark & Co, here’s why:\nkayla\n“OK glass, find bacon.”\nDogs: You love dogs, dogs love you. We have plenty of pups in the office.\nGrowth: We are growing super fast and we need incredibly smart folk to build incredible dog apps.\nImpact: Every dev has a huge impact on how we work and how we build things.\nFancy Tech: Love machine learning? Love to work on highly scalable systems? Want to create an app for Google Glass? This is your place.\nExciting Problems: Have the urge to mathematically calculate the optimal treat for a 5lb Chihuahua? (Hint: It’s probably poop) We have lots of data to comb through.\nBrand Spankin’ New Office: Complete with pods to work in, beer fridge, and dog beds.\nBenefits: Competitive salary and equity, 401k and health insurance.\nBenefits Your Pup: Unlimited dog treats, belly rubs, BarkBox, and PetPlan health insurance.\nInterested?\nSend us a note at tech@bark.co with links to your work and a photo of your pup (if applicable). The quantity of your experience is not nearly as important as the quality of it. Code examples and shipped products speak volumes to us.\nThis position is full-time salaried position (with equity) and on-site at our amazing new office in Chinatown, New York. We offer health insurance for both you and your pup, 401k, wonderful team lunches, and a warm dog to pet anytime you wish.", is_draft: true, company_id: 92, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://bitly.theresumator.com/apply/LwnAzh/Lead-Android-Developer.html", title: "LEAD ANDROID DEVELOPER", full_text: "go to our web site » « go back to job listings lead android developer location: new york, ny department: engineering type: full time min. experience: experienced bitly is looking for an experienced android engineer to join our team! you should have experience developing for a wide range of android devices, and be prepared to carry a project from start to finish. ideal candidates should have a strong design sense, knowledge in the latest android design trends, and be able to collaborate with a design and product team.more about the jobyou will be creating android applications, widgets and additional tools for major android versions, screen resolutions and device skins.take part in the full lifecycle of application development: from requirement through development, to maintenance and enhancement.work with existing design, product and engineering teams to develop bitly’s android presence.development of tools and sdks to further bitly integration with third party android applications.about you:worked with eclipse, intellij or other major android ide and the android java sdk.a knowledge and love of mobile development, especially android development.a track record of successful releases and maintenance of android applications.in-depth, articulate skills with android interface and design best practices.comfortable with working in teams across disciplines, as well as self-driven development.qualifications2+ years of android experience4+ years of software and/or web development experience, especially mobileat least one app a major android app store (google play, amazon)experience with a wide variety of android device resolutions and sdk versions preferable.strong technical background required, design and user experience skills a plusa bachelors in computer science or equivalent experienceexperience working with remote data via rest and jsonexperienc