  {link: "http://www.bombfell.com/about/jobs", title: "Web Developer", full_text: "bombfell requires javascript to work properly please relead the page after enabling javascript on your browser. have an account? sign in | (0) items in cart how it works pricing threads faq get started get a jobby job web developer you you're wicked smaht and get sh*t done with minimal supervision. you're familiar with web technologies, databases and can get nice 'n comfy on both the front end and back end. you write code because it's frackin' fun. you like to say words like \"frack\". the role we're looking for someone to build out the infrastructure that enables us to make clothing a solved problem for the awesome man. you'll fundamentally shape the matching algorithms that help us figure out what clothes a certain guy will love. you'll build out internal dashboards so we can obsessively monitor the crazy highs and teary-eyed lows of our company's key metrics. you'll release code that makes our heart skip a beat, break things that make our blood boil, and then we'll all argue and make up. perks lunch is provided every day, as are office snacks (but keep your hands off my annie's bunny grahams). we also provide a monthly unlimited ride metrocard. giddy up send us your resume and anything that highlights your ability to get sh*t done (github, open source work, sample code). intern web developer you you're familiar with computer science concepts and can demonstrate fluency in at least one language. you're eager to learn and make a difference. you write code because it's frackin' fun. you like to say words like \"frack\". the role we're looking for someone with the potential to grow into a kick-ass professional developer. you'll learn to code front-end, back-end (and in between). you'll help build our algorithms and logistical processes, and make a huge impact on how we operate. you'll push out code on your first day and if it breaks, we'll make sure to fix it. perks lunch is provided every day, as are office snacks (but keep your hands off my annie's bunny grahams). we also provide a monthly unlimited ride metrocard. giddy up send us your resume and anything that highlights your ability to get sh*t done (github, open source work, sample code). e-commerce fashion intern you you have an eye for fashion. you're a trendsetter. and you're a whiz at excel and photoshop. you're ambitious, smart and anal. you're efficient and organized. you're not afraid to give your opinion. and you always want to get your hands dirty. the role as a key member of our operations team, you'll whip our inventory into shape, then tell us what we're doing is stupid and lay out how we can do it better. you'll work with our stylists to provide customer support, measure clothes and pack boxes. you'll assist the buyers with inventory decisions, and do whatever it takes to keep the wheels moving, because that's what we all do and that's what makes startups awesome. most importantly, you'll learn how to create order out of chaos, how to hold things together with paper clips and chewing gum and other real-world skills for startups that you won't learn in a classroom. we're looking for someone who can work part time (approx. 20 hrs/wk) for us starting immediately. qualifications must be working towards college degree (or a recent college graduate). interest in fashion (especially menswear) is a must! must be super duper duper detail-oriented!!! must have a positive attitude, be self motivated and eager to learn. must be willing to do manual labor (able to lift 50 lbs). must be able to do data entry and analysis. must be tech-savvy and have excel and pc proficiency. must have excellent written and verbal communication skills. excellent interpersonal, customer service, organizational and problem-solving skills. able to take direction and constructive feedback. key responsibilities keep abreast of key trends for styling users. participate in purchase order entry and other data entry and filing as needed. assist with receiving and processing inventory. research and distribute product knowledge to stylists and internal team. assist with merchandise damages and credits from vendors. tag and organize electronic pictures of inventory. assist in styling photo shoots, including setup and breakdown. giddy up send us a copy of your resume in pdf format along with a cover letter describing why you think you would be the perfect bombfell intern. about faq blog contact give a gift how it works pricing threads jobs free returns & exchanges international shipping free email updates menswear trends, clothing picks and awesome giveaways. © 2014 bombfell, inc. terms of service privacy policy × item has been added to cart continue shopping checkout contact us! drop us a note and we'll respond shortly thanks! we'll be in touch. whoops! please try again later send", is_draft: true, company_id: 129, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
