  {link: "http://www.anvilandgear.com/jobs/", title: "Cryptocurrency / Bitcoin Services Developer", full_text: "+ Menu About Capabilities Clients Contact Jobs The Next Great Adventure. We look for hungry and passionate individuals who are not only great at what they do, but are always striving to be better. Our culture is that of a tight knit team who knows how to work together to accomplish the impossible. And we believe this can only happen with an exceptional team that knows how to learn quickly, support each other and most importantly strive for new discoveries in each undertaking. Take a look at our current openings and if something sounds challenging and exciting, well then, we would certainly like to hear from you. Cryptocurrency / Bitcoin Services Developer Overview We are looking for a versatile, quick learning and up-and-coming developer to join our newly formed Cryptocurrency Services team. We strongly believe in the future of cryptocurrency (Bitcoin, as well as the larger digital/cryptocurrency space) and are looking for someone to work with us to create services to help traders, miners and investors. Role As a service developer you will be working with agency partners, user experience and design teams as well as senior engineers to develop web services in a variety of areas in the cryptocurrency sector. The structure of the team is unique in that the majority of the team will be splitting their time between this endeavor and the consulting arm of the company (though this role is solely in the cryptocurrency space). Additionally, there are two engineers leading development remotely. Both have extensive industry experience and work at the staff/principal level at major technology companies (you know and use these services). They will be working remote with you and the rest of the team here in NYC to design and implement the system. This role will be part research, part systems engineer and part pure development. You will work to help refine service ideas and then to see them through development, deployment and maintenance. Key Technologies / Skills You don’t need them all but more is better, and as this is a quickly emerging space, being a fast and effective learner is key above all. Python Amazon Web Services / EC2 Google App Engine Distributed Cloud Systems CSS / HTML / Javascript Systems Administration / Systems Reliability Git Cryptocurrencies, cryptocurrency services (Bitcoin, pools, exchanges, mining software, etc.) Financial services / finance software Compensation This is a new endeavor for us, and in almost all accounts a startup. However, we have the advantage of being able to leverage a highly capable design team, and have the space and equipment necessary to get up and running. That being said we are not a large enough company to skip bootstrapping this endeavor to profitability. This position will pay a monthly stipend of $2k/month while the initial projects get off the ground. Also, for experienced candidates an equity stake in the endeavor is very much on the table as well. Our goal here is not to get something for nothing, but to use all the resources we can spare to build this as soon as possible. We are looking for someone excited enough about cryptocurrencies to believe in building something with us. We believe that we should be generating revenue in the first 4-6 months and as soon as that happens we can scale this role up to full time with a market and experience appropriate salary. Culture We have always had the startup mentality and have a small, closely knit team. We work incredibly hard, and our business is delivering results in high pressure situations for clients of every size. That being said, we highly value an independent and laid back work culture. We hate micromanagement and believe that every member of the team should be responsible for their own time. The short of it We have an amazing and growing team, great office environment, excellent (and extensive) bourbon collection, an incredible amount of passion for the space and a set of opportunities the likes of which have never been seen before. This is a chance build the something truly amazing alongside fantastic people. If this sounds exciting then let’s talk about building the future together. Please send in a resume/cover letter/work samples and/or any information you think would help us get to know you and understand your experience, skill set and personality. We look forward to hearing from you. jobs@anvilandgear.com Anvil · and · Gear Anvil: The age of tools. A symbol of the forge and the first steps of engineering. Gear: The age of industry. The symbol and building block of machines. Contact Us 25 Broadway, Floor 9 New York, New York 10004hello@anvilandgear.com+1 (347) 565.4327 © Anvil and Gear, Inc. 2012", is_draft: true, company_id: 52, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://jobs.amicushq.com/", title: "Frontenders", full_text: "Frontenders\n\nYou delight in pushing browsers to their limits.\nRealtime interactions are your middle names.\nYou're not afraid of a little RoR.", is_draft: true, company_id: 48, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.1stdibs.com/about/jobs/mobile-architect", title: "Mobile Architect", full_text: "We are currently seeking a Mobile Architect to join our Engineering team based in NYC. The Mobile Architect will be responsible for the strategy, development, and design of our new mobile apps. Experience within fast-paced consumer-facing brands are a must.\n \nSome of what you’ll do…                  \n \nLead development and help design a suite of iOS and Android apps for 1stdibs\nBuild out our mobile team to complement existing services, front-end, and operations teams\nFocus on applications targeted towards consumers, designers as well as dealers within the luxury goods industry\nLeverage shared services and contribute toward the creation of a robust internal API\nDevelop, prototype, and test new ideas, and remain at the forefront of mobile technology trends\n \nAbout you…\nMinimum 3 years experience building native iOS applications, including one\nor more functional, high-usage app in the App Store.\nAbility to troubleshoot and explain performance bottlenecks\nExperience creating real-world APIs for mobile\nExperience writing and debugging multi-threaded code.\nPrior use of CoreData, MapKit, and Push Notification libraries.\nAndroid experience a plus", is_draft: true, company_id: 6, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://www.smartrecruiters.com/AppboyInc/74187360-mobile-development-lead", title: "MOBILE DEVELOPMENT LEAD", full_text: "Mobile Development Lead New York, NY Company Description Appboy is a rapidly growing analytics and marketing automation platform for mobile apps. Job Description Appboy is a rapidly growing analytics and marketing automation platform for mobile apps. We're looking for a mobile software engineer with a strong background in product ownership and team leadership to become the cross-platform engineering lead of our mobile SDKs. The Appboy mobile SDK powers the analytics collection and messaging delivery for billions of events a month across tens of millions of devices on iOS and Android. While continuing to enhance the SDKs for our existing deployments, we'll also be rapidly expanding our platform availability in the coming quarters. As the mobile development lead, you'll be expected to live and breathe mobile of all kinds, ensuring that Appboy's mobile SDKs are of top-notch engineering quality and providing great user experiences for both the developers that use our SDK as well as the users who interact with the built-in messaging. It's a unique opportunity to serve both technologists and users, valuing elegance of design and performance while delivering high quality, cutting-edge user experience. Responsibilities Ensure execution of the SDK product roadmap. Work with other mobile developers to plan and design feature implementations and software architecture for all SDKs. Contribute to the development and coding of one or more SDKs (depending on platform expertise and need). Utilize a strong mobile product sense to ensure that implementation of the roadmap benefits the developers, marketers and end-users who user our software. Qualifications Extensive development experience in at least one major mobile platform, as well as experience or willingness to learn others. Degree in computer science or equivalent experience. Past experience leading a team of developers to deliver user or client facing products. Intense interest in the mobile ecosystem and a strong desire to learn and explore new technologies. Background in work on systems, software design, concurrency and API design. Posted by Blake Walsh share this job The free social recruiting platform Learn more", is_draft: true, company_id: 56, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://jobs.amicushq.com/", title: "Rubyist", full_text: "Features Careers We're hiring! Tweet Apply or refer a friend and you could win $2,000, a dairy cow donated in your name, and so much more... Apply Refer If we hire you or the person you refer, you'll get all of: Why Amicus? Amicus is reshaping civil society through innovation. We believe profits and social good can go hand in hand. At Amicus, you can work for a fast growing startup that's disrupting a really large market and feel great about what you do. Nonprofits in the U.S. currently spend $60 billion annually to raise $300 billion — 20 cents on the dollar! We build tools that increase the amount nonprofits raise, while drastically decreasing their costs. Amicus puts more money in the hands of great organizations and creates lots of value in the process. Tired of deciding whether to do good or do well? You've come to the right place. Oh, and we're based in New York City*, the Rome of our time. *Not based in NYC? Amicus can fix that. Our Investors Amicus is backed by an amazing group of investors: Who we're looking for You're a talented, socially-conscious developer looking for a rigorous project with tangible civic returns. You could write code in your sleep, but you're kept awake at night thinking about how to direct your skills towards a more meaningful impact. Rubyists You dream in RoR. Front-end, back-end, you'll code it all. Agile is your middle name. Frontenders You delight in pushing browsers to their limits. Realtime interactions are your middle names. You're not afraid of a little RoR. Director of Partner Success You'd write a book on nonprofit tech, but you're too busy using it. You manage web/digital programs for nonprofits. You know lots of people who do what you do, and they know you. Job Application Marketing & Copywriting Intern You love to write, and you're really good at it. You're eager to learn about social good startups. You have published awesome things on the internets. Job 