  {link: "http://www.1stdibs.com/about/jobs/front-end-engineer-javascript-html-css", title: "Front-End Engineer (JavaScript, HTML, CSS)", full_text: "We need your ideas and passion for good, clean design!  Ground floor opportunity for front-end enthusiasts who want to code things The Right Way™.  Opportunity to contribute to the design and development of our new site(s).  Additional coding to optimize existing site, as necessary.\nSome of what you'll do…  \nArchitect and implement complex user interactions through JavaScript, CSS and HTML\nCreate highly optimized code\nLeverage best practices to create modularized reusable code\nEmbrace object-oriented front-end architecture\nLeverage your experience with object-oriented PHP (or similar)\nUnderstand and love responsive design and modular CSS\nEmbrace MV* on the client-side\nUtilize server-side technology as a last resort, only when client-side JavaScript cannot do and the services team cannot provide\nWork with our top Product team which includes former leaders from Gilt, eBay and Zappos\nAbout you…\nExperience developing code for high-traffic web sites\nAbility to troubleshoot and explain performance bottlenecks\nBe awesome and make those around you awesome!\nAbility to bring your intellectual curiosity and thoughtful opinions with you everyday                 \nExperience developing consumer-facing websites in a professional production environment a plus\nAn appreciation for one-of-a-kind items such as furniture, art and jewelry always welcome\nYour participation in the larger Developer Community is strongly supported and encouraged!\nTechnical experience pluses:- (JavaScript - jQuery, Underscore, Backbone), (CSS preprocessor - Sass), (PHP - CodeIgnitor, Twig, Assetic, PHPUnit)", is_draft: true, company_id: 6, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://ch.tbe.taleo.net/CH04/ats/careers/requisition.jsp?org=APPLICO&cws=37&rid=16", title: "Connected Designer", full_text: "About Offerings Resources Careers Contact Connected Revolution Connected Designer Location: New York, NY DescriptionApplico helps businesses turn their products into platforms Applico is trailblazing a new type of services firm, the platform innovation company. It is our belief that platforms are the key business model in the Connected Revolution, and as a mobile industry visionary and thought leader, we help position our clients to compete where the market is going - not just where it is today. We meld the worlds of strategy and implementation to help turn our clients products into platforms. Our end-to-end services provide our clients with all the help they need to build and scale innovative platforms that disrupt markets and invigorate internal cultural shifts. As a member of the Applico team, connected designers will be responsible for creating immersive experience that represent our, as well as the clients, brand. Our designers strive to be unicorns with focus on both user experience and visual design. This person will be tasked with cultivating our design first culture as well as pushing the boundaries of our digital products. Role: Conceive, design and architect dynamic and visually stunning user interfaces for mobile devices Develop and iterate on standardized documentation to represent both visual and user experience work product Work closely with the product and development teams to create visual and user experience requirements Contribute to and practice user centric design in every aspect of the SDLC Product rapid design iterations based on user feedback, technical constraints and market dynamics Effectively communicate design concepts to other members of the Product Engineering team Assist in production design to accurately and efficiently deliver assets to the engineering teams Control your design by being a valued member of the QA team. Each iteration is controlled by our designers. Partner with clients on business goals from a visual perspective Collaborate with senior management on the long term vision for what constitutes a mobile experience Is able to quickly adapt to multiple SDLC’s (Agile vs. Waterfall) Values user testing as much as we do! Skills / Experience: Cross Platform (Android, Windows, iOS, HTML) mobile application design experience Expert in Photoshop, Illustrator, Keynote and inDesign Experience with agile and scrum type tools Proficient with a range of interaction design, visualization and rapid design prototyping tools Proven ability to assess, prioritize and make design trade-offs against business, technical and user constraints Current and thorough understanding of consumer internet, enterprise, mobile, and connected technologies Ability to comfortably articulate, pitch and sell ideas Demonstrated portfolio of award winning projects Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in Communications, HCI, Fine Arts or related area Are you a returning applicant? Previous Applicants: Email: Password: If you do not remember your password click here. Back to Search Results New Search Our WorkStrategy Design Development AboutOur Company Our Story Our Values Leadership Board of Directors Partners & Awards OfferingsOfferings Strategy Product Management Design Engineering QA Analytics Practice Areas Platforms MoreNews Blog Resources Contact Careers Connected Revolution All rights reserved. © 2013 Applico Inc. | i f t g r", is_draft: true, company_id: 60, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Mobile", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
