  {link: "https://arc90.recruiterbox.com/jobs/28598/", title: "Director of IT Infrastructure", full_text: "SFX Entertainment requires an experienced IT professional to oversee all aspects of its IT infrastructure needs in its 5 New York area offices. The ideal candidate for this position is able to deftly design, plan, coordinate,manage and execute IT projects and activities in a collaborative and effective manner. Areas of Responsibility Wireless and wired networks Internet connection service Video and voice telecom systems Device support (“help desk”) This role does not include oversight of any other communication or collaboration tools, services, or technologies. In other words, the focus is on the physical IT infrastructure of the business, not the application layer. Capabilities & Responsibilities: Ability to articulate and establish IT departmental goals, objectives, operatingprocedures and best practices Ability to communicate these to staff and management team, and connect these to business practices Communicate IT progress and achievements in terms that non-technical staff can understand Provide device support (hardware and OS) to 100+ users across 5 offices — including Windows, Mac, iOS, and Android devices, and printers Support LAN and WAN network including routers, VPN, firewalls. Manage company voice and video telecommunications, video conferencing and A/V related office equipment and services Expertly handle vendor relations, contract management, SLAs, renewals. etc... Facility with Budgeting and Scoping Requirements: Strong technical knowledge of networks and operating systems Strong technical knowledge of current network hardware, protocols, and standards especially with Cisco routers and ASAs Strong and proven project management skills Strong consensus/relationship building and communications skills Experience with data back-up and disaster recovery solutions Proven experience in IT infrastructure planning and development 3+ years of IT experience a