  {link: "http://www.blenderbox.com/company/jobs/front-end-designer-developer", title: nil, full_text: "Blenderbox projects company news search search Design Front-end Designer/Developer If you are a talented visual designer who knows HTML and CSS inside-out, this is the gig for you. Your responsibilities will include working with the team to brainstorm concepts, developing original designs, executing visuals based on established design direction, production design and putting together stylesheets and design specs. You should know Photoshop/Illustrator/Indesign and CSS/HTML have a solid understanding of designing with grids and design for user interface and navigation have a portfolio showing awesome layout and typography skills be able to design for mobile and tablet be detail-oriented be able to work both independently and as part of a team be comfortable juggling multiple projects have great communication skills love a good challenge be motivated to learn have 1+ years working in the digital space, preferably in an agency setting We offer a dynamic working environment, competitive compensation, a benefits plan that includes health and dental, 401k and a generous vacation package. No Recruiters, please. Work with Us Think this position might be a good fit for you? If you live in the NYC area and are qualified to work in the US, please send us your details: I'd like to apply for the Front-end Designer/Developer position. You can check out my website here: , and my resume and cover letter are attached here. Sincerely, Your Face HereJoin the Team About UsBlender who? DesignVisual DesignerCalling all designers... join our quest for pixel perfection. 26 Dobbin St. 3rd Fl. Brooklyn, NY 11222Tel: 718.963.4594Facebook Twitter Jobs » Contact » Blog » © 2014 blenderbox, inc. All rights reserved", is_draft: true, company_id: 119, dept: nil, years_exp: 1, sub_dept: nil, description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.blenderbox.com/company/jobs/web-developer", title: "Web Developer", full_text: "Blenderbox projects company news search search Technology Web Developer We're looking for a well-rounded developer who is eager to join our fun and exciting development team. We use a combination of technologies including .NET/SQL Server, PHP/MYSQL, Django, and ROR and are constantly learning and experimenting with new techniques and technologies. As a Blenderbox Developer, you will balance your intimate knowledge of front-end and back-end technologies including DB schema and best-of-breed front-end HTML/CSS with our emerging self-defined process of Agile Development using MVC, Restful architecture and good object oriented design. It's ok if you specialize in one particular technology, but familiarity with multiple languages and the ability to work with a team on multiple projects is a must. To apply, use the form or send us an email with the subject line “Blenderbox Developer” Attach your resume in PDF format and include a link to your online portfolio. New York City area candidates only. No phone calls, please. Blenderbox is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Work with Us Think this position might be a good fit for you? If you live in the NYC area and are qualified to work in the US, please send us your details: I'd like to apply for the Web Developer position. You can check out my website here: , and my resume and cover letter are attached here. Sincerely, Your Face HereJoin the Team About UsBlender who? DesignFront-end Designer/DeveloperJoin our creative team and help us to bring great designs to life. 26 Dobbin St. 3rd Fl. Brooklyn, NY 11222Tel: 718.963.4594Facebook Twitter Jobs » Contact » Blog » © 2014 blenderbox, inc. All rights reserved", is_draft: true, company_id: 119, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: nil, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://www.betterment.com/about/jobs/product-engineer/", title: "Product Engineer", full_text: "Not only are you a JavaScript wizard or full stack generalist, but nothing motivates you more than your friends using the stuff you’re building.We believe in close collaboration over verbose documentation. You’ll sit side-by-side with product managers and user experience designers, refining the product to delight our customers. If you’re passionate about high-quality code and making the customer experience a great one, there’s a seat for you at Betterment.Tech:Backbone.js, Sass, Grunt.js, Casper.js, Node.js, JavaAt Betterment, you’re going to…Build things people love. Our goal is to delight our customers whenever possible. Sleek design, simple user experience, and access to smart decisions help us to achieve it.Solve problems. Take your ideas to the next level right away. We experiment, iterate, learn, and repeat.Collaborate, with purpose. You’ll work in small groups with other talented thinkers and figure out how to make Betterment’s revolutionary software even better.Gain trust through transparency. We believe in taking the guesswork out of investing. That means a consistent experience for our customers — you’ll build the tools to make it possible.Create efficiency. Our software helps customers save time and money. We maintain it through clean code, pragmatic programming, and lean engineering.Work with people who care. Half of our team is made up of engineers but we believe everyone at Betterment is an engineer with their own tools. We’re a group of talented professionals who pride ourselves on what we do. We’re smart, innovative, energetic, and lots of fun.Come join usTo apply, please email your resume and a short cover letter in pdf format to jobs@betterment.com with the subject line “Product Engineer”.", is_draft: true, company_id: 103, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
