  {link: "http://www.i-m.co/appycouple/AppyJobs/open-jobs.html", title: "FRONT-END DEVELOPER", full_text: "FRONT-END DEVELOPER\n \nThis role is perfect for someone that places major emphasis and value both on style and UX with magical functionality.\n \nJoin us to be a key founding member of our fast growing company on the cutting edge of both technology and design. Yes, yes we have great benefits--medical, vision, gym, lunch time yoga, rooftop parties, Poland Spring cooler, 360 windows -- even in the bathroom, dogs are welcome and we do call for milkshakes, sushi and treats (us and dogs) all the time!\n \nYou happy makes up appy!\n \nYou should be able to:\n• Work with both product dev teams & backend developers\n• Have a Good eye for design\n• Be able to learn as you go, ask questions, show confidence AND have an opinion \n• Read and understand software APIs and technical documentation\n• Create beautiful and scalable code that is well structured and documented\n• Architect CSS that is scalable, reusable\n• Knowledge of cross-browser issues / support (IE 8 and up)\n \n \nThis matters:\nHTML5 /CSS3/SASS\nPHP experience (nice to have Drupal)\njQuery / AJAX\njQuery-UI / jQuery-UI widgets /jQuery-mobile\nGit/Github \nMac OSx command line\nPhotoshop / Adobe Creative Suite \nPrincipals of DRY &  progressive enhancement in software design", is_draft: true, company_id: 65, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.jobscore.com/jobs/buzzfeed/front-end-engineer/d2YsL8exir4PCLeJe4efaV?ref=rss&sid=68", title: "Front End Engineer", full_text: "Front End Engineer at BuzzFeed in New York, NY\n\nBuzzFeed is seeking an experienced developer who is passionate about developing innovative products and great user interfaces with beautiful front-end code. We're a new kind of media company for the social world. Our technology powers the social distribution of content, detects what is trending on the web, and connects people in realtime with the hottest content of the moment. Our site is a rapidly growing hub for media that reaches over 100 million monthly unique visitors.\n\nThis job is based in our NYC offices and offers a competitive compensation with stock options.\n\n \n\nAbout You\n\n You love the web and building web apps. You have real-world experience shipping code and you want your work to be used by over 80 million people every month.\nYou love Javascript, HTML, CSS and all their quirks. Mastery of JS Frameworks like Prototype and JQuery with ability to use as a tool, not a crutch.\nYou live and breath AJAX, semantic layouts, browser testing, MVC, Firebug/Chrome Dev Tools, and all that is modern front-end web development.\nYou understand and can contribute to product design. You’re not “technically” a designer, but you appreciate and understand good UI design, UX, and typography.\nComfort with git, linux, and virtualized cross-os/browser development\n \n\nAbout The Job\n\n \n\nYou’ll be creating complex interfaces and real applications with Javascript, not just adding some pretty JQuery effects. You’ll also be working with cross-browser HTML, CSS, and template code, and exploring new front-end technologies with Canvas, HTML5, CSS3, etc. We have an agile, iterative development process. We deploy early and often. We favor experimentation over perfection, but know when it’s important to get it right. We’re building a small, collaborative team. We’re looking for motivated individuals who can work both independently and collaboratively, own their projects, and become key contributors. We don’t want worker drones.\n\n \n\nPluses\n\nExperience with Facebook Connect, Twitter Login, OAuth, etc\nExperience with Selenium or similar tools to test front-end code Experience with mobile web development and technologies\nExperience with server-side languages like PHP, Perl, or Python and corresponding front-end templating syntaxes like mustache, template toolkit, and jade", is_draft: true, company_id: 159, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: "BuzzFeed is seeking an experienced developer who is passionate about developing innovative products and great user interfaces with beautiful front-end code. We're a new kind of media company for the social world. Our technology powers the social distribution of content, detects what is trending on the web, and connects people in realtime with the hottest content of the moment. Our site is a rapidly growing hub for media that reaches over 100 million monthly unique visitors.", key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
