  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/consulting-engineer", title: "Consulting Engineer", full_text: "MongoDB is looking for a team of consulting engineers to further our ongoing plans for world domination! As a technical consultant, you'll be MongoDB's ambassador to our clients and other MongoDB users. These positions are located in New York, Palo Alto, or Washington DC and will require North American travel (expected 50% of the time).Responsibilities You'll deliver advisory consulting to and lead comprehensive training sessions with MongoDB's clients, helping them solve mission-critical challenges in areas as varied as schema design, performance optimization (both in a database and in an application), software architecture, production operations When in the MongoDB office, you'll work with our team of software engineers and support staff to provide top-quality support for MongoDB users Requirements Excellent analytic and diagnostic skills are paramount, every other detail is negotiable 3+ years of software development/consulting/support experience desired Competence in at least one of the following languages (in no particular order): Java, C#, Ruby, PHP, Perl, Python, C++ Experience developing or supporting applications in a few different verticals is a plus Strong database knowledge is a plus; MongoDB experience is a double-plus You have a broad familiarity with enterprise-scale software architectures, application development methodologies, and deployment/operational considerations You're interested in a very customer-facing role, work well both alone and in teams (so excellent interpersonal and written communication skills are required) Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, sub_dept: "Technical Services", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/nodejs-driver-engineer", title: "Node.js Driver Engineer", full_text: "You will be the voice of Node.js, on both the MongoDB team and within the broader MongoDB community. You will be responsible for supporting MongoDB in the Node.js ecosystem through driver development, integration with open source tools, community support, and developer advocacy.Responsibilities Advocate the adoption of MongoDB to the broader Node.js developer community Work with exciting companies such as Craigslist and foursquare to help them with their MongoDB implementations Contribute to and create open source applications and libraries Evangelize our developer products in person and online by presenting at conferences, blogging, writing technical tutorials, and other similar activities Requirements Strong experience programming in and a passion for Node.js Active participant and contributor to open source Experience blogging and writing technical articles on Node.js, ideally with an existing follower base Considerable success as a software developer, architect, technology evangelist, CTO, or consultant working with web or mobile technologies Strong command of web application or mobile application development landscapes Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/network-engineer", title: "Network Engineer", full_text: "You are a Network Engineer with experience designing and implementing multiple networks globally. Your job will be to create and maintain a secure network between our offices, EC2, and co-located data centers. In this critical role, you will be the network specialist within our fast-paced DevOps Team. Responsibilities Configure and maintain the network infrastructure for our office, data centers, and production environment Build a secure, globally distributed environment for MongoDB Work within our DevOps Team to create scalable networks, and improve our existing network Requirements 5+ years of experience working with Cisco and Juniper products Experience building and maintaining a globally distributed network You have worked with multiple networking protocols, including BGP Basic knowledge of Linux systems Experience with Meraki networks is a plus Familiarity with scripting languages (Python, JavaScript, Perl) and with MongoDB a big plus Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 5, sub_dept: "Dev Ops", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.buzztable.com/company/careers", title: "Software Engineer", full_text: "855-321-buzz • sign in why buzztable product customers support company join our team at buzztable, we are building products that are shaping the future of restaurant dining... and we could use your help. we are headquartered in the chelsea area of downtown new york city. if you're interested in joining us, check out these opportunities: perks for all competitive salaries and equity packages coverage for medical, dental, and vision insurance endless whiskey and beer on tap flexible vacations team getaways current opportunities frontend engineeryou probably have an eye for design, but enjoy making concepts come to life. we appreciate what john resig did for the community, but cringe when newbies on stackoverflow think jquery=javascript. at buzztable, you'll work directly with the founder to craft the next generation of restaurant technology. we expect you to have an expert knowledge of javascript, and have the ability to write and debug ui components. a bs or ms degree in comupter science or a related technical field is preferred. how to apply: the window object of this page has a \"bt\" property in it. find the string of the following object bt.ui.messagebox._container. then, calculate the problem below and append the result to your answer. (function(x){ delete x; return x; })(1); once you have the solution, say hello at apply+<answer>@buzztable.com software engineerif you started programming before you had a cell phone this position is probably for you. you like to tinker with things, see what's under the hood, and try to break it (and improve it). at buzztable, you'll work directly with the founder to build and scale the next generation of restaurant technology. our backend is mostly written in php (some ruby), but knowledge and interest in node.js, ruby, or python is welcomed. 5+ years experience building products. this doesn't mean 5 years after college... if you started building products at 17 and you're 22... you're welcome to apply. how to apply: say hello at the solution to this problem. apply+((610+01112)>>1)@buzztable.com merchant sales internhands down the best way to get sales experience before you graduate. you'll work directly with sales veterans. our sales team has years of experience working for hearst and clear channel communications before applying their techniques to the startup environment. at buzztable, you'll do everything from prospecting and converting leads to shadowing our sales team in the field and responding to restaurant support requests. if this is you, send us an e-mail at apply+sales@buzztable.com. about team press careers next steps buzztable demo watch this short demo and learn how buzztable can help you manage your wait and connect with your guests.watch now resources news social media wait list management contact sales or call 855-321-buzz about testimonials pricing press blog legal privacy help buzztable on facebook buzztable on twitter buzztable on linkedin buzztable on foursquare buzztable waitlist on itunes app store buzztable blog © 2013 buzztable, inc. all rights reserved. proudly made in nyc.", is_draft: true, company_id: 160, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 5, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.buzztable.com/company/careers", title: "Frontend Engineer", full_text: "Frontend Engineer\nYou probably have an eye for design, but enjoy making concepts come to life. We appreciate what John Resig did for the community, but cringe when newbies on stackoverflow think jQuery=JavaScript.\n\nAt BuzzTable, you'll work directly with the founder to craft the next generation of restaurant technology. We expect you to have an expert knowledge of JavaScript, and have the ability to write and debug UI components. A BS or MS degree in Comupter Science or a related technical field is preferred.\n\nHow to Apply: The window Object of this page has a \"BT\" property in it. Find the string of the following object\nBT.UI.MessageBox._container\n. Then, calculate the problem below and append the result to your answer.\n\n(function(x){\n   delete x;\n   return x;\n})(1);\n            \nOnce you have the solution, say hello at apply+<answer>@buzztable.com", is_draft: true, company_id: 160, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 2, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/java-driver-engineer", title: "Java Driver Engineer", full_text: "You will be the voice of Java, on both the MongoDB internal team and within the broader MongoDB community. You will be responsible for supporting MongoDB in the Java ecosystem through driver development, integration with open source tools, community support, and developer advocacy.Responsibilities Advocate the adoption of MongoDB to the broader Java developer community Work with exciting companies such as Craigslist and foursquare to help them with their MongoDB implementations Contribute to and create open source applications and libraries Evangelize our developer products in person and online by presenting at conferences, blogging, writing technical tutorials, and other similar activities Requirements Strong experience programming in and a passion for Java Active participant and contributor to open source Experience blogging and writing technical articles on Java, ideally with an existing follower base Considerable success as a software developer, architect, technology evangelist, CTO, or consultant working with web or mobile technologies Strong command of web application or mobile application development landscapes", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 3, sub_dept: "Back-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/systems-engineer", title: "Systems Engineer", full_text: "You are a hard-core kernel tweaker and optimizer, scripter and orchestration wizard, network, security, and storage infrastructure specialist. Your job will be to work closely with the core engineering team to develop best practices, validate & optimize infrastructure configurations, develop automation and help our customers build and engineer state of the art MongoDB deployments. You must have direct hands on experience operating modern high scale web based applications.Responsibilities Develop best practices for deployment (e.g. HA, DR) and maintenance (e.g. expanding file-system, cluster recovery etc.) Understand the performance impact of kernel configurations, BIOS settings, NIC/HBA/RAID setup Understand where and how to scale Assist engineering triaging customers deployments, performance issues, debugging the full application life cycle Maintain linux packages and recipes for automated installers (chef,puppet) Document and/or provide input to documentation and white papers Requirements 5-7 years of system administration or development operations Day-to-Day management of a production cluster of 50+ nodes Familiarity with scripting languages (Python, JavaScript, Perl) and with MongoDB a big plus Excellent analytical skills Excellent verbal and written skills BSc in Computer Science Nice to Haves You want to be part of a great team building the most significant database innovation in decades You consider yourself an expert level administration \"geek\", build your own kernels and want to expand your knowledge You're flexible, joining a small team, so you're willing to take on a wide variety of responsibilities You are well organized, used to keeping many balls in the air at the same time Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 5, sub_dept: "Dev Ops", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/mongodb-uiux-summer-intern", title: "MongoDB UI/UX Summer Intern", full_text: "MongoDB is seeking an interaction experience intern to focus on user interface development for our online products and services. You will be responsible for UI design and implementation for mongodb.org, the MongoDB Monitoring Service (MMS) and other products and services we develop, and serving as an advocate for users of these products throughout the design and development process. Responsibilities Help define and implement user experience for MongoDB related online products and services Develop a deep understanding of users through ongoing research and analysis of user behavior patterns, advocate for the user Collaborate with MongoDB Engineering to research, design and develop user interfaces for MongoDB products and services, partnering with engineers for design and implementation Assist our software engineering interns in making their \"backend\" projects more beautiful and user friendly Requirements BA/BS in human/computer interaction and/or interaction design or 1-3 years’ relevant work experience Skills and experience prototyping, designing, testing, implementing, and evaluating user experience for web based applications Familiarity with usability heuristics and best practices in UX design Ability to create wireframes and processflow diagrams, strong wireframe and user testing skills Ability to plan and administer usability tests Strong portfolio of visual design examples Strong experience with HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript Experience working with version control systems, specifically git Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/technical-writer-documentation-specialist", title: "Technical Writer, Documentation Specialist", full_text: "You want to help us develop the best technical documentation, tutorials, reference materials, and educational materials possible to support the MongoDB and its users.Responsibilities Work as a part of the engineering team to document new features and products Develop and maintain new documentation and other technical materials to support users of MongoDB Organize complex information in easy to understand documents, tutorials, and reference material Review and edit documentation and specifications from other engineers and Technical Writers Requirements Flexiblity. You are comfortable joining a small team, where you'll be responsible for writing and maintaining documentation for a variety of products and services to support many different kinds of users Experience writing clear and concise technical documentation for complex topics Experience organizing, structuring, and maintaining large bodies of documentation Familiarity with systems software (e.g. Unix/Linux, Databases) as well as web development tools and practices Ability to read, understand, and communicate the function and behavior of code Excellent analytic and problem solving skills Excellent verbal and written communication skills You're technically inclined and curious, and are comfortable working closely with, and understanding the language and concerns of, database kernel engineers, administrators, and application developers You're interested in databases, software development, and open source are great and want to contribute to these kinds of projects You want to contribute to building great open source database software Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, sub_dept: "Technical Services", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/online-education-summer-software-engineering-intern", title: "Online Education, Summer Software Engineering", full_text: "You will work with engineers on the education team to build an interactive lesson track that teaches students how to use MongoDB using the technology framework at codecademy.com. Today, codecademy has no direct support for MongoDB lessons, although they use MongoDB to deploy their platform. Your first task will be to build the software that allows online assessment of MongoDB skills in the browser, possibly leveraging the existing MongoDB-in-a-browser work. You will build an extension to codecademy that will allow anyone to create interactive MongoDB lesson tracks, and then you will implement the first track so that the millions of users of codecademy can learn about MongoDB. This will be a 10 week internship with the possibility of an extension. Requirements In the process of receiving a BS or MS in Computer Science Interested in online education Experience with front-end web development Experience with mobile development a plus Prior experience with MongoDB and a genuine interest in databases a HUGE plus!", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 0, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: ["In the process of receiving a BS or MS in Computer Science", "Experience with front-end web development", "Experience with mobile development a plus", "genuine interest in databases a HUGE plus"], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://arc90.recruiterbox.com/jobs/22144/", title: "Web Designer", full_text: "arc90 is looking for a web designer to join our team. we’re looking for a designer that understands and values the impact that strong visual design has on the usability of a web application, a designer that works with the user in mind at all times. we need someone who can create highly detailed, polished interface designs for web apps that thousands of users interact with daily. along with being a strong visual designer, we are looking for someone who can take their finished designs and make them live and breathe using standards-driven, semantic html, css and javascript. you are our ideal candidate if you: love what you do can show us that your love for design translates into high quality work can communicate and collaborate exceptionally well in a team environment have at least a working knowledge of html/css/javascript (the more advanced, the better) we are not looking for: freelancers, design shops, outsourcers, etc. this is a full-time, in-house position only. graphic designers without web design experience no recruiters please about us arc90 is part of the sfx family of companies. we are a team of designers, developers, and strategists dedicated to building the next generation of electronic music experiences. we offer a relaxed and fun work environment where your input and abilities will have a direct impact on the end product of every project you are a part of. you’ll be part of a tight-knit, supportive, creative, collaborative community that is passionate about building great user experiences, learning new skills and techniques, and doing the right thing. join us! to apply if you feel you’d be a good fit at arc90, send your online portfolio and a short note about yourself. feel free to include links to github, dribbble, etc. as well. fair warning: if you send an email without a link to your portfolio (that showcases web design work), you’re out of the running! apply for this position or see other jobs at arc90 application form first name * last name email * phone * resume website / blog / portfolio * github profile why do you want to work at arc90?", is_draft: true, company_id: 66, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: ["strong visual design", "highly detailed, polished interface designs", "take their finished designs and make them live and breathe using standards-driven, semantic HTML, CSS and Javascrip", "Can show us that your love for design translates into high quality work", "at least a working knowledge of HTML/CSS/Javascript (the more advanced, the better)"], req_skills: []},
  {link: "https://arc90.recruiterbox.com/jobs/25733/", title: "Front End Web Developer", full_text: "Arc90 is looking for a brilliant front-end developer to join our team to work on an exciting new music platform! Our ideal candidate is experienced with different front end technologies and has an eye for design. You definitely: Are a smart, motivated, focused person who enjoys creating great software. Enjoy working with a team of smart folks, but can work independently when needed. Solid JavaScript skills: you know the good parts and when its okay to use the bad. Have experience with frameworks and libraries, but know when to roll your own. Know HTML and CSS like the back of your hand. Care about creating thoughtful, semantic markup. Have created customer-facing web applications in the past. Have a bias towards shipping software. You understand technical debt and why it is sometimes necessary. Are passionate about your craft. You might be writing your own game, or hack on an open-source project - we want people who love what they do. In our wildest dreams, you: Are familiar with responsive design. Know your way around back-end code and build tools like Rake, Grunt, etc. Understand and have worked with RESTful APIs. Like to play around with transpiler languages like CoffeeScript, ClojureScript, etc. About us Arc90 is part of the SFX family of companies. We are a team of designers, developers, and strategists dedicated to building the next generation of electronic music experiences. We offer a relaxed and fun work environment where your input and abilities will have a direct impact on the end product of every project you are a part of. You’ll be part of a tight-knit, supportive, creative, collaborative community that is passionate about building great user experiences, learning new skills and techniques, and doing the right thing. Join us! To apply: Send a short note introducing yourself and why this position appeals to you. Include a resume and some samples of your work: this means code samples and a link to a portfolio if you have one. Applicants who do not send code samples will not be considered... we like people who can read directions! Apply for this position or See other jobs at Arc90 Application Form First Name * Last Name Email * Phone * Resume * Website / Blog / Portfolio * Github Profile Why do you want to work at Arc90? *", is_draft: true, company_id: 66, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 1, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: ["experienced with different front end technologies and has an eye for design", "Solid JavaScript skills: you know the good parts and when its okay to use the bad", "Know HTML and CSS like the back of your hand", "Have experience with frameworks and libraries, but know when to roll your own", "Have created customer-facing web applications in the past.", "familiar with responsive design", "Know your way around back-end code and build tools like Rake, Grunt", "Understand and have worked with RESTful APIs", "Like to play around with transpiler languages like CoffeeScript, ClojureScript"], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/web-application-developer", title: "Web Application Developer", full_text: "MongoDB is looking for a Senior Web Application Developer to join us in building the best database monitoring and Backup systems on the planet. Mongo Management Service (MMS) is the team responsible for the design and development of all products that orbit MongoDB. To date these products include: a freely available, cloud-based monitoring and alerting system for MongoDB and a continuous backup solution for which provides point-in-time recovery for replica sets and cluster-wide snapshots of sharded systems.Responsibilities Design, implement, and test core MMS features in a small team environment that will directly impact the global engineering community Assist support team in using MMS to troubleshoot customer issues with MongoDB Requirements 5+ years experience building web applications front ends using JavaScript, a server side templating language and Java controllers (JSP, Freemaker) 3+ years developing client side web applications. Experience with client side MVC frameworks like Backbone.js, Handlebar.js, bootstrap are a plus! Extensive experience using Ajax, jQuery Familiarity with MongoDB a plus Nice to haves You consider yourself an expert level developer You have good web design chops You're flexible. You'll be joining a small team, so you're willing to take on a wide variety of responsibilities You are well organized, used to keeping many balls in the air at the same time You realize that comprehensive testing is your responsibility as a developer Apply now in New York, NY", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 5, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: []},
  {link: "http://www.mongodb.com/careers/positions/web-application-developer", title: "Web Application Developer", full_text: "web application developer. new york, ny. mongodb is looking for a senior web application developer to join us in building the best database monitoring and backup systems on the planet. mongo management service (mms) is the team responsible for the design and development of all products that orbit mongodb. to date these products include: a freely available, cloud-based monitoring and alerting system for mongodb and a continuous backup solution for which provides point-in-time recovery for replica sets and cluster-wide snapshots of sharded systems.responsibilities.design, implement, and test core mms features in a small team environment that will directly impact the global engineering community.assist support team in using mms to troubleshoot customer issues with mongodb.requirements.5+ years experience building web applications front ends using javascript, a server side templating language and java controllers (jsp, freemaker).3+ years developing client side web applications. experience with client side mvc frameworks like backbone.js, handlebar.js, bootstrap are a plus!.extensive experience using ajax, jquery.familiarity with mongodb a plus. nice to haves.you consider yourself an expert level developer.you have good web design chops.you're flexible. you'll be joining a small team, so you're willing to take on a wide variety of responsibilities.you are well organized, used to keeping many balls in the air at the same time.you realize that comprehensive testing is your responsibility as a developer.apply now in new york, ny.about mongodb.mongodb (from humongous) is reinventing data management and powering big data as the leading nosql database. designed for how we build and run applications today, it empowers organizations to be more agile and scalable. mongodb enables new types of applications, better customer experience, faster time to market and lower costs. mongodb has a thriving global community with more than 6 million downloads, 125,000 online education registrations, 25,000 mongodb user group (mug) members and 20,000 annual mongodb days attendees. the company has more than 900 customers, including many of the world’s largest organizations.to all recruitment agencies: mongodb does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or mongodb employees. mongodb is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. life @ mongodb. 1.2. did you know?. .you can apply for a job using your linkedin account! save time and include added resources by using linkedin to include your resume, work experience, and recommendations in your application.apply now with linkedin. apply now in new york, ny.copyright © 2014 mongodb, inc. legal notices.information you submit as part of your application is subject to the mongodb jobs privacy policy. .", is_draft: true, company_id: 2, dept: "Engineering", years_exp: 5, sub_dept: "Front-End", description: nil, key_phrases: [], req_skills: ["JS: Expert"]},
